1 a Minute is a docu - drama film written and directed by Indian American actress Namrata Singh Gujral , and is based on her own life and the lives of other women who suffered from cancer .
Urban Games ( Chinese : 城市游戏 ) is a 2014 Chinese - United States action - thriller film directed by Bob Brown and Zhang Peng and starring Shawn Dou and Michelle Chen .

Annai Bhoomi 3D is a 1985 Tamil - language Indian feature film starring Vijayakanth in lead role .

Judge Not ; or The Woman of Mona Diggings is a 1915 American drama film starring Julia Dean and featuring Harry Carey .

The Spencer repeating rifle was adopted by the Union Army , especially by the cavalry , during the American Civil War , but did not replace the standard issue muzzle - loading rifled muskets in use at the time .

John Durbin Ward ( February 11 , 1819 -- May 22 , 1886 ) was an Ohio lawyer , politician , newspaper publisher , and American Civil War officer .
The five Sullivan brothers were World War II sailors who , serving together on the USS Juneau ( CL-52 ) , were all killed in action on its sinking around November 13 , 1942 .

USS Sorrel ( 1864 ) was a small 68-ton steamer purchased by the Union Navy towards the end of the American Civil War .

William Babcock Hazen ( September 27 , 1830 -- January 16 , 1887 ) was a career United States Army officer who served in the Indian Wars , as a Union general in the American Civil War , and as Chief Signal Officer of the U.S. Army .
The Mark 15 torpedo , the standard American destroyer - launched torpedo of World War II , was very similar in design to the Mark 14 torpedo except that it was longer , heavier , and had greater range and a larger warhead .

Theodor Weissenberger ( 21 December 1914 -- 11 June 1950 ) was a German Luftwaffe military aviator during World War II and a fighter ace credited with 208 enemy aircraft shot down in 375 combat missions .

General Sir Kenneth Arthur Noel Anderson , KCB , MC ( 25 December 1891 -- 29 April 1959 ) was a senior British Army officer who saw service in both World War I and World War II . He is mainly remembered as the commander of the First Army during Operation Torch , the Allied invasion of North Africa .

Paul Rand Dixon ( 1913 - 1996 ) was a decorated World War II veteran , chairman and commissioner of the Federal Trade Commission of the United States from 1961 to 1969 and again briefly in 1976 .
Thomas Hoban ( born September 11 , 1872 ) was a coxswain serving in the United States Navy during the Spanish-- American War who received the Medal of Honor for bravery .

Friedrich Körner ( 24 January 1921 -- 3 September 1998 ) was a World War II Luftwaffe Flying ace .

Thelma Johnson Streat ( August 12 , 1911 -- May 1959 ) was an African American artist , dancer , and educator , who gained prominence in the 1940s for her art , performance and work to foster inter - cultural understanding and appreciation .
Guy - Crescent Fagon ( 11 May 1638 -- 11 March 1718 ) was a physician and botanist .
Christopher Carrick ( 1882 -- 1927 ) was a footballer who played for West Ham United , Tottenham Hotspur , Reading , Bradford City and Glentoran as an outside - left .
Daniel Rock ( Very Reverend Canon Rock , D.D. ) ( 31 August 1799 , Liverpool -- 28 November 1871 Kensington , London ) was an English Roman Catholic priest , ecciesiologist and antiquarian .
Ge Xuan ( 164 - -244 ) was a Chinese Taoist .
Chic Calderwood ( 1 September 1937 -- 12 November 1966 ) was a Scottish light - heavyweight boxer from Craigneuk in North Lanarkshire , Scotland who was active from 1957 to 1966 .
Francisco Pereira de Moura ( 1925 - -1998 ) was a Portuguese scholar , economist and politician opposed to the Estado Novo regime .
Heonan of Silla ( died 861 ) ( r. 857 - -861 ) was the 47th king of the Silla kingdom of Korea .
James Yeadon ( 10 December 1861 -- 30 May 1914 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played three times for Yorkshire County Cricket Club in 1888 .
Charles Augustus Lafayette Lamar ( 1824 - 1865 ) the son of Gazaway Bugg Lamar was born and raised in Savannah , Georgia .
Charles George Broyden ( 3 February 1933 -- 20 May 2011 ) was a mathematician who specialized in optimization problems and numerical linear algebra .
Gum Yuen ( October 1875 -- 15 May 1943 ) was an Australian cabinetmaker , Chinese community leader , furniture manufacturer and restaurateur .
James Vincent Cleary ( 18 September 1828 -- 24 February 1898 ) was a Canadian Roman Catholic priest and Archbishop of Kingston , Ontario .
Frank Runacres ( 2 June 1904 - 1974 ) was an English painter who worked in both watercolours and oil .
B. K. Gadhvi ( 1937 -- 2005 ) was a leader of Indian National Congress from Gujarat and was a member of the Seventh , Eighth and Eleventh Lok Sabhas from 1980 to 1989 and from 1996 to 1997 representing the Banaskantha Parliamentary Constituency .
Ralph Robert Watts Sherman Stonor , 6th Baron Camoys DL JP ( 5 July 1913 -- 9 March 1976 ) was an English aristocrat and Justice of the Peace .
Father Matta El Meskeen or Matthew the Poor , born Youssef Iskandar ( 20 September 1919 -- 8 June 2006 ) was an Egyptian Coptic Orthodox monk .
Martin Kavanagh ( 1895 --1987 ) was a teacher and historian .
Gaius Caesonius Macer Rufinianus ( c. AD 157 -- c. AD 237 ) was a Roman military officer and senator who was appointed suffect consul in around AD 197 or 198 .
Samuel Goodere ( 1687 - -1741 ) was a captain in the British Royal Navy , who was the third and youngest son of Sir Edward Goodere , 1st Baronet .
John de la Pole , 1st Earl of Lincoln ( 1462/1464 -- 16 June 1487 ) was a leading figure in the Yorkist aristocracy during the Wars of the Roses .
Franciska Gaal ( 1 February 1904 -- 2 January 1973 ) was a Jewish Hungarian cabaret artist and film actress .
Sir John Rogerson ( 1648 - -1724 ) was an Irish politician , wealthy merchant and property developer .
Sir Marmaduke Gresham , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1627 -- 14 April 1696 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 and from 1685 to 1689 .
Martha Thompson ( 1731 - -1820 ) was an English Methodist .
Peter G. Fletcher ( 9 January 1936 -- 21 May 1996 ) was a noted British orchestral and choral conductor , music educator and author .
Margaret Eliza Maltby ( 10 December 1860 -- 3 May 1944 ) was an American physicist notable for measurement of high electrolytic resistances and conductivity of very dilute solutions .
Alexander Macbean ( died 1784 ) was a British writer and amanuensis , known as a lexicographer .
Zita Linker ( Hebrew : ציטה לינקר‎ , born 1 March 1917 , died 26 January 2009 ) was an Israeli politician who briefly served as a member of the Knesset for Likud in 1977 .
Sir William Thorold , 1st Baronet ( 1591 - -1678 ) was an English landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1661 to 1677 .
Sir Edward Carne ( c.1500 - 19 January 1561 ) was a Welsh Renaissance scholar , diplomat and English Member of Parliament .
Henryk Ehrlich ( sometimes spelled Henryk Erlich ; 1882 -- 15 May 1942 ) was an activist of the Bund , member of the Petrograd Soviet , Warsaw City Council and member of the executive committee of the Second International .
Philip Roche ( died 1798 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic priest and commander during the Irish Rebellion of 1798 .
Stephen of Aumale ( c. 1070 - -1127 ) was Count of Aumale from before 1089 to 1127 , and Lord of Holderness .
Humphrey Weld ( died 29 November 1610 ) was an English merchant who was Lord Mayor of London in 1608 .
Edgar William Boyles ( 24 March 1921 -- 7 May 2001 ) was a senior British civil servant who became Under - Secretary at the Inland Revenue ( 1975 - -81 ) .
Joaquín Canaves ( 8 January 1640 - 3 June 1721 ) was a Spanish prelate who served as the Bishop of Malta from 1713 till 1721 .
Fraser Frisell ( 1774 - -1846 ) , was a friend of Chateaubriand and Joubert .
Mária Vadász , née Vanya ( 1 January 1950 -- 18 August 2009 ) was a Hungarian handball player , Olympic bronze medalist and World Championship silver medalist .
Shamsul Huda Chaudhury ( Bengali শামসুল হুদা চেীধুরী 1 May 1920 - 15 February 2000 ) was a renowned Bangladeshi politician , mass - media administrator , minister and two time Speaker of Bangladesh Jatiya Sangsad .
Clémentine Hélène Dufau ( 18 August 1869 -- 18 March 1937 ) was a painter .
John Robert Godley ( 29 May 1814 -- 17 November 1861 ) was an Irish statesman and bureaucrat .
Władysław of Bytom ( Polish : Władysław bytomski ; 1277/83 -- around 8 September 1352 ) , was a Duke of Koźle during 1303 - 1334 , Duke of Bytom from 1316 , Duke of Toszek since 1329 and Duke of Siewierz during 1328 - -1337 .
Enid Charles ( 29 December 1894 -- 26 March 1972 ) was a socialist , feminist and statistician who was a pioneer in the fields of demography and population statistics .
Sergeant Terrence Begley ( died 25 August 1864 ) was an Irish soldier who fought in the American Civil War .
Saint Fer dá Chrích mac Suibni ( also called Feardachrich , Feradach , Ferdachricus , Fer dá Crích , Ferdacrioch , ffear - Dachrich , Firdacrich ) b. c. 710 -- d. 18 May 768 , was the Abbot of Armagh , Ireland from 758 to 18 May 768 .
Otto Bittorf ( 13 July 1917 -- 11 January 1999 ) was a highly decorated Oberleutnant in the Wehrmacht during World War II and a Major in the Bundeswehr .
Sultan Jauhar ul - Alam Amauddin Syah ( died 1726 ) was the twenty - first sultan of Aceh .
Joseph Panny ( 23 October 1796 -- 7 September 1838 ) was an Austrian composer and violinist who lived primarily in Vienna .
David Ruthven , 2nd Lord Ruthven of Freeland ( died April 1701 ) was a Scottish politician .
Edmund Bunny ( 1540 - -1619 ) was an Anglican churchman of Calvinist views .
Thomas Mullins , 1st Baron Ventry ( 25 October 1736 -- 11 January 1824 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and peer .
Gwylog ap Beli ( 695?--725 ) was one of the rulers of the Kingdom of Powys , son of Beli ap Eiludd .
Enrico Gasparri S.T.D. JUD ( 25 July 1871 -- 20 May 1946 ) was a Roman Catholic Cardinal and Archbishop .
Robert Cleveland ( 1744 - -1812 ) was an American revolutionary from Wilkes County , North Carolina , and served as a Captain in the militia under his brother Colonel Benjamin Cleveland .
Billy Spence ( died 1980 ) was a loyalist activist in Northern Ireland .
Rajeshwari Chatterjee ( 24 January 1922 -- 3 September 2010 ) was an Indian scientist and an academic .
John James Maximilian Oertel ( born at Ansbach , Bavaria , 27 April 1811 ; died at Jamaica , New York , 21 August 1882 ) was a German - American journalist .
Rabbi Selig Starr , born Zelig Starobinski ( 15 June 1893 Yanow or Yanaveh , Poland -- 2 November 1989 ) , was a 20th - century Talmudic scholar in Poland , Chicago and Jerusalem .
Åsmund Sveen ( 28 April 1910 -- 31 January 1963 ) was a Norwegian poet , novelist and literary critic .
Fyodor Koriatovych ( Polish : Fiodor Koriatowic , Rusyn : Федур Коръятович , Ukrainian : Федір Коріятович , Lithuanian : Teodoras Karijotaitis ) ( died 1414 in Mukacheve ) was a Ruthenian prince of Lithuanian origins , son of Karijotas , Duke of Navahrudak , and grandson of Gediminas , Grand Duke of Lithuania .
Davor Dujmović ( 20 September 1969 -- 31 May 1999 ) was a Bosnian actor best known for his memorable roles in Emir Kusturica 's movies as Mirza in When Father Was Away on Business , Perhan in Time of the Gypsies and Bata in Underground .
Walter Einsel ( 1926 - -1998 ) was an American sculptor and illustrator from Westport , Connecticut .
Ernest John Christopher Polge CBE , FRS ( 16 August 1926 - - 17 August 2006 ) was an English biologist , most noted for his work in cryopreservation .
István Móna ( 17 September 1940 -- 28 July 2010 ) was a Hungarian modern pentathlete and Olympic champion .
Gaius Avidius Nigrinus ( died 118 ) was a Roman who lived between the 1st and 2nd centuries .
Ivan Vurnik ( 1 June 1884 -- 8 April 1971 ) was a Slovene architect that helped found the Ljubljana School of Architecture .
Alexander Stopford Catcott ( 1692 - -1749 ) was an English churchman from Bristol , and headmaster of Bristol Grammar School from 1722 to 1743 or 1744 .
Henry Slade ( 1835 - 1905 ) was a famous fraudulent medium who lived and practiced in both Europe and North America .
Frederick Forchheimer ( 1853 - -1913 ) was an American pediatrician known for describing Forchheimer spots .
Charlotta Maria Thérèse Lizinka Dyrssen , née af Ugglas ( 28 July 1866 -- 9 September 1952 ) , was a Swedish women 's rights activist .
George Jackson Churchward CBE ( 31 January 1857 -- 19 December 1933 ) was Chief Mechanical Engineer of the Great Western Railway ( GWR ) in the United Kingdom from 1902 to 1922 .
Geoff Stone ( 10 April 1924 -- 1993 ) was an English footballer who made 35 appearances in the Football League playing as a centre half for Notts County and Darlington .
John Tiktak ( 1916 , Kareak camp-1981 ) was a Canadian Inuk sculptor who spent most of his artistic career in Rankin Inlet .
Charles Wagley ( 1913 - -1991 ) was an American anthropologist and leading pioneer in the development of Brazilian anthropology .
Baltasar Jaime Martínez Compañón ( born 1737 , died 1797 ) was a Spanish prelate who served as Bishop of Trujillo , Peru , Peru from 1779 to 1790 , at Trujillo Cathedral , and Archbishop of Bogotá , New Granada , from 1790 to 1797 .
Mary Heaton Vorse O'Brien ( 1874 - -1966 ) was an American journalist , labor activist , and novelist .
Francesco Bassi ( early 1642 - 1732 ) was an Italian painter active in the early - Baroque period , mainly in his hometown of Cremona , but also in Venice .
John Terence Reese ( 28 August 1913 -- 29 January 1996 ) was a British bridge player and writer , regarded as one of the finest of all time in both fields .
Ruth Plumly Thompson ( 27 July 1891 -- 6 April 1976 ) was an American writer of children 's stories , best known for writing many novels placed in Oz , the fictional land of L. Frank Baum 's classic children 's novel The Wonderful Wizard of Oz and its sequels .
Udai Singh II ( 4 August 1522 -- 28 February 1572 ) was the Maharana of Mewar and the founder of the city of Udaipur in the present day Rajasthan state of India .
Julen Goikoetxea ( 18 August 1985 -- 7 October 2006 ) was a Basque racing cyclist from Ondarroa .
Kedamangalam Sadanandan ( 1926 -- 13 April 2008 ) was a Kadhaprasangam artist , film actor , screenwriter and lyricist from Kerala .
Thomas Douglas Guest ( 1781 - -1845 ) was a British historical- and portrait painter .
Aaron Lockett ( 1 December 1892 -- 10 February 1965 ) was an English footballer and cricketer .
Stacey Grimaldi ( 18 October 1790 -- 28 March 1863 ) , was an English lawyer and antiquary .

Angelo Celli ( 25 March 1857 -- 2 November 1914 ) was an Italian physician , hygienist , parasitologist and philanthropist known for his pioneering works in malarial parasite and control of malaria .
William Noy ( 1577 -- 9 August 1634 ) was a noted British jurist .
Francisco Méndez ( 1907 - 1962 ) was a Guatemalan poet and short - story writer born in Joyabaj , El Quiché .
Sir William Tredenham ( ca . 1638 - 12 May 1662 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1659 and 1662 .
Jan Piekałkiewicz ( 19 September 1892 -- 19 February 1943 ) was a Polish economist and statistician , politician and the Polish Underground State 's Government Delegate .
Leopold Bellak ( 1916 - -2002 ) was an psychologist who worked on clinical psychological assessment , particularly with the Thematic Apperception Test .
Ignazio Buttitta ( 19 September 1899 -- 5 April 1997 ) was an Italian dialectal poet .
William Marion Reedy ( 1862 - -1920 ) was a St. Louis - based editor best known for his promotion of the poets Sara Teasdale , Edgar Lee Masters , and Carl Sandburg to the audience of his newspaper , Reedy 's Mirror .
Amarendranath Chatterjee ( Bengali : অমরেন্দ্রনাথ চট্টোপাধ্যায় ) ( 1 July 1880 -- 4 September 1957 ) was an Indian independence movement activist .
Harry Clinton Gossard ( 1884 - -1954 ) was an American educator and geometer .
Spence Broughton ( c. 1746 -- 14 April 1792 ) was an English highwayman who was executed for robbing the Sheffield and Rotherham mail .
Donal Keenan ( 1919 -- 19 September 1990 ) was an Irish Gaelic games administrator , Gaelic football coach , selector and former player .
Dorothy B. Hughes ( 10 August 1904 -- 6 May 1993 ) was an American crime writer and literary critic .
Queen Heonjung ( 헌정왕후;獻貞王后 , c. 966 -- 1 August 992 ) was a Korean Goryeo dynastys queen .
Patrick John Morris ( 13 April 1948 -- 16 January 2008 ) was a British composer , musician , and songwriter .
Tommaso Tamburini ( 6 March 1591 -- 10 October 1675 ) was an Italian Jesuit moral theologian .
Hendrick ten Oever ( 1639 -- 1716 ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
John Grimaldi ( 22 May 1955 -- 15 November 1983 ) was a musician , songwriter and artist .
Thomas Wallensis ( died 1255 ) was a Welsh Franciscan , archdeacon of Lincoln and then bishop of St. David 's .
Rolf Maximilian Sievert ( Swedish : ( ˈrɔlf maksɪmˈiːlɪan ˈsiːvəʈ ) ; 6 May 1896 -- 3 October 1966 ) was a medical physicist whose major contribution was in the study of the biological effects of radiation .
Charles - Hippolyte - Philippe Spinola , known as Philippe Spinola ( 1612 - -1670 ) was count of Bruay , baron of Andre , and lord of Kounice , a lordship which he later exchanged for those of Calonne - sur - la - Lys and Viefville , Grandee of Spain and Knight of the Golden Fleece .
Charles Hill , Baron Hill of Luton PC ( 15 January 1904 -- 22 August 1989 ) was a British cabinet minister , doctor and television executive .
Niklaus Niggeler ( 3 May 1817 - 26 May 1872 ) was a Swiss politician from the canton of Bern .
Heinrich Wilhelm Ludolf ( 20 December 1655 -- 25 January 1712 ) was a German Pietist , secretary to Prince George of Denmark , and ecumenical traveller .
Wang Yucheng ( or Yu - Ch'eng ) ( 王禹偁 , 954 - -1001 ) was a Chinese poet from Juye in the Shandong province .
Petre Mavrogheni ( 1819 -- 20 April 1887 ) also known as Petru Mavrogheni was a Romanian politician who served as the Minister of Foreign Affairs from 11 May until 13 July 1866 and as the Minister of Finance .
Jan Balabán ( 29 January 1961 -- 23 April 2010 ) was a Czech writer , journalist , and translator .
Timothy J. Stryker , better known as Tim Stryker or Stryker ( 9 December 1954 -- 6 August 1996 ) was a computer programmer , best known as the creator of MajorBBS , a computer bulletin board software package .
Pap Cheyassin Secka or Pap Cheyassin Ousman Secka ( June 1942 -- 29 March 2012 ) was a Gambian lawyer and politician .
Kunnakudi Vaidyanathan ( 2 March 1935 -- 8 September 2008 ) was an Indian classical music violinist .
Eleanor Oglethorpe ( 1662 - -1732 ) was an employee of the royal household during the reigns of Charles II and James II . She followed James II to France , where he was exiled after the Glorious Revolution .
John Loch ( 8 September 1781 -- 19 February 1868 ) was a Member of Parliament for Hythe and Chairman of the East India Company .
Dennis Brian Close , CBE ( 24 February 1931 -- 13 September 2015 ) was an English cricketer , the youngest man ever to play Test cricket for England .
Miguel Lino de Ezpeleta ( sometimes spelled as de Espeleta ) ( Manila , June 1701 -- Cebu , July 1771 ) was a Spanish Criollo born in Manila who served as the Bishop of Cebu from 1757 until his death in 1771 .
Blessed Caius of Korea ( 1571 in Korea -- 15 November 1624 in Nagasaki , Japan ) is the 128th of the 205 Roman Catholic Martyrs of Japan beatified by Pope Pius IX on 7 July 1867 , after he had canonized the Twenty - six Martyrs of Japan five years before on 8 June 1862 .
Laurence Chisholm Young ( 14 July 1905 -- 24 December 2000 ) was an American mathematician known for his contributions to measure theory , the calculus of variations , optimal control theory , and potential theory .
Vitéz Baron Sándor Szurmay de Uzsok ( 19 December 1860 -- 26 February 1945 ) was a Hungarian military officer and politician , who served as Minister of Defence for the Hungarian portion of the Dual Monarchy of Austria - Hungary between 1917 and 1918 .
James Wood Johnson ( 1856 - -1932 ) was an American businessman and one of the co - founders of Johnson & Johnson .
Ilona Stetina ( 1855 - 1932 ) , was a Romanian pioneer educator and women 's rights activist .
John Tufton , 4th Earl of Thanet ( 7 August 1638 -- 27 April 1680 ) , styled The Honourable John Tufton until 1679 , was an English politician and nobleman .
Romesh Bhandari ( 29 March 1928 -- 7 September 2013 ) was an Indian Foreign Secretary , former Lieutenant Governor of Delhi , Andaman and Nicobar Islands , and former governor of Tripura , Goa and Uttar Pradesh .
Colonel Mariano Chico ( 1796 - -1850 ) served one of the briefest terms as Alta California governor from April 1836 to July 1836 .
John Wygryme ( died 5 October 1468 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1457 to 1468 .
Charles W. Dullea ( May 30 , 1889 -- 1966 ) was the Chief of Police in the San Francisco Police Department from 1940 to 1947 .
Edward William Barnard ( 1791 - -1828 ) , was an English divine , poet and scholar .
Lê Chiêu Thống ( 1765 - -1793 ) , born Lê Duy Khiêm and later Lê Duy Kỳ , was the last king of the Vietnamse Lê dynasty .
Eloy Mestrelle , first name sometimes spelled Eloye , ( d. 1578 ) was a French moneyer who was responsible for introducing milled coinage to England .
James Patrick Mullins ( 5 January 1874 -- 26 November 1965 ) was a Liberal party member of the Canadian House of Commons and served as mayor of Bromptonville at one time .
Hans Henrik Rode ( 9 September 1767 -- 29 December 1830 ) was a Danish - Norwegian military officer .
Arthur Saul ( died 1586 ) was an English Puritan cleric and academic , a Marian exile and canon of Gloucester Cathedral .
António Galvão ( c. 1490 - -1557 ) , known in English as Antonio Galvano , was a Portuguese soldier , chronicler and administrator in the Maluku islands , and a Renaissance historian , the first to present a comprehensive report of all the leading voyages and explorers up to 1550 , either by Portuguese and by other nationalities .
Ivan Rassimov ( Born Ivan Djerasimović ; Serbian Cyrillic : Иван Ђерасимовић ) ( 7 May 1938 -- 14 March 2003 ) was an Italian film actor of Serbian origin who appeared in many horror and exploitation films .
Élie Fruchart ( 8 July 1922 -- 1 July 2003 ) was a French football player who played with US Auchel .
Hasan Moglica ( 1854 - -1915 ) , commonly referred as Hoxhë Moglica , was an Albanian educator , religious leader , engineer , philosopher , nationalist figure and patriot .
Gustav de Vries ( 22 January 1866 - -16 December 1934 ) was a Dutch mathematician , who is best remembered for his work on the Korteweg -- de Vries equation with Diederik Korteweg .
Gustavus Arthur Talbot ( 24 December 1848 - 16 October 1920 ) was a British member of parliament and a Coalition Conservative politician .
Lancelot Brown ( baptised 30 August 1716 -- 6 February 1783 ) , more commonly known as Capability Brown , was an English landscape architect .
Otto Landsberg ( 4 December 1869 -- 9 December 1957 ) was a German jurist , politician and diplomat .
In November 1945 , Mefail Shehu was killed in an ambush with his remaining soldiers by the partisans .
Manuel Moral y Vega ( 16 March 1865 - 7 November 1913 ) was a Portuguese photographer and publisher active in early twentieth - century Peru .
Jens Falkenberg ( 6 May 1875 -- 26 March 1963 ) was a Norwegian equestrian .
Waratton , Waratto , or Warato ( died 686 ) was the mayor of the palace of Neustria and Burgundy on two occasions , owing to the deposition he experienced at the hands of his own faithless son .
Edward Upham ( 1776 - -1834 ) was an English bookseller , antiquarian and orientalist .
Des Hackett ( 1925 -- 7 August 1998 ) was an Australian naturalist .
Joseph Clemens ( 9 December 1862 -- 21 January 1936 ) was an American Methodist Episcopalian chaplain , missionary and plant collector who served and worked in South East Asia and elsewhere .
Peter Stent ( c. 1613 - -1665 ) was a seventeenth - century London printseller , who from the early 1640s until his death ran one of the biggest printmaking businesses of the day .
Carl Wahlbom ( 1810 - -1858 ) was a Swedish military artist .
Álvaro Obregón Tapia ( 18 December 1916 - -27 September 1993 ) was a Mexican political figure who served as governor of the northwestern border state of Sonora from 1955 to 1961 .
James Mursell ( 1893 - -1963 ) wrote extensively about music education and the use of music in a classroom setting .
Pomeroy Wills Powers , known as P.W. Powers , ( 1853 - -1916 ) was an attorney and property developer in Kansas City , Kansas , and Los Angeles , California , where he was president of the City Council in 1900 - -02 .
Charles Edward Davis ( 1827 - -1902 ) was an English architect and antiquary .
Melek Amet ( 4 October 1960 - 22 May 2008 ) was one of the best rated models of the eighties in Communist Romania .
Hugo Birger ( born Hugo Birger Peterson ) ( 12 January 1854 -- 17 June 1887 ) was a Swedish painter .
Sir Thomas Chamberlayne , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1635 - -1682 ) of Wickham and of Northbrooke , Oxfordshire .
Lord Henry George Charles Gordon - Lennox PC ( 2 November 1821 -- 29 August 1886 ) , known as Lord Henry Lennox , was a British Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1846 to 1885 and was a close friend of Benjamin Disraeli .
Shahzada Kashmira Singh Bahadur ( 1821 - 7 May 1844 ) was the sixth son of Ranjit Singh , Maharaja of Sikh Empire .
Jogendra Nath Mandal ( Bengali : যোগেন্দ্রনাথ মণ্ডল ; 29 January 1904 -- 5 October 1968 ) , was one of the central and leading Founding Fathers of modern state of Pakistan , and legislator serving as country 's first minister of law and labour , and also was second minister of commonwealth and Kashmir affairs .
Andrew Petrie ( 1798 - 20 February 1872 ) was a pioneer , architect and builder in Brisbane , Queensland , Australia .
Albrecht Kauw ( 1621 - -1681 ) was a Swiss still - life painter , cartographer and a painter of vedute .
Dr. Dixie Tan died at Singapore General Hospital on 23 April 2014 , aged 78 , following a two - month illness with brain cancer .
Matilda Moldenhauer Brooks ( 1888 - -1981 ) is best remembered for her 1932 discovery that the staining compound methylene blue is an antidote to carbon monoxide and cyanide poisoning .
Warren Stanford Stone ( 1 February 1860 - 12 June 1925 ) was a railway worker who rose to head the Brotherhood of Locomotive Engineers in the United States from 1903 to 1925 .
Pierre Macret ( 1727 - -1796 ) was a well - known Parisian cabinetmaker ( ébéniste ) .
Thomas Cheseman or Baker ( ca . 1488 - -1536 or later ) was an English politician .
Gerald Savory ( 17 November 1909 -- 9 February 1996 ) was an English playwright and screenwriter specialising in comedies .
William Abernethy Drummond ( called Abernethy ; 1719?--1809 ) , was a bishop of Edinburgh .
Thomas Pole ( 13 October 1753 -- 28 September 1829 ) was an American - born English physician and writer .
Senkodi immolated herself in front of the Tahsil office at Kancheepuram at 5.45 p.m , 28 - 08 - 2011 .
Captain Charles Bampfield Yule , R.N. ( 1806 - -1 November 1878 at Anderton , Cornwall ) was an explorer and author of the Admiralty Australia Directory .

Eliyahu Meridor ( Hebrew : אליהו מרידור‎ , 20 July 1914 -- 16 October 1966 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Herut and Gahal from 1959 until his death in 1966 .

Isaac Barré ( 1726 -- 20 July 1802 ) was an Irish soldier and politician .

George Ashburnham , 3rd Earl of Ashburnham , KG , GCH , FSA ( 25 December 1760 -- 27 October 1830 ) was a British peer .
Paul Jousse ( died 1945 ) was a South African white trader in Bechuanaland .
James Chamberlain Baker ( June 2 , 1879 -- 1969 ) was an American Bishop of the Methodist Episcopal Church , The Methodist Church , and the United Methodist Church , elected in 1928 .
P. K. Manthri ( real name P. K. Manthri Kumaran ) ( 31 May 1933 -- 6 December 1984 ) was an Indian cartoonist .
Cyryl Ratajski ( 3 March 1875 , in Zalesie Wielkie -- 19 October 1942 , in Warsaw ) was a Polish politician and lawyer .
Joseph Parslow ( 22 March 1812 -- 4 October 1898 ) was an English manservant , who worked as butler for the English naturalist Charles Darwin for over thirty years .
Anne Sutherland - Leveson - Gower , Duchess of Sutherland VA ( 21 April 1829 -- 25 November 1888 ) , 1st Countess of Cromartie in her own right and known as the Marchioness of Stafford from 1849 to 1861 , was a British peeress .
Lotte Toberentz , born Maria Charlotte Toberentz ( May 27 , 1900 -- after January 1964 ) was the head overseer of the Uckermark concentration camp for girls in its early years .
Percy Holmes ( 25 November 1886 -- 3 September 1971 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played for Yorkshire and England .
Mirza Bashir Ahmad ( 1893 - -1963 ) was an Ahmadiyya scholar and writer , and a son of Mirza Ghulam Ahmad , the founder of the Ahmadiyya movement who had claimed to be the promised Messiah and Mahdi awaited by Muslims .
Richard Norris Wolfenden ( 1854 - 1926 ) was an English physician and oceanographer
Charlie Doherty ( 23 January 1876 -- 5 March 1961 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
David Younghusband ( 1883 - -1965 ) was a residential architect and building contractor in Ottawa , Canada .
Johann Peter Alexander Wagner ( 26 February 17301 - -7 January 1809 ) was a German rococo sculptor .
Israel ben Meir di Curiel ( 1501 - -1573 ) was an influential 16th - century rabbi at Safed , Ottoman Palestine .
Zhang Hongjie ( 1979 - -2004 ) , also known as Steffi Zhang was a 25-year - old Chinese University of Canberra communications student found murdered in her flat in Belconnen in January 2005 .
Shmuel Dayan ( Hebrew : שמואל דיין‎ ; 8 August 1891 -- 11 August 1968 ) was a Zionist activist during the British Mandate of Palestine and an Israeli politician who served in the first three Knessets .
Peter Dowds ( 1871 -- 2 September 1895 ) was a Scottish footballer who played in the Football League for Aston Villa and Stoke .
Sebastiano Ceccarini ( 1703 - -1783 ) , born in Fano , was an Italian Baroque painter .
William McCance ( 1894 - -1970 ) was a Scottish artist , and was second Controller of the Gregynog Press in Powys , mid - Wales .
Furneaux Cook ( 1839 -- 19 January 1903 ) , born John Furneaux Cook , was an English opera singer and actor best known for baritone roles in the comic operas of Gilbert and Sullivan and Alfred Cellier on the London stage .
Johannes Eccard ( 1553 - -1611 ) was a German composer and kapellmeister .
Nicholas I Sanudo ( or Niccolò ; died 1341 ) was the fifth Duke of the Archipelago from 1323 to his death .
Giuseppe De Notaris ( 18 April 1805 , Milan -- 22 January 1877 ) was an Italian botanist generally known for his work with cryptogams native to Italy .
Kjeld Bonfils ( b. Copenhagen , August 23 , 1918 -- 1984 ) was a Danish jazz pianist and vibraphone player .
James Watson Corder ( 1867 - -1953 ) is a historian best remembered for documenting family history in Sunderland , Tyne and Wear , England .
Brian Kuttner ( 11 April 1908 London , England -- 2 January 1992 Birmingham , England ) was an English mathematician who worked on Fourier Series .
Thomas Melvill(e ) ( 1726 -- December 1753 ) was a Scottish natural philosopher , who was active in the fields of spectroscopy and astronomy .
Sir Brook Bridges , 1st Baronet , FRS ( 12 August 1679 - 16 March 1728 ) was a British barrister .
Isabella of Cyprus , also known as Isabelle de Lusignan ( born before March , 1216 or after 1216 -- 1264 ) , was the Princess of Antioch by her marriage .
Count Johan Adam Cronstedt ( 12 December 1749 in Stockholm -- 21 February 1836 in Stockholm ) was a Swedish Lieutenant General and governor of Östergötland County .
Graham Rathbone ( 22 August 1942 -- 8 January 2012 ) was a Welsh professional footballer .
Ilm - ud - din ( 4 December 1908 -- 31 October 1929 ) was a Muslim who murdered a blasphemous book publisher named Mahashe Rajpal for publishing the book Rangila Rasul , that offended religious values of Muslims .
Kurt von Wessely , also Curt von Wessely , ( German pronunciation : ( kʊʁt fɔn vɛsəlɪ ) ; d. 25 October 1917 ) , was an Austrian tennis player who was active during the beginning of the 20th century .
Mohammed Karim ( 1896 -- 1972 ) ( Arabic : محمد كريم‎ ) was an Egyptian film director , writer , and producer .
Charles Warne ( 1802 -- 11 April 1887 ) was an English antiquarian and archæologist .
General William Wemyss of Wemyss ( 9 April 1760 -- 30 November 1852 ) was a Scottish soldier in the British Army and Member of Parliament .
Arthur Lionel Smith ( 1850 -- 12 April 1924 ) was a British historian at the University of Oxford .
Rim Kin(Khmer : រីម គីន ) ( 1911 - -1959 ) was a Cambodian writer , and one of the founders of Cambodian modern literature .
Charles Kassler Jr ( September 9 , 1897 , Denver , Colorado -- April 3 , 1979 , San Diego , California ) was a painter , printmaker , and lithographer .
Saints Castus and Emilius ( died 250 AD ) are venerated as saints and martyrs by the Eastern Orthodox and Roman Catholic Churches .
Thomas Spring of Castlemaine ( died 1597 ) was an English Protestant soldier , landowner and Constable of Castlemaine in County Kerry , Ireland .
DeCoursey Fales ( 1888 - -1966 ) was a lawyer , banker , collector , bibliophile and yachtsman .
Ashraf Marwan ( Arabic : أشرف مروان‎ ) ( 2 February 1944 -- 27 June 2007 ) was an Egyptian billionaire and alleged spy for Israel , or possibly an Egyptian double agent .
August Heinrich Ferdinand Tegetmeyer ( 14 March 1844 Leipzig - 31 May 1912 ) was a German illustrator and engraver who provided the images for a large number of publications .
Major Edward Hay Mackenzie Elliot ( 30 November 1852 -- 5 December 1920 ) was a British soldier who served as Private Secretary to David Boyle , 7th Earl of Glasgow while he was Governor of New Zealand in the 1890s .
Sigurd Syr ( Old Norse : Sigurðr Sýr ) ( died ca . 1018 ) was a Norwegian petty king of Ringerike , a region in Buskerud .
Abraham of Arbela ( died c. 348 ) ( also known as Abramius ) was a bishop of Arbela in Assyria .
Lucien Wulsin III ( 1916 - -2009 ) was a lawyer , entrepreneur , banker , arts advocate , university trustee and erstwhile performer .
Nicholas Cresswell ( 5 January 1750 -- 26 July 1804 ) was an English diarist .
Antonis Katsantonis ( Greek : Αντώνης Κατσαντώνης ; c. 1775 - -1808 ) was a notable Greek klepht who lived in the era before the Greek War of Independence .
June Wandrey Mann ( 1920 - -2005 ) was a First Lieutenant in the U.S. Army Nurse Corps from Wautoma , Wisconsin .
Eivind Groven ( 8 October 1901 -- 8 February 1977 ) was a Norwegian microtonal composer and music - theorist .
Mahaveer Prasad ( Hindi : महावीर प्रसाद ) ( 11 November 1939 -- 28 November 2010 ) was an Indian politician .
Khun Sa ( Burmese : ခွန်ဆာ , pronounced : ( kʰʊ̀ɴ sʰà ) ) , also known as Chang Chi - fu ( Chinese : 張奇夫 ; pinyin : Zhāng Qífú ; Thai : จันทร์ จางตระกูล ; rtgs : Chan Changtrakul ; 17 February 1934 -- 26 October 2007 ) was a Shan warlord .
An Dehai ( Chinese : 安德海 ; pinyin : Ān Déhǎi ; Wade -- Giles : An Te - hai , 1844 -- 12 September 1869 ) was a palace eunuch at the imperial court of the Qing dynasty .
Prof Samuel Newby Curle FRSE ( 1930 - 1989 ) was a notable British mathematician .
Barry Albin - Dyer OBE ( 2 February 1951 -- 6 June 2015 ) was an undertaker whose firm Albin and Sons were known for their work repatriating the bodies of servicemen killed in Iraq and Afghanistan .
Yusuf Warsame Saeed ( Somali : Yuusuf Warsame Saiid ; Arabic : يوسف ارسام سعيد‎ ; died 7 April 2013 ) was a Somali politician .
Al - Mu'ayyad Ahmad ( 944 - 1020 ) was an imam of the Zaydiyyah sect .
James Bell Pettigrew , MD FRS FRSE FRCPE ( 26 May 1834 -- 30 January 1908 ) was a Scottish naturalist and museum curator .
Dr. Thomas Wrigley Grimshaw , CB ( 16 November 1839 -- 23 January 1900 ) was an Irish physician and surgeon who became Registrar General for Ireland from 1879 to 1900 .
Pietro Morgari ( 1852 , Turin - 1885 , London ) was an Italian painter , primarily of portraits .
Alexander Agricola ( /əˈɡrɪkələ/ ; born Alexander Ackerman ; 1445 or 1446 -- 15 August 1506 ) was a Netherlandish composer of the Renaissance writing in the Franco - Flemish style .
King Soane Patita Maituku ( 1947?- ) was the Tu'i Agaifo of the Kingdom of Alo from November 2002 until February 19 , 2008 , when he was deposed as the result of a unanimous decision taken by the kingdom 's four chiefly clans .
Sheyh Hamid - i Vali ( 1331 - -1412 ) , better known by his sobriquet Somuncu Baba , was an ascetic teacher of Islam in Bursa , Turkey , who exerted extensive influence and is known as a Muslim saint .
José Manuel Restrepo Vélez ( 30 December 1781 -- 1 April 1863 ) was an investigator of Colombian flora , political figure and historian .
Jean Abraham Grill ( 21 July 1736 -- 12 March 1792 ) , sometimes called Johan Abraham Grill , was a Swedish merchant , supercargo , director of the Swedish East India Company ( SOIC ) and ironmaster at Godegård with several factories .
Jared Sidney Torrance ( 1853 - -1921 ) was an American real estate developer , best known as the founder of Torrance in southwest Los Angeles County , California .
Marten Heemskerck van der Heck ( 1620 , Alkmaar -- 1660 , Alkmaar ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Richard Rushton ( 18 September 1902 -- 1981 ) , sometimes known as Dick Rushton , was an English footballer who made 62 appearances in the Football League playing for Lincoln City , Barnsley , Bury and Swindon Town .
Ludwig Dessoir , original name Leopold Dessauer ( 15 December 1810 -- 30 December 1874 ) was a German actor born in Posen , the son of a Jewish tradesman .
Vice Admiral Francis Hosier ( 1673 - -1727 ) was a British naval officer .
Ray Garby ( 16 January 1923 -- 14 March 2009 ) is a former Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Lieutenant Bolesław Kontrym ( Zatruka , Russian Empire , 27 August 1898 -- 20 January 1953 , Warsaw , Poland ) , also known by codenames Żmudzin , Biały , Bielski and Cichocki , was a Polish Army officer , a Home Army soldier , participant in the Warsaw Uprising and organizer of underground secret - police force Cichociemni .
Syahrir ( 24 February 1945 -- 28 July 2008 ) was a prominent Indonesian political economist .
Peter Jarman died on 23 July 2007 , aged 72 ( not 75 as some sources quote ) , and his funeral was on 6 August in Poole .
William Conyers , 1st Baron Conyers ( 21 December 1468 -- 14 April 1524 ) , also known as William Conyers of Hornby , was an English baron and aristocrat .
Des Hoysted ( 1923 -- 25 March 2010 ) was an Australian radio broadcaster and horse racing identity .
Zunduin Khangal ( Mongolian : Зундуйн Хангал ) ( 1948 - -1996 ) was a Mongolian classical composer of European music .
Ferid Džanić ( 1918 -- 17 September 1943 ) was a Bosniak soldier during World War II who was killed in southern France at age 25 during an anti - German rebellion .
Jan Prins ( 14 May 1944 in Zaandam -- 7 March 2008 in The Hague ) was a Dutch newspaper editor and journalist .
Æthelred the Unready , or Æthelred II , ( c. 968 - -23 April 1016 ) was King of the English ( 978 - -1013 and 1014 - -1016 ) .
William Keasberry ( 1726 -- 15 November 1797 ) , sometimes spelt Keasbury , was an English actor and theatre manager of the 18th century whose career was chiefly in Bath , Somerset .
Sir Alfred William Flux CB ( 8 April 1867 -- 16 July 1942 ) was a British economist and statistician .
Ameyo Adadevoh ( born Ameyo Stella Shade Adadevoh ; 27 October 1956 -- 19 August 2014 ) was a Nigerian physician .
Sir James Macklin , DL , JP ( 23 September 1864 -- 17 April 1944 ) was an English jeweller and farmer , active in public life in Wiltshire .
Baron Charles de Biencourt de Saint - Just ( 1591 or 1592 , Champagne , France -- 1623 or 1624 , Port - Royal of what was then Acadia , New France ) was a member of the French nobility and military officer .
Johann Friedrich Klöffler ( 20 April 1725 -- 21 February 1790 ) was a German conductor , composer , and administrator .
Jack Lipsham ( born 1881 , Chester ; died 1959 ) is a former English footballer .
Henry Foot ( 21 November 1805 -- 14 May 1857 ) was an English - born cricketer who played for Victoria .
Martin Grünberg ( * 1655 , Insterburg , then in East Prussia , now in Russia -- between 16 and 23 October 1706 or 1707 ) was a German architect and master builder .
Sir Philip St Clere ( died 16 May 1408 ) was a son of Sir Philip St Clere and Joan de Audley .
Leanna Field Driftmier ( 1886 - -1976 ) was an American radio personality and writer based in Shenandoah , Iowa .
Otto von Fürth ( 18 November 1867 -- 7 June 1938 ) was an Austrian physician , physiologist and biochemist .
Fernando da Guerra ( c. 1390 -- 26 September 1467 ) was a Portuguese ecclesiastic .
Abraham Aurelius ( 1575 -- 1632 ) was an English pastor of the French Protestant church in London .
John Bartlow Martin ( Hamilton , Ohio , 4 August 1915 - 3 January 1987 ) was an American diplomat , author of 15 books , Ambassador , and speechwriter and confidant to many American Democratic politicians including Adlai Stevenson , John F. Kennedy , Robert F. Kennedy , Lyndon B. Johnson , and Hubert Humphrey .
Thích Huyền Quang ( 19 September 1919 -- 5 July 2008 ) was a Vietnamese Buddhist monk , dissident and activist .
Rodrigo Gómez ( died 1146 ) was a Castilian nobleman and military leader under Alfonso VII . He governed large parts of Asturias and northern Castile , was involved in the politics with neighbouring Navarre , to whose royal family he was related by marriage , and took part in the Reconquista .
Diwakar Krushna Kelkar ( Devanagari : दिवाकर कृष्ण केळकर ) ( 1902 -- 1973 ) was a Marathi writer from Maharashtra , India .
Josephus Flavius Cook ( 1838 - -1901 ) , commonly known as Joseph Cook , was an American philosophical lecturer , a descendant of Pilgrims who started his ascent to fame by way of Monday noon prayer meetings in Tremont Temple in Boston that for more than twenty years were among the city 's greatest attractions .
Ezra Norton ( 8 April 1897 -- 4 January 1967 ) was an Australian newspaper baron and businessman .
John R. Sweney ( 1837 - -1899 ) was born in West Chester , Pennsylvania . , December 31 , 1837 .
Margaretha Sandra ( 1629 in Middelburg -- 1674 in Aardenburg , Zeeland ) , was a Dutch heroine , known for participation in the defence of Aardenburg during the siege of the French in 1672 .
Patrick Hepburn , 1st Earl of Bothwell ( died 18 October 1508 ) was Lord High Admiral of Scotland .
Dan Muller aka Daniel Cody Muller ( 1889 - -1976 ) , artist , illustrator and writer of the American West ;
Charles Sidney Leary ( November 2 , 1889 -- 1950 ) was an English - born lumberman and political figure in British Columbia .
Empress Dou Miao ( Chinese : 竇妙 ; died 172 ) , formally Empress Huansi ( literally , `` the diligent and deep - thinking empress '' ) , was an empress during Han Dynasty .
Giovanni Battista Tolomei , S.J. , ( 3 December 1653 -- 19 January 1726 ) was an Italian Jesuit priest , theologian and cardinal .
Frantz Oskar Mosfjeld ( 20 January 1896 -- 21 April 1977 ) was a Norwegian literary scholar known for his widely cited ( in the field ) opus magnum on Henrik Ibsen 's biography , Henrik Ibsen og Skien :
Lloyd Brevett OD ( 1 August 1931 -- 3 May 2012 ) was a Jamaican double bassist , songwriter , and a founding member of The Skatalites .
Johann Heinrich Tobler ( 1777 - -1838 ) was a singer and composer of Appenzell Ausserrhoden , active in the formative period of Switzerland as a federal state .
Berto Poosen ( 27 February 1944 -- 26 February 2012 ) was a Belgian volleyball player .
David Bellhouse ( 1764 - -1840 ) was an English builder who did much to shape Victorian era Manchester , both physically and socially .
Braccio da Montone ( 1 July 1368 -- 5 June 1424 ) , born Andrea Fortebracci , and also known as Braccio Fortebraccio , was an Italian condottiero .
Amnon Carmeli ( Hebrew : אמנון כרמלי‎ , born 22 August 1929 , died 4 December 1993 ) was a former Israeli footballer who played for Maccabi Petah Tikva , scoring the club 's winning goal in the 1952 State Cup final .
Campbell Drummond Riddell ( 9 January 1796 -- 1858 ) was an Australian Colonial public servant who served as Colonial Treasurer .
Humphrey Bowman ( 1879 - -1965 ) worked in the Education Departments in the British Protectorates in Egypt from 1903 to 1911 and Sudan from 1911 to 1913 .
Erwin Bälz ( 13 January 1849 -- 31 August 1913 ) was a German internist , anthropologist , personal physician to the Japanese Imperial Family and cofounder of modern western medicine in Japan .
Ben Zion Hyman ( 1891 - 1984 ) was a Canadian Jewish bookseller .
Dick Pointer ( before 1778 -- 1827 ) was an American frontier hero and an African slave .
Eduard Hempel ( born 6 June 1887 , Pirna died 12 November 1972 Gundelfingen ) was a German diplomat .
George Weston Wrigley ( 24 June 1847 -- 14 January 1907 ) was a Canadian journalist and social reformer .
John de St Paul ( c. 1295 -- 1362 ) , also known as John de Owston and John de Ouston , was Archbishop of Dublin 1349 - -62 and Lord Chancellor of Ireland 1350 - -56 .
Joseph Matthäus Aigner ( 18 January 1818 -- 19 February 1886 ) was an Austrian portrait painter , who studied under Friedrich von Amerling and Carl Rahl .
Michał Weinzieher ( born 1 June 1903 in Będzin , Russian Empire , Polish lands of the Russian Partition ; d. April 1944 in Kraków ) was a Polish art historian and art critic , museologist , and separately also a writer on constitutional law ( known for his studies of the thought of Leon Petrazycki ) .
Tony Biever ( 1908 -- 1990 ) was a Luxembourgish politician for the Christian Social People 's Party ( CSV ) and jurist .
William Fanshawe ( 1583 -- 4 March 1634 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1614 and 1625 .
Simon Peter Tilemann ( 1601 , Lemgo -- 1668 , Vienna ) , was a German Baroque painter who was active Bremen , Kassel and Italy .
Sir Edward Horsey ( 1525 -- 21 March 1583 ) was a conspirator against Queen Mary , then a soldier , ambassador and courtier under Queen Elizabeth .
Nicholas Greaves , D.D. ( 1605?--1673 ) was an English churchman who was Dean of Dromore cathedral , County Down .
Peter Smart ( 1569 - 1652 ? ) was an Anglican Puritan clergyman , kept imprisoned for 12 years after he preached against innovations in the ceremonies at Durham Cathedral .
William Holden Hutton ( 24 May 1860 -- 24 October 1930 ) was a British historian and a priest of the Church of England .
Antonio Fontanesi ( 23 February 1818 -- 17 April 1882 ) was an Italian painter who lived in Meiji period Japan between 1876 and 1878 .
Michelangelo Maestri was an Italian artist of the 18th century who died in Rome in 1812 .
Einar Fredrik Åke Tinius Nagell - Erichsen ( 15 February 1934 -- 12 November 2007 ) was a Norwegian publisher , noted for his leadership of the Schibsted media conglomerate which includes the broadsheet newspaper Aftenposten and the tabloid Verdens gang .
Duke William of Württemberg ( German : Herzog Wilhelm Nikolaus von Württemberg ; 20 July 1828 -- 5 November 1896 ) was an Austrian and Württemberg General .
Park Gil - ra ( Korean : 박길라 ; 1965 -- 1986 ) was a South Korean talent and singer .
Bill Drew ( 7 February 1890 -- 30 July 1955 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Sidney Edwards Morse ( 7 February 1794 Charlestown , Massachusetts - 24 December 1871 New York City ) was a U.S. inventor , geographer and journalist .
Georg Fritze ( 1 August 1874 -- 3 January 1939 ) was a German theologian , Protestant pastor , religious socialist and an anti - fascist .
William Ashburnham , 2nd Baron Ashburnham ( 21 May 1679 -- 16 June 1710 ) was an English landowner and politician .
Giovanni Ghiselli ( 15 November 1934 -- 26 February 1997 ) was an Italian sprinter who won three gold medals in one edition of Mediterranean Games .
Adeniran Ogunsanya , QC , SAN ( 31 January 1918 -- 22 November 1996 ) was a Nigerian lawyer and politician .
Růžena Vacková ( 23 April 1901 Velké Meziříčí -- 14 December 1982 Prague ) was a Czech art historian and theoritician , theatre critic and pedagogue .
Rani Mangammal ( 1689 - -1704 ) was a queen regent on behalf of her grandson , in the Madurai Nayak kingdom in present day Madurai , India , towards the end of the century .
John Swaine ( 26 June 1775 -- 25 November 1860 ) , was an English draughtsman and engraver .
Hugh Tyrrel ( Anglo - Norman : Huge Tyrel ; died 1199 ) was an Anglo - Norman noble and crusader ; he played a prominent part in the Norman invasion of Ireland , became the first baron of Castleknock and took part in the Third Crusade .
Francis Berry ( 23 March 1915 -- 10 October 2006 ) was a British academic , poet , critic and translator .
John Lemon ( 6 November 1754 -- 5 April 1814 ) was a British Whig Member of Parliament .
Hong Tianguifu ( simplified Chinese : 洪天贵福 ; traditional Chinese : 洪天貴福 ; pinyin : Hóng Tiānguìfú ) ( 23 November 1849 -- 18 November 1864 ) , also called Hong Tiangui and in Qing historical record , Hong Futian ( 洪福瑱 Hóng Fútiàn ) , was the second and last king of the Heavenly Kingdom of Taiping .
Banesh Hoffmann ( 6 September 1906 -- 5 August 1986 ) was a British mathematician and physicist known for his association with Albert Einstein .
Carel van Savoyen ( 1619 - -1665 ) , also known as Carlo da Savoia , was a Flemish painter of the Baroque period .
Alexander Francis Lydon ( /ˈlaɪdən/ ; 1836 - -1917 ) was an English watercolour artist , illustrator and engraver of natural history and landscapes .
Lionel Régal ( 21 July 1975 -- 15 August 2010 ) was a French hillclimbing racer .
Moshe Ben - Ze'ev ( Hebrew : משה בן זאב‎ ) ( 1911 -- 1995 ) was an Israeli jurist who served as Attorney General between 1963 and 1968 .
Henri Bacry ( 1928 - -2010 ) was Professor Emeritus at the Université de la Méditerranée .
Lieutenant Colonel Joseph Janvier Woodward ( 1833 - -1884 ) , commonly known as J. J. Woodward , served in the U.S. Civil War as Army Assistant Surgeon and produced several publications on war - related diseases .
Sir Hugh Myddelton ( or Middleton ) , 1st Baronet ( 1560 -- 10 December 1631 ) was a Welsh clothmaker , entrepreneur , mine - owner , goldsmith , banker and self - taught engineer .
Ella Mary Leather ( 1876 - -1928 ) was a collector of the local folklore and songs of Herefordshire .
Thomas Isaac Mardy Jones ( 21 January 1879 -- 26 August 1970 ) was a British politician and miner .
On the morning of 23 January 1929 Arthur Desmond suffered a stroke in his apartment at 1353 North Clark Street , just a few blocks north of the Newberry Library .
Hilary Shuard CBE ( 14 November 1928 -- 24 December 1992 ) was an internationally known expert on mathematics in primary schools .
William Campbell Steere ( 1907 - 1989 ) was an American botanist known as an expert on bryophytes ( mosses , liverworts , and hornworts ) , especially arctic and tropical American species .
Rev. John Keep ( 20 April 1781 -- 11 February 1870 ) was a trustee of Oberlin College from 1834 to 1870 .
Helmuth Koinigg ( 3 November 1948 -- 6 October 1974 ) was an Austrian racing driver who died in a crash in the 1974 United States Grand Prix , only his second Grand Prix start .
Flora Finch ( 17 June 1867 -- 4 January 1940 ) was an English - born film actress who starred in over 300 silent films , including over 200 for the Vitagraph Studios film company .
Christofer Rutger Ludvig Manderström ( 22 January 1806 - 18 August 1873 ) was the Swedish - Norwegian Prime Minister of Foreign Affairs between 1858 - 1868 .
Bartholomæus Deichman ( 9 August 1671 -- 13 April 1731 ) was a Danish / Norwegian clergyman and book collector .
Sir Herbert Croft , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1651 -- 3 November 1720 ) was the only son of the Right Reverend Herbert Croft , Bishop of Hereford and Anne Browne , the only daughter of the Very Rev. Dr. Jonathan Browne and Anne Barne Lovelace .
Franciscus Patricius ( Italian : Francesco Patrizi , Croatian : Franjo Petriš or Frane Petrić ; 25 April 1529 -- 6 February 1597 ) was a philosopher and scientist from the Republic of Venice of Croatian descent .
Lefevre James Cranstone ( March 6 , 1822 -- June 22 , 1893 ) was an accomplished English artist known for his watercolor genre - style landscapes and oil paintings .
Mehmet II of Karaman , Mehmed Beg ( Turkish : Mehmet Bey ) , Mehmed Beg II , also known as Nasir al - Din Mehmed Beg ( ? - 1423 ) was the ruler ( Turkish : bey ) of Karaman in what is now modern Turkey in the 15th century .
Frances Jennings Casement ( 1840 - -1928 ) was an American suffragette and voting advocate from Painesville , Ohio .
Charles Cooper Henderson ( 14 June 1803 -- 21 August 1877 ) was a British painter of horses and coaches .
Henry Furnese ( after 1688 -- 30 August 1756 ) was a British politician .
Akaitcho ( variants : Akaicho or Ekeicho ; translation : `` Big - Foot '' or `` Big - Feet '' ; meaning : `` like a wolf with big paws , he can travel long distances over snow '' ) ( ca . 1786 - 1838 ) was a Copper Indian , and Chief of the Yellowknives .
Mary Gordon Calder ( c. 1906 - -1992 ) was a Scottish paleobotanist .
Reg Milburn ( 25 March 1927 -- 3 July 2002 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Enos Bronson ( 1774 - -1823 ) was an American writer and newspaper publisher .
Zhang Zhenshi 张振仕 ( 1914 - -1992 ) was a famous effigy painter and fine art educator in China .
Khan Bahadur Sir Ghulam Muhammad Ali Khan GCIE ( 1882 - -1952 ) was the fifth Prince of Arcot and ruled from 1903 to 1952 .
Sir Antony Fisher ( Antony George Anson Fisher , also nicknamed AGAF ) ( 28 June 1915 -- 8 July 1988 ) was a British businessman and philanthropist .
Fred Pierce Corson ( 11 April 1896 - 16 February 1985 ) was an American bishop of The Methodist Church and the United Methodist Church , elected in 1944 .
Peter Hunter Blair ( 1912 - -September 1982 ) was an English academic and historian specializing in the Anglo - Saxon period .
Frith Banbury MBE ( 4 May 1912 -- 14 May 2008 ) was a British theatre actor and director .
John Michael Montias ( 3 October 1928 -- 26 July 2005 ) was an economist and art historian , well known for his contributions to the economic history of Dutch Golden Age painting .
Francis Constable ( 1592 -- 1 August 1647 ) was a London bookseller and publisher of the Jacobean and Caroline eras , noted for publishing a number of stage plays of English Renaissance drama .
Leopold II , Duke of Austria ( 1328 -- 10 August 1344 ) , a member of the House of Habsburg , was the younger son of Duke Otto the Merry .
Dr. Daniel Díaz Maynard ( 1934 ? -- 22 March 2007 ) was an Uruguayan lawyer and politician .
Hanns Georgi ( 21 September 1901 -- 23 October 1989 ) was a German painter , printmaker and book illustrator .
James Brolan ( 7 April 1964 -- 29 May 2006 ) was a British freelance journalist and television sound technician , who was killed while working for CBS News in Baghdad , Iraq .
Domnall mac Ailpín ( Modern Gaelic : Dòmhnall mac Ailpein , anglicised sometimes as Donald MacAlpin , known in most modern regnal lists as Donald I ) ; ( 812 -- 13 April 862 ) was King of the Picts from 858 to 862 .
Tekle Giyorgis II ( Ge'ez ተክለ ጊዮርጊስ , `` Plant of Saint George '' born Wagshum Gobeze ዋግሹም ጎበዜ lit . `` Governor of Wag , my courageous one '' ; died 1873 ) was nəgusä nägäst ( Emperor ) of Ethiopia from 1868 to 1871 .
Ilija Gregorić ( c. 1520 -- 1574 ) was a Croatian soldier , best known as the military commander of rebels during the Croatian and Slovenian peasant revolt of 1573 .
Mariano Noriel ( 1864 - January 27 , 1915 ) was a Filipino general who fought during the Philippine Revolution and the Philippine - American War .
Ulf Fase ( died 1247 ) was the jarl of Sweden c 1221 - 47 .
Sir Arthur Landsborough Thomson ( 8 October 1890 -- 9 June 1977 ) was a Scottish ornithologist .
Norman Stewart Mitchell - Innes , known as Mandy Mitchell - Innes ( 7 September 1914 -- 28 December 2006 ) was an amateur cricketer for Somerset , who played in one Test match for England , in 1935 .
Lewys Glyn Cothi ( c. 1420 -- 1490 ) , also known as Llywelyn y Glyn , was a prominent Welsh poet who composed numerous poems in the Welsh language .
Sipke van der Land ( 12 February 1937 -- 22 November 2015 ) was a Dutch preacher , writer , teacher and television presenter .
Francis Godolphin , 2nd Baron Godolphin ( 2 November 1706 -- 25 May 1785 ) was a British peer and politician .
Conal Holmes O'Connell O'Riordan ( pseudonym Norreys Connell ) ( 29 April 1874 - 18 June 1948 ) was an Irish dramatist and novelist .
James Kelly Cole ( 1885 - 1909 ) was a member of the Chicago Branch of the Industrial Workers of the World until his death in the fall of 1909 .
Moti Abba Rebu was king of the Gibe Kingdom of Jimma ( reigned 1855 - -1859 ) .
James DeRuyter Blackwell ( 18 March 1828 -- 5 September 1901 ) of Warrenton , Virginia is a celebrated author and poet of the American Civil War era .
Willie Paton ( 1 August 1925 -- 2005 ) was a Scottish footballer who played for Rangers and Ayr United .
Joseph Eric Stephenson ( 17 September 1914 -- 8 September 1944 ) was an English footballer who played as an inside left at both professional and international levels .
Juliette Bussière Laforest - Courtois ( Cap - Français , Saint - Domingue ( later Haiti ) 1789 -- 24 December 1853 ) , was a Haitian teacher and journalist .
Clelia Matania ( 18 September 1918 -- 13 October 1981 ) was a British - born Italian film and voice actress .
Dr. Thomas Neill Cream ( 27 May 1850 -- 15 November 1892 ) , also known as the Lambeth Poisoner , was a Scottish - Canadian serial killer , who claimed his first proven victims in the United States and the rest in England , and possibly others in Canada and Scotland .
George Younger , 1st Viscount Younger of Leckie Bt ( 13 October 1851 -- 29 April 1929 ) was a British politician .
Ge Fuyuan ( 格輔元 ) ( died November 7 , 691 ) was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty and Wu Zetian 's Zhou Dynasty , serving briefly as a chancellor during Wu Zetian 's reign .
Henry Charles Tonking ( b. Camborne , Cornwall , 17 Jan. 1863 ; d. Glasgow , 7 June 1926 ) was a British organist .
Edward Dwelly ( 1864 - -1939 ) was an English lexicographer and genealogist .
George Learmond ( or Learmonth ) ( c. 1478 - -1531 ) was a Scottish Benedictine who was Prior of Pluscarden and almost Bishop of Aberdeen .
Rev. Elwood Morris Wherry ( 1843 - -1927 ) was an American Presbyterian missionary to India where he spent forty years of his life ( between 1868 and 1923 ) .
John Wemyss ( c. 1579 - -1636 ) , also spelled Weemes or Weemse , was a Church of Scotland minister , Hebrew scholar and exegete .
John de Leche ( or John de Leck or John de Leek ) ( died 1313 ) was a canon of Dunkeld and prelate during the early 14th century .
Henry Alder ( 6 April 1874 -- 17 May 1949 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played one game with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Mauritz Gisiko ( born 1794 , d. 1863 ) was a Swedish pianist and music educator of good reputation .
Stekšys ( or Steksė ) ( other spellings include Stakys , Stejkint , Stekintas , Stegikintas , Stegutas ) was a duke of Lithuania , killed in 1214 near Lielvārde during an attack against Livonia .
James Canby ( 1781 - 1858 ) was a businessman and banker based in Wilmington , Delaware , and an early American railroad executive .
Albert Hayhurst ( 17 September 1905 -- 8 November 1991 ) was an English cricketer and footballer .
S. E. Aimé - Joseph de Fleuriau ( 1870 - 1938 ) was a French diplomat , who served as Ambassador to London from 1924 until 1933 .
Murray Morrison ( 1820 - -1871 ) was a California State Assembly member , president of the Los Angeles Common Council and a judge of the Superior Court .
Eochaid mac Domangairt ( died ca . 697 ) was a king of Dál Riata ( modern western Scotland ) in about 697 .
Sultan bin Saqr Al Qasimi ( 18th century -- 1866 ) was the ruler ( 1803 - -1840 , 1840 - -1866 ) of the emirates of Sharjah and Ras Al Khaimah on the Trucial Coast ( currently known as the United Arab Emirates ) .
Marian Porwit ( 1895 - 1988 ) was a Polish military officer , a Colonel of the Polish Army and a military historian .
William Balmain ( 2 February 1762 -- 17 November 1803 ) was a Scottish - born naval surgeon and civil administrater who sailed as an assistant surgeon with the First Fleet to establish the first European settlement in Australia , and later to take up the appointment of the principal surgeon , for New South Wales .
Đỗ Thanh Nhơn ( died 1781 ) was an 18th - century Vietnamese military commander .
Duke Gong of Cao ( ? -- 618 BCE ) ( Chinese : 曹共公 ; pinyin : Cáo Gòng Gōng ) was the seventeenth ruler of the vassal State of Cao during the Chinese Spring and Autumn Period ( 770 -- 475 BCE ) .
Theulf ( died 20 October 1123 ) was a medieval Bishop of Worcester .
Elisha Leavitt ( 1714 - -1790 ) was a Hingham , Massachusetts , Loyalist landowner who owned several islands in Boston Harbor .
Ieuan Ddu ab Dafydd ab Owain ( fl . 1440 - -1480 ) , was a Welsh poet , also known as Ieuan Dafydd Ddu and Ieuan Dafydd ab Owain .
Francis David Charteris , 12th Earl of Wemyss and 8th Earl of March , KT , DL ( 19 January 1912 -- 12 December 2008 ) succeeded his grandfather in the family titles in 1937 .
Peston Padamji Ginwala ( 9 February 1919 -- 2 July 2008 ) also known as Pesi Ginwala was a noted senior barrister from India , working at Calcutta High Court .
Tripuraribhatla Ramakrishna Sastry or T. Ramakrishna Sastry ( Telugu : త్రిపురారిభట్ల రామకృష్ణ శాస్త్రి ) ( 10 April 1914 -- 21 May 1998 ) was a famous stage and film actor in the early period of Telugu cinema .
Rodney Diak ( 15 June 1924 -- 6 October 2007 ) was a British film , television , and theater actor .
Franco Bracardi ( 16 May 1937 - 27 February 2005 ) was an Italian actor , composer , pianist and stand - up comedian .
Don Lafferty ( 1933 - -1998 ) was a Grandmaster checkers ( British English : draughts ) player .
Cahalan Ó Corcrán , Irish Abbot , died 1001 .
Joseph Milton Bernstein ( September 30 , 1908 -- July 1975 ) was an American accused of spying for the Soviet Union and later confirmed as a Soviet agent by the US intelligence program Venona .
Stass Paraskos ( Greek : Στας Παράσκος ; 17 March 1933 -- 4 March 2014 ) was an artist from Cyprus , although much of his life was spent teaching and working in England .
Charles Vyse ( 1882 Staffordshire - 1971 Deal , Kent ) , was an English studio potter , noted for producing colourful figurines of characters seen on London streets .
Hilal Al - Ahmadi ( 1954 ? -- 17 February 2011 ) , who was an Iraqi veteran journalist with over 30 years of experience and well known for his reports about corruption , was assassinated in front of his home east of Mosul , Iraq .
Zhou Jiannan ( Chinese : 周建南 ; pinyin : Zhōu Jiànnán ; 1917−1995 ) was a Chinese politician .
Krushnashastri Chiplunkar ( Devanagari : कृष्णशास्त्री चिपळूणकर ) ( 1824 - -1878 ) was a social activist and a Marathi writer from Maharashtra , India .
Seamus Grew ( 20 July 1951 -- 12 December 1982 ) was a volunteer in the Irish National Liberation Army ( INLA ) who , along with Roddy Carroll , was killed in controversial circumstances by police officers from the Special Support Unit of the Royal Ulster Constabulary .
Thomas Philip Perkins ( 3 September 1904 -- 26 December 1978 ) was an English professional golfer best known for winning the 1928 Amateur Championship ( British Amateur ) .
Robert Guy Howarth ( 1906 - -1974 ) was an Australian scholar , literary critic and poet .
David Marine ( 20 September 1888 -- 6 November 1976 ) was an American pathologist .
Stephen Reville D.D. , O.S.A. ( 9 May 1844 - 18 September 1916 ) was a Bishop of Sandhurst , Victoria ( Australia ) .
Reginald Corbet ( by 1513 - -1566 ) was a distinguished lawyer in four reigns across the mid - Tudor period , and prospered throughout , although he seems to have been definitely Protestant in sympathy .
Chuop Hell ( 1909 -- ca . 1975 ) was a Cambodian statesman .
Livingstone Walker ( 14 June 1879 - 10 October 1940 ) was an English amateur cricketer .
Mary Ní Mháille ( died 1525 ) Gaelic - Irish Lady .
Arthur Tutin ( 1907 -- 1961 ) was an English footballer who played in the Football League for Aldershot and Stoke City .
Carl Herman Theodor Alfred Lagerheim , ( 4 October 1843 -- 23 May 1924 ) was a Swedish politician and diplomat .
Jonathan Carr ( 1942 - -2008 ) was a British journalist and author , who lived and worked primarily in Germany .
Abdul Kadir Shaikh ( 1926 - -2008 ) was a Pakistani politician who was the 13th governor of Sindh from 6 July 1977 to 17 September 1978 .
Tomasz Chołodecki ( 21 December 1813 -- 17 July 1880 ) was a political activist and Polish rebel and soldier , who took part in almost every major event that supported Poland 's independence in the 19th century .
Hermas Deslauriers ( 21 October 1879 -- 28 May 1941 ) was a member of the Canadian House of Commons , initially as one of the Laurier Liberals then as a Liberal member .
Gardner Colby ( 1810 - -1879 ) was a prominent businessman and Christian philanthropist .
Edward Thurlow , 1st Baron Thurlow PC , KC ( 9 December 1731 -- 12 September 1806 ) was a British lawyer and Tory politician .
Giles de Badlesmere , 2nd Baron Badlesmere ( 18 October 1314 -- 7 June 1338 ) was an English nobleman .
Fáilbe mac Pípáin was the eighth abbot of Iona ( fl . 669 - 679 ? ) .
Serafin Olarte ( died 1821 ) was a Totonac chief and general who led a revolt against Spanish rule during the Mexican War of Independence in ( then province ) Veracruz .
Arend Dickmann ( 1572 - -1627 ) , more correctly Dijckman , was briefly Admiral of the Polish Navy .
Antonis Migiakis ( Greek : Aντώνης Mηγιάκης ; born 23 October 1911 - 19 November 1999 ) was a star forward for Greek football team Panathinaikos in the 1930s .
Sterling Houston ( 1945 - -2006 ) was an African - American experimental playwright , actor , musician and prose writer renowned for his works of social commentary exploring black and gay identity .
The Blessed Giorgio di Biandrate , or Giorgio da Orazio di Biandrate ( died 1483 ) was a member of the family of the counts of San Giorgio Canavese in north - west Italy .
Margaret Gill ( 1797 - 1864 ) was born in Yorkshire , England , and was the first wife of American black actor Ira Frederick Aldridge .
Pierre Gauvreau ( 23 August 1922 -- 7 April 2011 ) was a Québécois painter who has also worked in film and television productions .
Eugène Train ( 1832 - -1903 ) was a French architect who taught for many years at the École des Arts Décoratifs .
Amalberga of Temse ( born about 741 , died 10 July 772 ) was a Lotharingian noblewoman from the Frankish royal house of the Pippinids who is celebrated as a saint in the Roman Catholic Church and the Eastern Orthodox Church .
Robert Vernon , 1st Baron Lyveden GCB PC ( 23 February 1800 -- 10 November 1873 ) , known as Robert Vernon Smith until 1859 , was a British Liberal Party politician .
Fritz Kortner ( 12 May 1892 -- 22 July 1970 ) was an Austrian stage and film actor and theatre director .
Samuel Stone ( July 18 , 1602 -- 20 July 1663 ) was a Puritan Minister .
Lain Singh Bangdel / Lain Bangdel ( Rai ) ( Nepali : लैनसिंह बाङ्देल ) ( 1919 - -2002 ) , was Nepal 's foremost artist , novelist , and art historian .
Anne Garber ( 1947 -- 17 July 2011 ) was a Canadian journalist , restaurant critic , food and travel writer .
Bagyi Aung Soe ( Burmese : ဗဂျီ အောင်စိုး ( bədʑì ʔàʊɴ só ) ; 1924 - -1990 ) was a Burmese painter renowned for his modernistic , semi - abstract art , which caused such a shock in Burma when it appeared that many called it `` psychopathic art '' .
Reginald Wilkie ( died 6 August 1962 ) was a British ice dancer .
Charles Wilson Greene ( 1866 - -1947 ) was an American professor of physiology and pharmacology from Indiana .
Theron R. Perlee or Per Lee , ( 1824 - -1894 ) , lawyer , soldier , 49er , politician and judge in the territory and early state of California .
Tewfik Mishlawi ( 1935 -- 24 January 2012 ) was a veteran Lebanese journalist who was well known in the Middle East and Arab world .
Jonathan Remington ( 1677 -- 1745 ) , was an Associate Justice of Massachusetts Supreme Judicial Court appointed by Gov. Jonathan Belcher .
Edward Tooker ( c. 1592 -- 17 April 1664 ) was an English lawyer , landowner and politician who sat in the House of Commons at various times between 1654 and 1664 .
Per Fuglum ( 7 January 1924 -- 13 June 2008 ) was a Norwegian historian , born in Oslo .
Rawshan Jamil ( 8 May 1931 -- 14 May 2002 ) was a Bangladeshi actress and dancer .
Kanailal Shil ( 5 September1895 -- 1974 ) was a Bangladeshi dotara player , song writer , composer , and collector of folk songs .
Odd Nansen ( 6 December 1901 -- 27 June 1973 ) was a Norwegian architect , author , and humanitarian , credited with his humanitarian efforts on behalf of Jews in the early years of World War II and for being a founder of UNICEF .
George Best ( 22 May 1946 -- 25 November 2005 ) was a Northern Irish professional footballer who played as a winger for Manchester United and the Northern Ireland national team .
Berthe Bovy ( 6 January 1887 -- 26 February 1977 ) , sometimes known as Betty Bovy , was a Belgian actress who appeared in theatre , films and television programmes for over 60 years .
Henry Van Asselt ( 11 April 1817 , Elspeet - 7 December 1902 , Seattle ) was a Dutch immigrant to the US , one of the first to settle the area that is now Seattle , Washington .
Viking Dahl , ( 8 October 1895 - 5 January 1945 ) , was a Swedish composer , active also as a painter and an author .
Henry III , Lord of Waldeck ( c. 1225/1230 -- 1267 ) was a German nobleman .
Ereyanga ( r.1098 - -1102 CE ) was the son of Hoysala Vinayaditya and distinguished himself as a Chalukya feudatory during their campaigns against Dhara of Malwa .
Chief Billy Bowlegs or Billy Bolek ( Holata Micco , Halpatter - Micco , Halbutta Micco , and Halpuda Mikko in Seminole , meaning `` Alligator Chief '' ) ( ca . 1810 - -1859 ) was a leader of the Seminoles in Florida during the Second and Third Seminole Wars against the United States .
Scott Pembroke ( 13 September 1889 -- 21 February 1951 ) was an American director , actor and screenwriter .
Kevin Coen ( 1947 -- 20 January 1975 ) , was a volunteer in the Sligo Brigade of the Provisional Irish Republican Army ( IRA ) who was killed in Northern Ireland by the British Army .
Johan Zoffany , Zoffani or Zauffelij RA ( 13 March 1733 -- 11 November 1810 ) was a German neoclassical painter , active mainly in England .
Thomas Galloway FRS ( 26 February 1796 -- 1 November 1851 ) was a Scottish mathematician born in Symington , South Lanarkshire , Scotland .
Stephen Weston ( 1665 - -1742 ) was an English bishop and educator .
Pedro de Ezcurra ( 1859 - -1911 ) was an Argentine politician who served as Minister of Agriculture in the early 20th century .
Bob Flegg ( 19 August 1918 -- 7 July 1944 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with St Kilda in the Victorian Football League .
Hans Eng ( 1907 - -1995 ) was a Norwegian physician and Nazi collaborator during World War II .
Knut Wulff , born 1913 in Malmö , died 2002 , was a Swedish entrepreneur and pioneer in the beauty and cosmetics area , who created many successful products and brands within his company Pierre Robert .
Ragnvald Skrede ( 24 April 1904 -- 16 August 1983 ) was a Norwegian author , journalist , literature critic and translator .
Maurie Beasy ( 14 March 1896 -- 28 April 1979 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Romolo Panfi ( Florence , 1632 - Carmignano , 1690 ) was an Italian painter , active in Tuscany .
Sir ( William ) Ian Clunies Ross ( 22 February 1899 -- 20 June 1959 ) was an Australian veterinary scientist .
George French Flowers ( 1811 -- 14 June 1872 ) was an English composer and musical theorist .
Johan Gustaf Åkerman ( 1888 - -1959 ) was a Swedish economist who was Professor of Political Economy in what was to later become the University of Gothenburg . He was the elder brother to swedish economist Johan Henrik Åkerman .
Uc de Lescura or de l'Escura ( fl . 1190 - -1204 ) was a minor troubadour .
Robert Moore Williams ( 1907 - -1977 ) was an American writer , primarily of science fiction .
Fu Hong ( Chinese : 苻洪 , 284 - -350 ) originally named Pu Hong ( Chinese : 蒲洪 ) , courtesy name Guangshi(Chinese : 廣世 ) , was the father of first emperor of Former Qin , Fu Jiàn .
Fanny Parnell born Frances Isabelle Parnell ( 4 September 1848 -- 20 July 1882 ) was an Irish poet , Irish Nationalist , and the sister of Charles Stewart Parnell , an important figure in nineteenth century Ireland .
Rey Charol ( 1936 - -1990 ) was an Argentine film and television actor of African descent .
Filippo Salviati ( 1582 -- 22 March 1614 ) was an Italian scientist and astronomer from a noble Florentine family .
Edwin Atherstone ( 1788 - -1872 ) was a poet and novelist .
John Shillingford ( died 1458 ) , of Exeter and Shillingford , Devon , was an English politician .
Öljei Temür Khan , Bunyashir Khan ( full name : Bunyashiri , died 1412 ) was the Mongol khan of the Northern Yuan dynasty based in Mongolia .
James Napper Tandy ( about 1739 -- 24 August 1803 ) was an Irish revolutionary , and member of the United Irishmen .
Zafer Önen , ( 1 January 1921 Çorum -- 13 December 2013 Istanbul ) was a Turkish film actor .
Daifallah Masadeh ( 1938 -- 18 December 2015 ) was a Jordanian lawyer and politician .
Ognjeslav Utješenović Ostrožinski ( spelled Utješinović in some sources ; Serbian Cyrillic : Огњеслав Утјешеновић Острожински ; 21 August 1817 -- 8 June 1890 ) was a Croatian Serb politician and writer .
Kristian Hellström ( 24 July 1880 -- 14 June 1946 ) was a Swedish middle - distance runner and a sports administrator .
Andrea Bellunello , also known as Andrea di San Vito ( 1440 -- 1506 ) was an Italian painter active in the early Renaissance period .
Agostino Veneziano ( `` Venetian Agostino '' ) , whose real name was Agostino de ' Musi ( c. 1490 -- c. 1540 ) , was an important and prolific Italian engraver of the Renaissance .
Emma Maria Macfarren ( née Emma Marie Bennett ) ( 19 June 1824 -- 9 November 1895 ) was an English pianist and composer who used the pseudonym Jules Brissac .
Hans - Erich Voss ( or Voß , see ß ) ( 30 October 1897 -- 18 November 1969 ) was a German Vizeadmiral ( vice admiral ) and one of the final occupants of the Führerbunker during the battle of Berlin in 1945 .
Bruce Turner ( 5 July 1922 -- 28 November 1993 ) was an English saxophonist , clarinetist , and bandleader .
Al - Muzaffar Mahmud was the Ayyubid emir of Hama first in 1219 ( 616 ) and then restored in 1229 - 1244 ( 626 - 642 ) .
Saint Gordianus ( died 362 ) was a Roman martyr who was killed during the reign of Julian the Apostate , and is commemorated on 10 May.
Sheila Brown Napaljarri ( c. 1940 - -2003 ) was a Warlpiri speaking Indigenous artist from Australia 's Western Desert region .
Charlie Hurst ( 25 January 1919 -- 23 January 1999 ) was an English footballer who played as a centre - half for various clubs including Bristol Rovers , Oldham Athletic and Rochdale .
Domnall Mór Ua Briain , or Domnall Mór mac Toirrdelbaig Uí Briain , was King of Thomond in Ireland from 1168 to 1194 and a claimant to the title King of Munster .
Edward Brotherton ( 1814 - -1866 ) was an English Swedenborgian and a campaigner for educational reform .
Eugen Jochum ( German : ( ˈɔʏ̯ɡeːn ˈjɔxʊm ) ; 1 November 1902 -- 26 March 1987 ) was an eminent German conductor .
Boudewijn Catz or Cats ( ca . 1601 - 18 May 1663 ) was apostolic vicar to the Dutch Mission from 1662 to 1663 .
Sylvester Wackerle ( sometimes shown as Silvester Wackerlie , Sr . ) ( 1 January 1908 -- 3 March 1978 ) was a West German bobsledder who competed in the mid-1950s .
John Dignan , Bishop of Clonfert , 13 June 1880 - 15 April 1953 .
Maurice R. Bebb ( 1891 - -1986 ) ( or M. R. Bebb as he signed his work ) was a notable etcher and printmaker of the American Midwest , whose best - known subjects were birds native to Oklahoma and Minnesota , where he spent his time .
Ephraim Porter Felt ( 7 January 1868 Salem - 14 December 1943 ) was an American entomologist who specialised in Diptera Ephraim Felt worked mostly Nematocera and particularly Cecidomyiidae . However he was the State Entomologist New York State and so worked with all insects of economic or medical significance .
Professor Sir George Grenfell - Baines OBE DL ( 30 April 1908 -- 9 May 2003 ) was an English architect and town planner .
Karl Ludwig Nitzsch ( 6 August 1751 , Wittenberg -- 5 December 1831 , Wittenberg ) was a German theologian , a professor of theology since 1790 .
Guido de Summa ( died 1151 ) was an Italian Cardinal .
Dr. Preston Bradley ( 1888 - -June 1 , 1983 ) was an American clergyman , author , and lecturer .
Henry Wirtz Thomas ( October 20 , 1812 -- June 22 , 1890 ) , a Republican politician , served as the 12th Lieutenant Governor of Virginia from 1875 to 1878 under Governor James L. Kemper .
Hobart Baumann Amstutz ( 18 September 1896 -- 26 February 1980 ) was a bishop of the American Methodist Church and the United Methodist Church , elected in 1956 .
Shaykh Shams ud - Dīn Muhammad Amir Kulal ( d.772/1370 ) was born at Sokhar near Bukhara .
Games Slayter ( 9 December 1896 -- 15 October 1964 ) was a prolific U.S. engineer and inventor .
Jacob Bryant ( 1715 - -1804 ) was a British scholar and mythographer , who has been described as `` the outstanding figure among the mythagogues who flourished in the late eighteenth and early nineteenth centuries '' .
Sir Thomas Lake ( 1561 -- 17 September 1630 ) was Secretary of State to James I of England .
Edward Daniel Clarke ( 5 June 1769 -- 9 March 1822 ) was an English clergyman , naturalist , mineralogist , and traveller .
Sir George Chetwynd , 4th Baronet of Brocton Hall ( 31 May 1849 -- 10 March 1917 ) was the heir to the Chetwynd baronetcy upon the death of his father in 1869 .
Augustinus Bludau ( 6 March 1862 -- 9 February 1930 ) was a Bishop of Ermland ( Polish : Warmia ) in East Prussia from 1909 - -1930 .
Domingo Crespo ( 1791 - -1871 ) was an Argentine politician who was governor of the province of Santa Fe from 1851 to 1854 .
Carlo Orsi ( Pavia -- London , 1894 ) was an Italian painter and sculptor .
George Thomas Moore Marriott ( 14 September 1885 -- 11 December 1949 ) was an English character actor most notable for a series of films he made with Will Hay .
Henry Neville , 5th Earl of Westmorland ( 1525 - -Aug 1564 ) was an English peer , member of the House of Lords and Knight of the Garter .
