Arthur Sandes ( 1793 in Dublin or Kerry -- 6 September 1832 in Cuenca , Ecuador ) was the commanding officer of the Rifle Battalion of the British Legions in the Spanish American wars of independence .
Vladimir Winkler ( Russian : Влади́мир Фра́нцевич Ви́нклер ; IPA : ( vlɐˈdʲimʲɪr ˈvʲinklʲɪr ) ; 1884 - -1956 ) was a Czech sculptor best known for early 20th century buildings ' facades in Russian Siberia .
David Seth - Smith FZS , MBOU ( 1875 - -1963 ) was a British zoologist , wildlife artist , broadcaster and author .
Richard Jenkyns ( 1782 -- 16 March 1854 ) was a British academic administrator at the University of Oxford and Dean at Wells Cathedral .
Sir Edward Duke , 1st Baronet ( c. 1604 -- 1671 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons of England in 1640 .
William Keith , 7th Earl Marischal ( 1610 - 1670 or 1671 ) was a Scottish nobleman and Covenanter .
Alberto Randegger ( 13 April 1832 -- 18 December 1911 ) was an Italian - born composer , conductor and singing teacher , best known for promoting opera and new works of British music in England during the Victorian era and for his widely used textbook on singing technique .
Wilhelm Breckvelt , or Breekvelt ( 1658 -- 1687 , Düsseldorf ) , was a Dutch Golden Age painter .
Fortunato Arriola ( 1827 - -1872 ) , born in Cosalá , Sinaloa , Mexico , was a painter of portraits and luminous tropical landscapes that were very popular in San Francisco , California , where he came to live in 1857 .
Norman Kenneth Jernigan ( November 13 , 1926 -- October 12 , 1998 ) was the longtime leader of the National Federation of the Blind , the principal blind people 's organization in the United States .
William Paget , 1st Baron Paget of Beaudesert KG PC ( 1506 -- 9 June 1563 ) , was an English statesman and accountant who held prominent positions in the service of Henry VIII , Edward VI and Mary I.
Chang Kee - ryo ( 14 August 1911 -- 25 December 1995 ) was a prominent surgeon , educator , and philanthropist of South Korea .
Missak Manouchian ( classical Armenian : Միսաք Մանուշեան ; pronounced ( misɑkʰ manuʃjɑn ) , 1 September 1906 -- 21 February 1944 ) was a French - Armenian poet and communist activist .
Rose de Burford ( sometimes Roesia and sometimes de Boreford ) ( date of birth unknown - died 1329 , England ) was a 14th - century merchant and business woman in the City of London , England .
Clayton Milborne ( born after 1676 -- 1726 ) , of Bloomsbury Square ;
James Hartley Beal ( September 23 , 1861 -- 1945 ) was an educator , legislator , author , and pharmacist in the U.S. State of Ohio who was the first recipient of the Remington Medal for distinguished service to American pharmacy .
Richard Knill ( 14 April 1787 -- 2 January 1857 ) was an English missionary .
Jean Michel Claude Richard ( August 16 , 1787 - 1868 ) was a noted French botanist and plant collector active in Senegal , Madagascar , Mauritius , and Réunion , and a Chevalier of the Légion d'honneur .
James Eadie ( 1827 - -1904 ) was a Scottish brewer who founded an eponymous brewery in Burton on Trent which operated for 90 years .
Joan Jackson , née Joan Hunter Dunn ( 13 October 1915 -- 11 April 2008 ) was the muse of Sir John Betjeman in his poem `` A Subaltern 's Love - song '' .
Erik Mesterton ( 4 October 1903 -- 10 January 2004 ) was a Swedish author , literature critic and translator .
Rogelio Polesello ( 26 July 1939 -- 6 July 2014 ) was an Argentine painter , muralist and sculptor .
Matthew Hay ( 1855 - -1932 ) was a Scottish doctor and champion of Public Health .
Arthur Sullivant Hoffman ( 1876 - -1966 ) was an American magazine editor .
Andrew Cassidy ( c. 1817 -- November 25 , 1907 ) was an early settler of San Diego , California
Charles Keith Linney ( 26 August 1912 -- 12 October 1992 ) played first - class cricket for Somerset from 1931 to 1937 .
Domnell Crone Ó Flaithbheartaigh ( died 1560 ) was a Lord of Iar Connacht , Ireland , and Chief of the Name .
Mary Barr Clay ( 1839 - -1924 ) was a leader of the American women 's suffrage movement .
Major - General David Limond C.B. ( 5 April 1831 - 10 July 1895 ) was a British soldier of the Royal Engineers ( Bengal ) and a member of a family with a strong tradition of military service .
Luciano García Alén ( 25 May 1928 -- 16 October 2015 ) was a Spanish physician and ethnographer , known for his studies of Galician culture .
Rosemary Edmonds ( 20 October 1905 -- 26 July 1998 ) , born Rosemary Lilian Dickie , was a British translator of Russian literature whose editions of Leo Tolstoy have been in print for 50 years .
Sir William Arbuthnot , 1st Baronet of Edinburgh FRSE ( 24 December 1766 -- 18 September 1829 ) was Lord Provost of Edinburgh and Lord Lieutenant of the City of Edinburgh .
Guecellone II da Camino ( born Guecellone da Montanara ; died 1187 ) was an Italian medieval noble and military leader , belonging to the Da Camino family .
On 19 June 1924 , he transferred from Class A of the reserves to Class C. Nothing more is known of John Stevenson Stubbs after that .
Carlos Albán Holguín ( died 11 March 1995 ) was a Colombian lawyer and politician who served as the 19th Permanent Representative of Colombia to the United Nations .
Charles Ambrose Zavitz ( 1863 - -1942 , born Coldstream , Ontario ) was born in 1863 into a family that was a combination of both Quakers and United Empire Loyalists .
Thomas Calston ( c.1361 - 1418 ) , of Littlecote , Wiltshire , was an English politician .
George Henry Lesch ( 1909 -- 1994 ) was the president and CEO of the Colgate - Palmolive company from 1960 to 1971 , and was also the chairman of the board of the company from 1961 to 1974 .
Edgar Charles Barnes ( 6 April 1909 -- 27 December 1987 ) was a pioneer in the field of industrial hygiene and the first industrial hygienist to work for a major U.S. corporation .
Thomas Beagley ( born 5 October 1789 at Farringdon , Alton , Hampshire ; died 21 February 1858 at Paddington , London ) was an English professional cricketer .
George Robert Elsmie ( 1838 - -1909 ) was a Scottish civil servant and judge in India , known also as an author .
Diana Wellesley , Duchess of Wellington MBE ( 14 January 1922 -- 1 November 2010 ) , was the wife of Valerian Wellesley , 8th Duke of Wellington , and a British intelligence officer during World War II .
Jane Gordon , Duchess of Gordon ( 1748 or 1749 -- 14 April 1812 ) , née Lady Jane Maxwell , was a Scottish Tory political hostess .
William Dingwall Fordyce ( 31 March 1836 -- 27 November 1875 ) was a Scottish Liberal politician .
Selim I Giray , Selim Khan Girai ( Crimean Tatar : I Selim Geray , Turkish : 1 . Selim Giray ) was a Crimean khan ( 1631 - -1704 ) .
George Tollet ( died 1719 ) was a mathematician and naval administrator .
Peter Spendelowe Lamborn ( 1722 -- 5 November 1774 ) was an English engraver and miniature painter .
Gyula Vályi ( 5 January 1855 , Marosvásárhely / Târgu Mureş -- 13 October 1913 , Kolozsvár / Cluj ) was a Hungarian mathematician and theoretical physicist , a member of the Hungarian Academy of Sciences , known for his work on mathematical analysis , geometry , and number theory .
George Guthrie Moir MA ( 30 October 1917 - 29 November 1993 ) , was a British television producer , Liberal Party politician , prominent Christian and writer who was one of the founders of Independent Television .
Michele Carlo Frari ( also mentioned as Mihovil Frari in Croatian sources ) ( 1813 , Split -- 1896 , Padua ? ) was a renowned professor of obstetrics in Padua from 1843 until 1889 .
Leik Munhtaw ( Burmese : လိပ်မွတ်ထော , pronounced : ( leiʔ mʊ̀ɴ tʰɔ́ ) ; Mon : မမောဟ်ထာဝ် ; c. 1432 - -1454 ) was the 14th king of the Hanthawaddy Pegu Kingdom in Burma for seven months in 1453 - -54 .
Bernardus IJzerdraat ( 1891 - -1941 ) was a Dutch resistance fighter in the Second World War .
Mary Hannah Fulton ( 31 May 1854-May 1927 ) was a medical missionary sent to South China by the Presbyterian Church .
Hu Songshan ( 1880 - -1955 ) , a Hui , was born in 1880 , in Tongxin County , Ningxia , China .
Joseph - Alexis Stoltz ( 14 December 1803 in Andlau -- 20 May 1896 ) was a French obstetrician .
Vicente Nebrada ( born Vicente Balbino Nebreda Arias , 31 March 1930 - 26 May 2002 ) was a Venezuelan dancer and choreographer .
Ludvig Stoud Platou ( 28 March 1778 -- 30 November 1833 ) was a Danish - Norwegian educator , historical and geographical writer , politician and State Secretary .
Lockhart Muirhead ( 1765 -- 1829 ) was a Scottish librarian , museum - keeper and academic .
Daniel Topolski ( 4 June 1945 -- 21 February 2015 ) was a British author , rower , rowing coach and commentator on BBC television .
Mohamed Mjid ( Arabic : محمد امجيد‎ ; 1917 - -20 March 2014 ) was a Moroccan politician and president of the Royal Moroccan Tennis Federation .
Tom Arklay ( 26 March 1914 -- 11 January 2002 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played for Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John Baptist Caryll ( 13 December 1713 -- 7 March 1788 ) was the third Jacobite Baron Caryll of Durford .
Rabbi Dovid Povarsky ( 1902 - -1999 ) is known for his erudite Talmudic lectures and his deanship as Rosh Yeshiva of Ponevezh Yeshiva .
Balthasar Báthory de Somlyó ( Hungarian : Báthory Boldizsár ; 1560 -- 11 September 1594 ) was a Transylvanian politician from the Báthory family , like his brother , prince Andrew Báthory , opponent of the Habsburgs in Transylvania .
Anna Lee , MBE ( born Joan Boniface Winnifrith , 2 January 1913 -- 14 May 2004 ) was a British - American actress .
Marcus Pløen Ingstad ( 18 August 1837 -- 24 September 1918 ) was a Norwegian scholar of Roman law and Professor of Jurisprudence at the Faculty of Law of the Royal Frederick University 1870 - -1918 .
James L. Clark ( 18 November 1883 in Providence , Rhode Island -- 1969 ) , was a distinguished explorer , sculptor and scientist .
Sherwin Burickson ( 1934 - -2004 ) psychologist , writer , and student of the ideas of G. I. Gurdjieff , was the first Jewish editor of the New Catholic Encyclopedia , and the author of A Concise Dictionary of Contemporary History , published in 1959 .
John Taihuttu ( 18 November 1954 -- 17 January 2016 ) was a Dutch professional football player of Moluccan - Indonesian origin .
Isidoro Arredondo ( 1655 - 1702 ) , an eminent Spanish painter , was born at Colmenar de Oreja , in 1653 .
Sir John Orde , 1st Baronet ( 22 December 1751 -- 19 February 1824 ) was the third son of John Orde , of Morpeth , Northumberland , and the brother of Thomas Orde - Powlett , 1st Baron Bolton .
Adolfo Celi ( Italian pronunciation : ( aˈdɔlfo ˈtʃɛːli ; aˈdolfo ) ; 27 July 1922 --19 February 1986 ) was an Italian film actor and director .
Friedrich Richard Petri ( 1824 - -1857 ) was a German - born Texas painter whose works recorded life in the original German immigrant settlements , and portrayed Native American tribes in family settings .
Friedrich Georg Hendel ( 14 December 1874- 26 June 1936 ) was an Austrian Hauptsschuldirektor ( high school director ) and entomologist mainly interested in Diptera .
John St Barbe ( 1742 - 1816 ) was a prominent English shipbroker and shipowner active in whaling , the transport of convicts and the slave trade .
François Mathieu ( 1962 - 2007 ) was a French neo - impressionist painter .
Henry Harland ( 1 March 1861 -- 20 December 1905 ) was an American novelist and editor .
Hugo Bettauer ( 18 August 1872 -- 26 March 1925 ) , born Maximilian Hugo Bettauer , was a prolific Austrian writer and journalist , who was murdered by a Nazi Party follower on account of his controversial views .
Philipp Hieronymus Brinckmann or Brinkman ( 1709 -- 21 December 1760 ) was a German painter and engraver
Hugh the Great ( 898 -- 16 June 956 ) was the Duke of the Franks and Count of Paris .
Elijah Mizrachi ( Hebrew : אליהו מזרחי ) ( c. 1455 -- 1525 or 1526 ) was a Talmudist and posek , an authority on Halakha .
Salvatore Toma ( 11 May 1951 -- 17 March 1987 ) was an Italian poet , born in the Southern Italian region of Apulia .
Girolamo di Benvenuto ( September 1470 - June 1524 ) was an Italian painter of the High Renaissance and son of the painter Benvenuto di Giovanni .
Massimo Consoli ( 12 December 1945 -- 4 November 2007 ) was known as `` the father of the Italian gay movement '' .
Knud Reimers ( 1906 - -1987 ) was one of the most important Scandinavian yacht designers of the 20th century .
Ferdinand Siegert ( 22 , April 1865 , Neuwied am Rhein -- 21 February 1946 , Köln ) was a German pediatrician .
Yuan Cha ( 元叉 ) ( died 525 ) , courtesy name Bojun ( 伯雋 ) , nickname Yecha ( 夜叉 ) , was an official of the Chinese / Xianbei dynasty Northern Wei , who initially came to power as the brother - in - law of Emperor Xiaoming 's mother and regent Empress Dowager Hu .
Louis Brennan CB ( 28 January 1852 -- 17 January 1932 ) was an Irish - Australian mechanical engineer and inventor .
Johann Christoph Altnickol , or Altnikol , ( 1 January 1720 -- 25 July 1759 ; dates of baptism and burial ) was a German organist , bass singer , and composer .
W. J. Hill ( 1834 - -1888 ) was an English actor , singer and comedian .
Johann Burchard Freystein ( 18 April 1671 -- 1 April 1718 ) was a German lawyer and hymn writer .
Bran Becc mac Murchado ( died 738 ) was a King of Leinster from the Uí Dúnlainge branch of the Laigin .
Józef Jacek Rybiński ( born February 28 , 1701 in Torczyn , died 1782 in Oliwa ) was a Cisterian and the last abbot of the Oliwa monastery .
James William Elliott ( J.W. Elliott ) ( 1833 - -1915 ) was an English collector of nursery rhymes .
Annibale Ciarniello ( 9 January 1900 in Bagnoli del Trigno , Province of Isernia -- 3 January 2007 ) was one of the last surviving veterans of the first World War at the time of his death , as well as the oldest medical doctor in Italy and one of the oldest people in the country .
Hermenegild Santapau ( 1903 - 1970 ) was a Spanish born naturalized Indian Jesuit priest and botanist , known for his taxonomical research on Indian flora .
Carlos Montezuma or Wassaja ( born c.1866 ; died 1923 ) was a Yavapai - Apache activist and a founding member of the Society of American Indians .
Luis Barrios Rojas ( 22 April 1935 -- 5 May 2010 ) , better known as Lucho Barrios , was a popular Peruvian Bolero singer , well known throughout Latin America , and especially popular in Chile .
Alexander Onufrievich Savitsky , also known as Ales Savitsky , ( 8 January 1924 -- 5 October 2015 ) was a Belarusian writer and public figure .
Jan Szczęsny Herburt ( 12 January 1567 -- 31 December 1616 ) was a Polish political writer , diplomat and a member of the Polish Sejm .
Peter Fairley ( 2 November 1930 in Kuala Lumpur , Malaysia -- 4 August 1998 ) was a science journalist who was the Science Editor for Independent Television News and TV Times magazine the late sixties and early seventies .
Maurice Edmond Müller ( 28 March 1918 -- 10 May 2009 ) was a Swiss orthopedic surgeon who was instrumental in the development of internal fixation techniques to treat bone fractures and who also significantly advanced the development of the hip prostheses .
Potenciano Gregorio , often referred to as Potenciano Gregorio , Sr . ( May 19 , 1880 to February 12 , 1939 ) was a Bicolano musician .
Adolphus Bernays ( 18 May 1795 , Mainz , Electorate of Mainz -- 22 December 1864 , Rectory , Great Stanmore , Middlesex ) was the first professor of German in the King 's College in London , and second professor of German in England .
Martín Fernández de Vilches ( also Martín de Vilches ) ( born Vilches , Kingdom of Jaén , ? - Bonilla de la Sierra , died ( 13 November 1469 ) , was a Roman Catholic prelate who served as Bishop of Ávila ( 1456 - 1469 ) .
Si Guo ( Chinese : 思果 ; Jyutping : Si Gwo ; 10 June 1918 -- 8 June 2004 ) is the pen name of `` Frederick '' Tsai Chuo - tang ( Chinese : 蔡濯堂 ; pinyin : Caì Zhuótáng ) , a renowned Chinese and translator most active between the 1940s and 1970s .
Fritz Herlen ( or Herlin ) ( before 1449 -- October 12 , 1491 ) was a German artist of the early Swabian school , in the 15th century .
John George Macleod ( Kirkhill , 8 May 1915 -- Edinburgh , 4 April 2006 ) was a Scottish doctor of medicine and a writer of medical textbooks .
Landgravine Elisabeth Amalie of Hesse - Darmstadt ( Elisabeth Amalie Magdalene ; 20 March 1635 -- 4 August 1709 ) was a princess of Hesse - Darmstadt and wife of the Prince - elector of the Palatinate .
John Boaden ( 1792/3 - -1839 ) was an English portrait painter
Charles Makley ( November 24 , 1889 - -September 22 , 1934 ) , also known as Charles McGray and Fat Charles , was an American criminal and bank robber active in the early 20th century , most notably as a criminal associate of John Dillinger .
Bob Standfield ( 30 September 1915 -- 1 October 1993 ) is a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton and Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Paul Hansard ( 1922 - -2013 ) was a German - born actor on both television and film .
Chet Parker ( August , 1891 - -1975 ) was a hammered dulcimer player from Michigan .
Frans Geurtsen ( 17 March 1942 -- 12 December 2015 ) was a Dutch footballer , who played at both professional and international levels as a striker .
Moira Forsyth ( 1905 - -1991 ) was an English stained glass artist .
Robert Maillart ( 6 February 1872 -- 5 April 1940 ) was a Swiss civil engineer who revolutionized the use of structural reinforced concrete with such designs as the three - hinged arch and the deck - stiffened arch for bridges , and the beamless floor slab and mushroom ceiling for industrial buildings .
Thelma Dewitty ( 1912 - -1977 ) was the first African American to teach in the Seattle Public Schools , Seattle , Washington , U.S ..
Capt . Edward Lyon Buchwalter ( June 1 , 1841 -- October 4 , 1933 ) was a Union Captain in the American Civil War , corporate figure , banker and farmer .
Louis Kronenberger ( December 9 , 1904 -- April 30 , 1980 ) was an American critic and author .
Jerzy Adamski ( 14 March 1937 -- 6 December 2002 ) was a Polish featherweight boxer who won a silver medal at the 1960 Olympics and a European title in 1959 .
Professor Joy Tivy ( 1924 - -1995 ) was a physical geographer at the University of Glasgow .
Jumbe Rajab Jumbe ( 19 March 1940 -- 26 October 2005 ) was a Tanzanian politician and member of the opposition party Chama cha Demokrasia na Maendeleo ( CHADEMA ) .
Hans Willem van Aylva ( ca . 1633 , Holwerd - 21 February 1691 , near Leuven ) was a Dutch soldier .
Isabella Pallavicini ( died 1286 ) , sometimes Jezebel , was the marchioness of Bodonitsa from 1278 .
Chu Yuan ( 褚淵 ) ( 435 - -482 ) , courtesy name Yanhui ( 彥回 ) , formally Duke Wenjian of Nankang ( 南康文簡公 ) , was a high - level official of the Chinese dynasties Liu Song and Southern Qi .
Charles Philippe Dieussart ( also Charles Philipp ) ( ca . 1625 - 1696 ) was a Dutch architect and sculptor , active in Germany in the second half of the seventeenth century .
Archibald Crawford , 1st Baron Hungarton ( 12 September 1890 -- 14 June 1966 ) , was a British businessman .
Sebhat Aregawi ( died 28 February 1914 ) was a Ras of Ethiopia .
Baburam Acharya ( Nepali:बाबुराम आचार्य ) ( 1888 -- 1971 ) was a Nepalese historian and literary scholar who coined the name Sagarmatha ( सगरमाथा ) , for the mountain better known as Mount Everest or Chomolungma ( in Sherpa Language ) or Quomolungma ( Tibetan ) .
Mary Stanley ( 1813 - -1879 ) is known primarily because of her dispute in the Crimea with Florence Nightingale , whose friend she also was .
William Burlestone or Borleston ( died 1406 ) , of Harberton , Devon , was an English politician .
Alfred Wilhelm Volkmann ( 1 July 1801 -- 21 April 1877 ) was a German physiologist , anatomist , and philosopher .
Junior Heffernan ( 11 August 1989 -- 3 March 2013 ) was an Irish triathlete and then bicyclist who at the end of his cut short athletic career was competing mostly in Great Britain .
Pierre - Olivier Malherbe ( 1569 - -1616 ) was a French explorer from the city of Vitré .
Matthew Fell ( 23 August 1875 -- 17 March 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood during the early years of the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Francis Caldwell CBE MVO KPM ( c.1860 -- 17 April 1934 ) was a British police officer who served as Head Constable of Liverpool City Police from 1912 to 1925 .
Xu Miao ( 172 - -249 ) , courtesy name Jingshan , was an official of the state of Cao Wei during the Three Kingdoms period .
Haji Mohamad Misbach , commonly known as Haji Misbach or Haji Merah ( Indonesian : The Red Hajji ) , Surakarta , 1876 - -1926 , was an early communist figure from the Dutch East Indies who preached that Islam and Communism were compatible .
Edmund la Touche Armstrong ( 1864 - 1946 ) , was an Australian historian and librarian .
Þuríður Sturludóttir ( 1199 - -1238 ) was daughter of Icelandic chieftain Sturla Sighvatsson and Sólveig Sæmundsdóttir .
Charles de Lannoy ( c. 1487 -- 23 September 1527 ) was a soldier and statesman from the Low Countries in service of the Habsburg Emperors Maximilian I and Charles V of Spain .
George Kanngieser ( 27 February 1912 -- 27 January 1997 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Jan Wacław Machajski ( 1866 , Busko - Zdrój -- 1926 ) , pseudonym A. Wolski ( A. Vol'ski ) ( often corrupted in Russian as Makhaev ) , was a Polish anarchist whose methodology was thoroughly Marxist .
István Klimek or Stefan Climek ( born 15 April 1913 , death 12 November 1988 ) , was a Romanian international footballer of Hungarian origin who played as a striker .
M. Anto Peter Ramesh ( 26 April 1967 -- 12 July 2012 ) was a Tamil computer scientist and technical writer .
Collela Mazee died in the evening of Tuesday 7 March 2000 at Masaba Hospital in Nairobi , Kenya after being admitted to the hospital on the 4th Saturday suffering from cardio - pulmonary arrest .
John Dylan Morgan ( 3 May 1946 -- 5 March 2011 ) was a mathematician , physicist , hypnotherapist , and author .
Jean - Claude Irvoas ( 1949 - -2005 ) was a French employee of a street furniture firm .
Saint Agathangelus of Rome ( died 312 ) , was a Roman deacon and disciple of Clement of Ancyra , was a martyr during the reign of emperor Diocletian .
Sherard Falkner Allison ( 19 January 1907 - -31 May 1993 ) was an English bishop .
Hendrik Swellengrebel ( Cape Town , 20 September 1700 -- Utrecht , 26 December 1760 ) was the first and only Dutch East India Company governor of the Dutch Cape Colony who was born in the Cape .
Jacob Frederick Warouw ( 8 September 1917 -- 15 October 1960 ) , also known as Joop Warouw , was a military officer involved in the Indonesian National Revolution .
Dr Charles Bernard Childs FRSE ( 1895 - 1956 ) was a British physicist and mathematician .
Maria Pogonowska ( 30 October 1897 -- 15 July 2009 ) was a Polish scientist of Jewish origin .
Norm Cashin ( 15 July 1915 -- 21 July 1969 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rigord ( Rigordus ) ( c. 1150 -- c. 1209 ) was a French chronicler , was probably born near Alais in Languedoc , and became a physician .
Sir Thomas Spencer , 3rd Baronet ( 1 January 1639 - 6 March 1685 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1679 .
Sir Muhammad Munawar Khan KCIE ( died 1903 ) was the Prince of Arcot from 1889 to 1903 .
Henry Haberfield Thomas ( 11 May 1886 - 17 October 1918 ) was an English aircraft designer and chief designer at S.E. Saunders Limited .
Germaine Cellier ( 1909 - -1976 ) was a French master perfumer .
Hugh Theodore Pinhey ( 7 December 1858 -- 6 February 1953 ) was a British soldier and one of the last surviving veterans of the Second Anglo - Afghan War .
Anastasios Andreou ( Greek : Αναστάσιος Ανδρέου , 1877 -- 1947 ) was a Greek athlete from Cyprus .
John Berridge ( February 1716 − 22 January 1793 ) was an Anglican evangelical revivalist and hymnist .
Frank Wilcoxon ( 2 September 1892 -- 18 November 1965 ) was a chemist and statistician , known for the development of several statistical tests .
Fydell Edmund Garrett ( 1865 - -1907 ) , known as Edmund Garrett , was a British publicist , journalist and poet .
Elias Constantine ( 22 May 1912 -- 22 May 2003 ) was a Trinidadian cricketer who played first - class cricket for Trinidad between 1932 and 1949 .
Anders Jahan Retzius ( 3 October 1742 - 6 October 1821 ) was a Swedish chemist , botanist and entomologist .
Ole Jacob Broch ( 14 January 1818 -- 5 February 1889 ) was a Norwegian mathematician , physicist , economist and politician .
Maurice Henry Pappworth ( 9 January 1910 -- 12 October 1994 ) was a pioneering British medical ethicist and tutor , best known for his 1967 book Human Guinea Pigs , which exposed the unethical dimensions of medical research .
Dae Wihae ( died 906 ) ( reigned 894 - -906 ) was the 14th king of the 7th--10th century Balhae kingdom , which encompassed modern day Korea and some southern parts of northeast China .
Lawrence Duhé ( 30 April 1887 -- 1960 ) was an early jazz clarinetist and bandleader .
Gheorghe Leonida ( 1892?-93 - 1942 ) was a Romanian sculptor known for creating the head of Christ the Redeemer , the statue of Jesus Christ in Rio de Janeiro , Brazil .
Fulvio Orsini ( 11 December 1529 -- 18 May 1600 ) was an Italian humanist , historian , and archaeologist .
Ede Király ( 23 February 1926 -- 10 August 2009 ) was a Hungarian figure skater .
Robert Carr Bosanquet ( 1871 - -1935 ) was a British archaeologist , operating in the Aegean and Britain and teaching at the University of Liverpool from 1906 to 1920 as the first holder of the Chair of Classical Archaeology there .
Franco Frasi , also known as Francesco Frasi ( 11 January 1928 -- 9 April 2009 ) was an Italian professional football player .
Han Hong - ki ( Hangul : 한홍기 ; 1924 -- 1996 ) was a South Korean football player and manager .
John C. Sullivan ( died 1830 ) was a surveyor who established the Indian Boundary Line and the Sullivan Line which were to form the boundary between Native Americans and white settlers in Indian Territory from Iowa to Texas .
Alhaji Abdurrahman Shugaba Darman ( 1920 - -2010 ) was a Nigerian politician from Borno State , and a contemporary of the late Sir Ahmadu Bello .
Kunhikuttan Thampuran ( 1864 - -1913 ) was an Indian poet from Kodungallur , Kerala .
Moshe Flimann ( Hebrew : משה פלימן‎ ; 1905 - -1973 ) served as the mayor of Haifa from 1969 to 1973 .
Brahim Déby Itno ( 6 June 1980 -- 2 July 2007 ) was the son of current Chadian President Idriss Déby .
Curumsey Damjee ( also spelled Karamsi or Kasamshi Damji ) JP , Rai Bahadur ( 1844 - 1918 ) was a noted businessman .
Richard Assheton Cross , 2nd Viscount Cross ( 28 January 1882 -- 14 March 1932 ) , was a British peer and civil servant .
Hayyim ben Jacob Alfandari ( 1588 -- 1640 ) was a talmudic educator and writer , teaching at Constantinople in 1618 .
Qi Yunshi ( 1751 - -1815 ) was a Chinese official and historian exiled to Central Asia between 1805 and 1809 who together with Wang Tingkai and Xu Song was prominent among the exiled officials employed by Songyun , the military governor of Xinjiang from 1802 to 1809 , to compile a gazetteer of Xinjiang .
Georg August Thilesen ( 20 December 1837 - 20 December 1917 ) was the Norwegian Minister of the Interior 1888 - 1889 and 1898 - 1899 , member of the Council of State Division in Stockholm 1899 - 1900 , and Minister of Finance in 1900 .
Senzangakhona kaJama ( ca . 1762 -- 1816 ) was a chief of the Zulu clan , and primarily notable as the father of three Zulu kings who ruled during the period when the Zulus achieved prominence , led by his oldest son Shaka .
Wang Zongji ( 王宗佶 ) ( died May 1 , 908 ) , né Gan ( 甘 ) , was an adoptive son of Wang Jian , the founding emperor of the Five Dynasties and Ten Kingdoms period state Former Shu .
Paul Haefliger ( 1914 in Germany -- 1982 in Switzerland ) was an abstract painter , art critic , writer and printmaker .
Joseph Weiß ( 1486 or 1487 - -1565 ) was a German Renaissance painter .
Hermann Steiner ( 1913 - 14 November 2005 ) was a Swiss inventor and businessman .
John Hastings , 2nd Baron Hastings ( 29 September 1287 -- 20 January 1325 ) was a medieval English Baron .
Rabbi Avraham Wolfensohn ( 1783 - -1855 ) was a Jewish rabbi , Talmudic judge and leader of the Askenazi community in Safed , Ottoman Syria in the middle of the 19th century .
Carl Jerrold Peterson ( 31 October 1936 -- 2 April 1969 ) was a United States Navy Lieutenant Commander and the commanding officer of Patrol River Boat Squadron 57 .
Vicente Lucio Salazar ( 20 December 1832 -- 14 February 1896 ) was Acting President of Ecuador between 16 April 1895 and 1 September 1895 .
John Neil McGilp OBE ( 30 October 1881 -- 1963 ) was a South Australian pastoralist and amateur ornithologist .
Ghislaine Dupont ( /ʒislɛn dypõ/ ; 13 January 1956 -- 2 November 2013 ) was a French journalist who specialised in African issues .
Preserved Fish ( 1766 - -1846 ) was a prominent New York City shipping merchant in the early 19th century .
Jean Baptiste Claude Chatelain ( 1710 - -1758 ) was an English engraver of French background .
André Lefaur ( 25 July 1879 - 5 December 1952 ) was a French film and theatre actor , notably working several times with director Sacha Guitry .
Agnes Nicholls ( 14 July 1876 ( some sources say 1877 ) -- 21 September 1959 ) was one of the greatest English sopranos of the 20th century , both in the concert hall and on the operatic stage .
Robert Spearman ( 1703 - -1761 ) was an English theologian , known as a Hutchinsonian .
John Clavell Mansel - Pleydell ( 1817 - -1902 ) , originally John Clavell Mansel , was a Dorset antiquary , known for contributions to geology , botany , and ornithology .
Happy Akhand ( Bengali : হ্যাপী আখন্দ ; 12 October 1960 -- 28 December 1987 ) was a Bangladeshi musician .
Gianna Persaki ( Greek : Γιάννα Περσάκη , French : Jeanne Persaki ; 1921 - -2008 ) was a distinguished woman artist , pioneer abstract painter and committed modernist , focused on the geometric structure of pictorial space and the thorough analysis of colour relationships .
Thomas Vincent ( May 1634 -- 15 October 1678 ) was an English Puritan minister and author .
Ronald Ferns ( 14 October 1925 -- 2 December 1997 ) was an English illustrator , designer , cartoonist and surrealist painter in oil and watercolour .
The Reverend George Turner Waldegrave MBE ( 18 March 1889 -- 15 May 1966 ) was the son of Reverend Samuel Edmund Waldegrave and Alice Millett .
Mikhail Marynich ( Belarusian : Міхаіл Марыніч ; Russian : Михаил Маринич - Marinich , 13 January 1940 -- 17 October 2014 ) was a Belarusian opposition leader from Homiel Voblast .
Gerard McLarnon ( 16 April 1915 , in Clitheroe , Lancashire -- 16 August 1997 ) was an English - Irish actor and playwright .
Benoni W. Finch ( died 1851 ) was an American pioneer .
Anthony Browne , 1st Viscount Montagu KG PC ( 29 November 1528 -- 19 October 1592 ) was an English peer during the Tudor period .
James Caughey ( 9 April 1810 -- 30 January 1891 ) was a Methodist minister and evangelist who was active in the United States , England and Canada .
Pope Benedict III ( Latin : Benedictus III ; died 17 April 858 ) was Pope from 29 September 855 to his death in 858 .
Andy Hughes ( 11 November 1965 -- 12 June 2009 ) was an English electronic music producer from Harrow , Middlesex .
Ratislaus of Rügen ( German : also Ratze , before 1105 -- 1141 ) was King of Rügen or Prince of the Rugians ( or Rani ) .
Clarrie Calwell ( 9 September 1896 -- 28 September 1975 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Charles Albanel ( 1616 -- 11 January 1696 ) , born in Auvergne , was a French missionary explorer in Canada , and a Jesuit priest .
Henri Charles Loeillot or Loeillot - Hartwig ( 1798 - -1864 ) , usually known as Karl Loeillot , was a French painter and lithographer .
Jayakanthan ( 24 April 1934 -- 8 April 2015 ) , popularly known as JK , was an Indian writer , journalist , orator , film - maker , critic and activist .
Ridgway Robert Syers Christian Codner Lloyd ( 20 December 1842 -- 1 June 1884 ) was an English physician and antiquary .
Charles Cooper Penrose - Fitzgerald ( 30 April 1841 -- 11 August 1921 ) was a Vice - Admiral in the Royal Navy .
John Richard de Capel Wise ( 1831 - -1 April 1890 ) was a writer and natural historian .
Thomas Copley , alias Philip Fisher ( born 1596 , Madrid , Spain -- 1652 , British colony of Maryland ) was an English Jesuit missionary in North America .
Philip van Artevelde ( c. 1340 -- 27 November 1382 ) was a Flemish patriot , the son of Jacob van Artevelde .
Eddy J. Changkye ( 2 February 1924 -- 31 October 1994 ) was a Mauritian diplomat , politician , Member of the National Assembly of Mauritius , municipal councillor , mayor , jurist , writer and poet .
John Burnet Biddulph ( 10 December 1796 Wigginton , Staffordshire - 3 March 1837 Graaff - Reinet ) was a South African explorer and trader who arrived with the 1820 Settlers .
Friedrich Wilhelm Brandtner ( 28 July 1896 - 1969 ) , known during his life as Fritz Brandtner , was a German - Canadian artist and art instructor .
Clarice Mayne ( 6 February 1886 -- 16 January 1966 ) was a music hall and variety theatre singer and performer .
Jasper Grosvenor ( 1794 - -1857 ) was an American financier of the early to mid 19th century .
After severe illness and suffering from depression , Nellie Cameron committed suicide through gas asphyxiation at her Taylor Square flat on 8 November 1953 .
Elvin J. Cassell ( December 3 , 1896 -- August 1970 ) was an American football coach in the United States .
George Lenne ( 20 February 1916 -- 18 February 2014 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Thomas Stewart , 2nd Earl of Angus ( b.b.1331 - 1361 ) was a medieval Scottish nobleman .
Ernest Blakelock Thubron , also known as Émile Thubron ( Boldon near Durham 15 July 1861 - 22 May 1927 Tokomaru , New Zealand ) was an Anglo - French motorboat racer and Olympic champion .
Harlan Lattimore ( November 25 , 1908- July,1980 ) , was a popular African - American singer with several jazz orchestras of the 1930s , most notably Don Redman 's .
Ma Yuanyi ( died 184 ) was a Yellow Turban rebel during the late Han Dynasty period .
Henry Rich , 1st Earl of Holland KG KB PC ( 19 August 1590 ( baptised ) -- 9 March 1649 ) , known as The Lord Kensington between 1623 and 1624 , was an English courtier , peer and soldier .
Giacomo Costa ( 14 December 1919 -- 22 January 2000 ) was an Italian Australian professional wrestler best known by his ring name , Al Costello .
Lord Henry Murray ( 13 June 1767 -- 3 December 1805 ) was a soldier and administrator who served as the fourth Lieutenant Governor of the Isle of Man .
Louisa Stevenson ( 15 July 1835 - -1908 ) was a Scottish campaigner for women 's university education , women 's suffrage and effective , well - organised nursing .
George Reavey ( 1 May 1907 -- 11 August 1976 ) was a Russian - born Irish surrealist poet , publisher , translator and art collector .
Gilbert Greenall , 1st Baron Daresbury DL ( 30 March 1867 -- 24 October 1938 ) , known as Sir Gilbert Greenall , 2nd Baronet , from 1894 to 1927 , was a British businessman .
Matthew Habershon ( 1789 - -1852 ) , was an English architect .
Richard Mowat or Mowatt ( 1865 - -1936 ) was a renowned and award - winning player of the Northumbrian smallpipes .
Radoslav Brzobohatý ( Czech pronunciation : ( ˈradoslaf ˈbr̩zoboɦatiː ) ; 13 September 1932 -- 12 September 2012 ) was a Czech film and television actor .
William Pierce Stubbs ( 1842 - -1909 ) or W.P. Stubbs was a marine painter in the Boston , Massachusetts , area in the 19th century .
Henri Dobert ( 1915 - -1943 ) was a member of the Buckmaster resistant cell during World War II . He was in charge of gathering information on building , location and troop movement in the Cabourg - Houlgate sector in Normandy .
Warren Bruno ( died 2012 ) was a restaurateur in Atlanta and a community leader in Atlanta 's Virginia - Highland neighborhood .
Sir Charles Solomon Henry , 1st Baronet ( 28 January 1860 -- 27 December 1919 ) was an Australian merchant and businessman who lived mostly in Britain and sat as a Liberal Member of Parliament ( MP ) in the House of Commons from 1906 until his death .
Manuel Afonso de Guerra was a Portuguese Bishop who served as Governor of Portuguese Cape Verde from 1622 until his death on 8 March 1624 .
Sir Francis Grant Ogilvie CB ( 8 August 1858 -- 14 December 1930 ) was a Scottish educator , museum director , and scientist .
Dhammazedi ( Burmese : ဓမ္မစေတီ , pronounced : ( dəma̰zèdì ) ; c. 1409 - -1492 ) was the 16th king of the Hanthawaddy Kingdom in Burma from 1471 to 1492 .
Henry Edward Doyle CB ( 1827 -- 17 February 1893 ) was a British painter and draughtsman , and for 23 years the director of the National Gallery of Ireland .
Laura Drew , a.k.a . Singh Kaur or Lorellei ( 1955 - -1998 ) was a new - age music composer , vocalist and instrumentalist , who had a prolific career that lasted from the early 1970s to the late 1990s , releasing 23 albums .
Bona Sijabat ( c. 1800 -- 1862 ) was a well - respected and long - time chief of a Batak tribe .
Abu'l - Fawaris , better known by his regnal name Qawam al - Dawla ( April 1000 -- October / November 1028 ) , was the Buyid ruler of Kerman ( 1012 - -1028 ) .
Franc Rozman , nom de guerre Stane ( Slovene convention : Franc Rozman -- Stane ) or Stane Mlinar , 27 March 1911 -- 7 November 1944 ) , was a Slovene Partisan commander in World War II .
Franciscus Bonae Spei ( 20 June 1617 -- 5 January 1677 ) was a Catholic scholastic theologian and philosopher .
Sheikh Liaquat Hussain ( 1929 -- 23 September 2009 ) , was a Pakistani politician and political figure who was the Member of the National Assembly from 1997 until his death .
Abu Nasr Abdul Kahhar ( also known as Sultan Haji or Haji of Banten ) was the sultan of Banten from 1682 to 1687 , who was largely responsible for subjugating Banten to the Dutch East India Company ( VOC ) .
Robert Knight , 1st Earl of Catherlough , KB , ( 1702 - -1772 ) , was a British Member of Parliament for Great Grimsby ( 1734 - -41 , 1762 - -68 ) , Castle Rising , Norfolk ( 1747 - -54 ) and Milborne Port , Somerset ( 1770 - -72 ) .
Alghu ( d. 1265 or 1266 ) was a khan of the Chagatai Khanate ( 1260 - 1265/6 ) .
Lu Ruilin ( Chinese : 鲁瑞林 ) ( 1911 - -1999 ) was a People 's Republic of China politician and People 's Liberation Army major general .
Hoon Balakram ( 1876 - -1929 ) was an Indian mathematician , civil servant and Bombay High Court judge .
Sidney Clarence Garrison ( 1885 - -1945 ) was an American educator and psychologist .
Alardo de Popma ( born before 1617 ; d. 1641 ) was a Flemish engraver , who worked in Madrid in the early seventeenth century , according to the earliest references to his works .
Larry Bimi ( died 23 July 2011 ) was a Ghanaian lawyer and public official .
Major Sir David Hughes - Morgan , 1st Baronet ( c. 1870 - -16 March 1941 ) , born David Hughes Morgan ( he changed his surname to Hughes - Morgan by deed poll in 1925 ) , was a Welsh solicitor and landowner .
Major - General John Tombs ( 1777 - -1848 ) was an officer in the British East India Company .
Henryk Minkiewicz ( 19 January 1880 -- 9 April 1940 ) was a Polish socialist politician and a General of the Polish Army .
Carl Raymond Gray ( 1867 - -1939 ) was an American railroad executive in the early 20th century .
Mimi Aguglia ( 21 December 1884 -- 31 July 1970 ) was an Italian actress , who was born in Catania , Sicily while her own mother , actress Giuseppina Aguglia , was playing Desdemona in Othello .
Cyril Ritchard ( 1 December 1898 -- 18 December 1977 ) was an Australian stage , screen and television actor , and director .
Choe Chang - ik ( Hangul : 최창익 , hanja : 崔昌益 , 1896 in Onsong County -- 1960 in Pyongyang ) was a Korean Independence activist , soldier , Social Movements .
Brian Swatuk ( 9 July 1949 -- 13 December 2014 ) was a Canadian jockey in Thoroughbred horse racing .
Elisabeth Röhl ; née Elisabeth Gohlke ( born Landsberg an der Warthe 22 August 1888 : died Düsseldorf 21 September 1930 ) was a German politician who unusually ( at the time ) was also a woman .
Count Kálmán Hunyady de Kéthely ( born 13 October 1828 , died 17 May 1901 ) was a Hungarian nobleman from the Hunyady family .
Bernardino Ludovisi ( c. 1693 -- 11 December 1749 ) , also called Bernardo , was an Italian sculptor .
Søren Nielsen May ( born in Helsingborg , died 16 September 1679 in Holbæk ) , also spelled Søren Nielsen Maj , was a Danish priest , who was parish priest and provost in Holbæk .
Tibor Bitskey ( 20 September 1929 -- 2 February 2015 ) was a Hungarian television and film actor .
Philibert Le Roy ( died 1646 ) was a 17th - century French architect and military engineer who worked in the Baroque and classical styles .
Leonard Mullins ( 1918 -- 19 September 1997 ) was a scientist and long - time Research Director at the former Malaysian Rubber Producers ' Research Association .
Daniel Innes ( ca . 1835 - -1918 ) operated dry - goods businesses in Illinois and Kansas and was a Los Angeles , California , real estate developer and investor .
Ulrich Woronowicz ( 26 January 1928 - -7 December 2011 ) was an East German Protestant theologian and writer .
Frederick William Sanderson ( 13 May 1857 -- 15 June 1922 ) was headmaster of Oundle School from 1892 until his death .
Peretz Kidron ( 29 July 1933 -- 6 November 2011 ) was an Israeli writer , journalist , and translator .
Professor Sir Edmund Happold ( 1930 - 12 January 1996 ) , better known as Ted Happold , was a structural engineer and founder of Buro Happold .
Jacob Fegth ( also spelled Feght ) ( born 18 September 1761 at Tangen , Drammen , died 2 October 1834 at Tangen , Drammen ) was a Norwegian timber merchant and ship - owner , and one of the largest timber merchants of Drammen in the early 19th century .
Blessed Luigi Caburlotto ( 7 June 1817 -- 6 July 1897 ) was an Italian priest and was the founder of the Daughters of Saint Joseph .
Tomás de Torrejón y Velasco Sánchez ( 23 December 1644 -- 23 April 1728 ) was a Spanish composer , musician and organist based in Peru , associated with the American Baroque .
Zhang Chunqiao ( Chinese : 张春桥 ; 1 February 1917 -- 21 April 2005 ) was a prominent Chinese political theorist , writer , and politician .
Edward Ayshford Sanford , FRS ( 23 May 1794 -- 1 December 1871 ) was a British Member of Parliament .
Angus MacVicar ( 28 October 1908 , Argyll -- 31 October 2001 , Campbeltown , Argyll and Bute ) was a Scottish author with a wide - ranging output .
John Baughan ( 1754 -- 25 September 1797 ) was a carpenter who was convicted at Oxford , England , in 1783 as Baffen ( alias Bingham and Baughan ) , and sentenced to be transported for 7 years for stealing 5 blankets .
John Cargill Brough ( 11 February 1834 -- 7 September 1872 ) , was a British science writer , lecturer , editor and librarian .
Edward Turberville or Turbervile ( c. 1648 -- 1681 ) was a Welsh informer , who perjured himself in support of the allegations of a Popish Plot .
Rik Renders ( 6 November 1922 -- 24 December 2008 ) was a Belgian racing cyclist .
Qamaruddin Butt ( 1914 -- 8 June 1974 ) was a Pakistani cricket player , writer and umpire .
Leonardo III Tocco was the last ruler of Epirus , from 1448 to 1479 .
Amelia Jackson ( 1842 - -1925 ) was an accomplished musician and the wife of Rector W. W. Jackson of Exeter College , Oxford .
Edward Guthlac Sergeant ( 3 December 1881 , Crowland , Lincolnshire -- 16 November 1961 , Kingston upon Thames ) was an English chess master .
Adam Rapacki ( 24 December 1909 - -10 October 1970 ) was a Polish politician and diplomat
Baroness Kathleen Annie Pannonica de Koenigswarter ( née Rothschild ; 10 December 1913 -- 30 November 1988 ) was a British - born jazz patron and writer .
Juho Niukkanen ( 27 July 1888 in Kirvu -- 17 May 1954 in Helsinki ) was a Finnish politician prior to , during , and after the Winter War .
Uwe Gronostay ( 25 October 1939 -- 29 November 2008 ) was a German choral conductor and composer .
Bernhard Rawitz ( 23 August 1857 , Ostrowo - 28 December 1932 ) was a German military physician , anatomist and zoologist .
Peter Goelet ( 1727 - 1811 ) was a merchant and real estate entrepreneur of New York City .
Maurycy Orzech ( Polish pronunciation : ( mauˈrɨt͡sɨ ˈɔʐɛx ) ; nom de guerre : Janczyn ; 1891 -- August 1943 , Warsaw ) was a Polish - Jewish economist , journalist , politician and a leader of the Jewish Bund in interwar Poland .
Rosabelle Osborne , CBE , RRC ( died 8 May 1958 ) was Principal Matron at the British War Office , 1924 .
Gerald Oshita ( 1942 - -1992 ) was an American musician , composer , and sound recordist .
Franz Ignaz von Streber ( 11 February 1758 -- 26 April 1841 ) was a German numismatist and theologian from Reisbach , Lower Bavaria .
Sheikh Mohammed Aboulkhair Zaki Badawi ( Arabic : الشيخ محمد أبو الخير زكي بدوي‎ ) , KBE , GCFO ( 14 January 1922 -- 24 January 2006 ) was a prominent Egyptian Islamic scholar , community activist , and promoter of interfaith - dialogue .
His Honour Alan George Weall Coulthard ( 20 January 1924 -- 25 June 1988 ) , was a British judge , broadcaster , writer and Liberal Party politician .
Henry J. Oosting ( March 12 , 1903-October 30 , 1968 ) was an American ecologist and professor .
Rowland Meyrick ( Merrick ) ( 1505 - -1566 ) was a Welsh bishop of Bangor .
Kujō Michiie ( 九条 道家 ) ( 1193 - -1252 ) was a Japanese regent in the 13th century .
Edward Crofton , 2nd Baron Crofton ( 1 August 1806 -- 17 December 1869 ) , known as Sir Edward Crofton , 4th Baronet , from 1816 to 1817 , was an Anglo - Irish Conservative politician .
Louis Van Zelst ( 1895 - 1915 ) was a batboy , mascot , and good luck charm for the Philadelphia Athletics from 1910 to 1914 .
Dimitrios Botsaris ( Greek : Δημήτριος Μπότσαρης , 1813 - -1871 ) was a Greek Army officer and Minister of War .
Sir Hugh Segrave or Seagrave ( died c. 1387 ) was a Lord Keeper of the Great Seal and Treasurer of England under Richard II of England .
Eduardo Lefebvre Scovell ( 1864 - -1918 ) was a British artist who was born on 26 August 1864 .
Yasa'ur ( died 1320 ) was a Chagatai prince who launched a revolt against the Ilkhan Abu Sa'id .
William Cowper , 1st Earl Cowper PC KC FRS ( c. 1665 -- 10 October 1723 ) was an English politician who became the first Lord Chancellor of Great Britain .
Matilda of Flanders ( French : Mathilde de Flandre ; Dutch : Mathilda van Vlaanderen ) ( c. 1031 -- 2 November 1083 ) was the wife of William the Conqueror and , as such , Queen of England .
Adolius ( Greek : ' Αδόλιος , d. 543 ) was a Byzantine silentiarius and military officer , active in the reign of Justinian I ( r. 527 - -565 ) .
George Newell Bowers ( 1849 - 1909 , active 1872 - 1906 ) was an American painter in Springfield , Massachusetts .
John William Norie ( 1772 in London -- 1843 ) , was a mathematician , hydrographer , chart maker and publisher of nautical books most famous for his Epitome of Practical Navigation ( 1805 ) which became a standard work on navigation and went through many editions as did many of Norie 's works .
Howard Gaye ( 1878 - -1955 ) was a British actor who worked mainly in the United States .
Hermann Schreiber ( 21 August 1882 -- 27 September 1954 ) was a German doctor of philosophy , rabbi and journalist .
Concemore Thomas Thwaites Cramp ( 19 March 1876 - -13 July 1933 ) , known as Charlie Cramp , was a British trade unionist and political activist .
Pearse Hutchinson ( 1927 -- 14 January 2012 ) was an Irish poet , broadcaster and translator .
Francesco Martelli ( 1633 -- 28 September 1717 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic Cardinal .
Thomas Chaplin ( 1591 - -1672 ) was an English draper and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1659 and 1660 .
Tim Coffey ( d. 8 November 1999 ) was an Irish soccer player .
Richard Traubner ( November 24 , 1946 -- February 25 , 2013 ) was an American journalist , author , operetta scholar and historian , and lecturer on theatre and ( mostly musical ) film .
Svatopluk Pluskal ( 28 October 1930 -- 29 May 2005 ) was a Czechoslovak footballer and holder of a silver medal from the World Cup in Chile in 1962 .
James Hoey Craigie TD FRIBA ( 7 May 1870 -- 30 March 1930 ) was a Scottish architect .
Johnny Murray ( 25 February 1898,-- 12 November 1954 ) was an Irish soccer player during the 1920s .
Sandor Salgo ( Hungarian : Salgó Sándor ; Budapest , 10 March 1909-Palo Alto , California , 2007 ) was a Hungarian - born Jewish composer , conductor , and violist who emigrated to America in 1937 .
James Carnegie , 9th Earl of Southesk KT ( 16 November 1827 -- 21 February 1905 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Harold Wesley George ( c. 1887 -- 10 May 1915 ) was an Australian representative rugby union prop forward who saw active service and fell in World War I.
Dr. George D. Winter ( 1927 - 1981 ) was the British - born pioneer of moist wound healing .
Henry Peyto - Verney , 16th Baron Willoughby de Broke and de jure 24th Baron Latimer ( 1773 - -1852 ) was a peer in the peerage of England .
W. S. Bodey ( 1814 -- 1859 ) was a prospector from Poughkeepsie , New York who discovered gold in Eastern California .
Wang Buwen ( zh : 王步文 , pinyin : Wáng Bùwén ) ( b. 13 January 1898 - d. 31 May 1931 ) was a Chinese politician in service to the Republic of China and the People 's Republic of China .
Eugenios Eugenidis ( Greek : Ευγένιος Ευγενίδης , December 1882 -- April 1954 ) was a prominent Greek shipping magnate of the 20th century .
Henri Teixeira de Mattos ( 1856 - -1908 ) , was a 19th - century Dutch sculptor .
Alfieri Maserati ( 23 September 1887 -- 3 March 1932 ) was an Italian automotive engineer , known for establishing and leading the Maserati racing car manufacturer with the other Maserati Brothers .
Ali Çetinkaya , also known as `` Kel '' Ali Bey ( 1878 - -21 February 1949 ) was an Ottoman Army officer and Turkish politician who served eight terms in the Grand National Assembly of Turkey , including a period in 1939 - -40 as his country 's first Minister of Transport .
James Rennell Rodd , 1st Baron Rennell GCB GCMG GCVO PC ( 9 November 1858 - -26 July 1941 ) , known as Sir Rennell Rodd before 1933 , was a British diplomat , poet and politician .
William Hales ( 8 April 1747 -- 30 January 1831 ) was an Irish clergyman and scientific writer .
Zhu Dexi ( Chinese : 朱德熙 ; pinyin : Zhū Déxī ; 1920 - -1992 ) was a Chinese linguist , grammarian , and educator .
Ursula Günther ( 15 June 1927 -- 20 or 21 November 2006 ) was a German musicologist specializing in the fourteenth and early fifteenth centuries and the music of Giuseppe Verdi .
Paul de Foix de Carmain ( 1528 - -1584 ) was a French prelate and diplomat .
Michael Maybrick ( 31 January 1841 -- 26 August 1913 ) was an English composer and singer , best known under his pseudonym Stephen Adams as the composer of `` The Holy City , '' one of the most popular religious songs in English .
Ygo Gales Galama ( c. 1443 -- 25 January 1492 ) was a 15th - century Frisian warlord and Galama - patriarch .
Roseo José Dagdag Rosales , Jr. ( 24 March 1974 -- 4 December 2011 ) also known as RJ Rosales , was a Filipino Australian singer , actor , musical theatre performer and TV presenter .
Marie - Anne Fragonard , née Gérard,(1745 - -1823 ) was a French painter of portrait miniatures .
Hazel Bell Wines ( 1885 - -April 1949 ) was a US teacher , politician , artist , and organizer for historical preservation in Nevada .
Leo Passianos ( died 22 June 1017 ) was the Byzantine general sent by the Catapan of Italy Leo Tornikios Kontoleon to fight the Lombard rebel Melus of Bari in 1017 .
Gáspár Heltai ( born : Kaspar Helth ) ( c. 1490 - -1574 ) was a Transylvanian Saxon writer and printer .
Anton Schwarzkopf ( 8 July 1924 -- 30 July 2001 ) was a German engineer of amusement rides , and founder of the Schwarzkopf Industries Company , which built numerous amusement rides and large roller coasters for both amusement parks and travelling funfairs .
Laura Henderson ( 6 December 1863 -- 29 November 1944 ) born Laura Forster , rose to prominence in the 1930s when , as a wealthy and eccentric widow , she founded the Windmill Theatre in London 's Great Windmill Street , in partnership with Vivian van Damm .
Sir Philip Carteret , 2nd Baronet ( c. 1650 - -1693 ) , also known as Philippe de Carteret IV , was the 5th Seigneur of Sark from 1663 to 1693 .
Frederick Tatham ( 31 July 1805 -- 29 July 1878 ) was an English artist who was a member of the Shoreham Ancients , a group of followers of William Blake .
Nissim Eliad ( Hebrew : נסים אליעד‎ , 1 July 1919 -- 15 November 2014 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the Independent Liberals between 1968 and 1977 .
Robert Brough ( 1872 -- 21 January 1905 ) was a Scottish painter born in Invergordon , Ross and Cromarty .
Frederick Victor Branford ( 1892 - -1941 ) was a British poet , known for verse of World War I and the years after .
Rusiate Nayacakalou ( 1927 - -1972 ) was a Fijian social anthropologist who was a graduate of the universities of New Zealand and London .
Lama Dampa Sonam Gyaltsen ( 16 May 1312 - 23 July 1375 ) , in orthographic spelling bLa ma dam pa bsod nams rgyal mts'an , was a ruler of Sakya which had a precedence position in Tibet under the Yuan dynasty .
Margrethe Vullum ( born Lehmann ; first married name Rode ; 14 February 1846 -- 14 August 1918 ) was a Danish - born Norwegian journalist , literary critic and proponent for women 's rights .
Mario Soffici ( 14 May 1900 -- 10 May 1977 ) was an Italian born Argentine film director , actor and screenwriter of the classic era .
Elias Riggs ( November 19 , 1810 -- January 17 , 1901 ) was an American Presbyterian missionary and linguist born in New Providence , New Jersey .
William Sidell ( 30 May 1915 -- 2 October 1994 ) was a carpenter and an American labor leader .
Eliza Greene Metcalf Radeke ( 1854 - 1931 ) was the president of the Rhode Island School of Design ( RISD ) in Providence , Rhode Island from 1913 to 1931 and was the daughter of RISD co - founder Helen Adelia Rowe Metcalf .
Anne Woodville , Viscountess Bourchier ( c. 1438 -- 30 July 1489 ) was an English noblewoman .
Walter Clement Powell ( 1850 - -1883 ) was an American photographer and the first cousin of Major John Wesley Powell .
Árpád Házi ( 20 September 1908 -- 13 November 1970 ) was a Hungarian communist politician , who served as Interior Minister between 1951 and 1952 .
Saint Guiraud ( 1070 - -1123 ) was a bishop of Béziers of the twelfth century He is said to have been the second prior of Cassan Abbey .
George Passantino ( 1922 - -2004 ) was an American artist , teacher , and author .
John II Orsini , also John Komnenos Doukas or Comnenus Ducas ( Greek : Ἰωάννης Κομνηνός Δούκας , Iōannēs Komnēnos Doukas , Italian : Giovanni II Orsini ) , was count palatine of Cephalonia from 1323 to 1324 and Despot of Epirus from 1323 to 1335 .
Sir Laurence Esmonde , 1st Baron Esmonde ( 1570?--1646 ) , was an Irish peer who held office as governor of the crucial fort of Duncannon .
Al - Layth ibn Ali ibn al - Layth ( died 928 ) was amir of the Saffarid amirate from 909 until 910 .
Charles Mahoney , O.F.M. , ( or Mahony ; alias Charles Meehan ; ca . 1640 -- 12 August 1679 ) was an Irish Friar Minor , who is honored as a Catholic martyr , one of the Eighty - five martyrs of England and Wales beatified by Pope John Paul II in 1987 .
Rufius Antonius Agrypnius Volusianus ( died 6 January 437 ) was a fifth - century Roman aristocrat who held at least two important posts during the reign of the emperor Honorius .
João Pereira dos Santos or Mestre João Pequeno de Pastinha ( 27 December 1917 -- 9 December 2011 ) as he was known within capoeira circles .
Roger Palmer , 1st Earl of Castlemaine , PC ( 1634 - -1705 ) was an English courtier , diplomat , and politician who sat in the House of Commons in 1660 .
David de Berry ( 1952 - -1995 ) was a U.S. composer of theater music as well as an actor and music director .
Edwin Daniel ( 1981 - -2008 ) was a Mexican artist , painter and illustrator .
Simon Kaspé ( died 1933 ) was a Jewish resident of Harbin , Manchuria , who was kidnapped , ransomed , tortured and murdered by a gang of fascist Russian criminals under the influence of Konstantin Rodzaevsky .
Bogusław IX ; ( 1407/1410 -- 7 December 1446 ) was a duke of Pomerania in Pomerania - Stolp , whose residence was Stargard .
William Chapman Foster ( 27 April 1897 - 15 October 1984 ) was an American businessman and high - ranking government official .
Gaston Sant Blanc ( 1759 - -1820 ) was a self - educated French watchmaker , the founder of the Sant Blanc watch and jewelry company .
John III Potho of Pothenstein ( also spelled Pottenstein ; d. 1390 ) was Bishop of Bishopric of Münster from 1379 to 1382 .
Georges - André Chevallaz ( 7 February 1915 -- 8 September 2002 ) was a Swiss historian , politician and member of the Swiss Federal Council ( 1974 - -1983 ) .
Levi Weeks ( 1776 - -1819 ) was the accused in the infamous Manhattan Well Murder trial of 1800 , the first murder trial in the United States for which there is a recorded transcript .
George Lily ( died 1559 ) was an English Roman Catholic priest , humanist scholar , biographer , topographer and cartographer .
Vytautas Sakalauskas ( 24 April 1933 -- 29 May 2001 ) was a Soviet Lithuanian politician who was the last Chairman of the Council of Ministers ( Prime Minister ) of the Lithuanian Soviet Socialist Republic before Lithuanian independence in 1990 .
Gertrud Grunow ( 8 July 1870 -- 11 June 1944 ) was a German composer , associated with the Bauhaus design school where she taught courses on musical composition and theory .
Petter Moe - Johansen , usually known as P. Moe - Johansen ( 16 October 1882 -- 1 April 1952 ) was a Norwegian newspaper editor and politician for the Labour and Social Democratic Labour parties .
Lizzie Higgins ( 1929 - 1993 ) was an Aberdeenshire ballad singer .
Pieter Paulus ( 9 April 1754 -- 17 March 1796 ) was a Dutch jurist , admiral - fiscal and politician .
Frederick Carlisle ( 4 November 1849 -- 22 October 1920 ) was an English cricketer active in 1869 who played for Lancashire .
Jama Mohamud Takar ( Somali : Jaamac ( Joocaar ) Maxamuud Takar ) ( 1930s -- November 2008 ) was a senior Somali politician and one of the leaders of Mohamed Muumin , a Leelkase sub - clan .
Charles Fielding ( or Feilding ; 2 July 1738 -- 11 January 1783 ) was a British naval officer who gained brief notoriety for his role in the Affair of Fielding and Bylandt in the run - up to the Fourth Anglo - Dutch War .
Saint Maughold ( Macaille , Maccaldus , Machalus , Machaoi , Machella , Maghor , Mawgan , Maccul , Macc Cuill ) of Man ( died ca . 488 AD ) is venerated as the patron saint of the Isle of Man .
Gabriel Ramushwana ( 1 July 1941 -- 12 January 2015 ) was a head of state of the South African Bantustan Venda ( 1990 - -1994 ) .
Herbert Hensley Henson ( 8 November 1863 -- 27 September 1947 ) was an Anglican priest , scholar and controversialist .
Carl Fehmer ( November 10 , 1838 -- 1917 ) was a prominent Boston architect during the 19th century , and Emerson and Fehmer was a partnership of Fehmer and William Ralph Emerson .
Sir Macpherson Robertson KBE ( 6 September 1859 -- 20 August 1945 ) was an Australian philanthropist , entrepreneur and founder of confectionery company MacRobertson 's .
Clarrie Featherston ( 11 December 1892 -- 22 June 1964 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Christos Hatzipetros ( Greek : Χρήστος Χατζηπέτρος , 1873 - -1945 ) was a Greek artillery officer who rose to the rank of Major General .
Marlo Lewis ( September 15 , 1915 -- June 8 , 1993 ) was an American executive producer of variety and comedy shows for CBS and is well known for co - producing the famous Ed Sullivan Show .
Ethel Watts Mumford ( 1876 or 78 ? -- 1940 ) was an American author from New York .
John Smith Clarke ( 4 February 1885 -- 30 January 1959 ) was a British lion tamer , politician , poet , newspaper editor and art expert .
Johanna Budwig ( 30 September 1908 -- 19 May 2003 ) was a German biochemist and author .
Henry Wainwright ( died 21 December 1875 ) was an English murderer .
Oswald Martyn ( 10 January 1887 -- 14 September 1959 ) was an English cricketer who played for Essex .
Derek Waring ( born Derek Barton - Chapple ; 26 April 1927 -- 20 February 2007 ) was an English actor who is best remembered for playing Detective Inspector Goss in Z - Cars from 1969 to 1973 .
Will Seymour Monroe ( 1863 Hunlock , Pennsylvania -- 1939 ) was a United States educator .
Xue Muqiao ( Chinese : 薛暮桥 ; pinyin : Xuē Mùqiáo ; 25 October 1904 - 22 July 2005 ) was a Chinese economist .
Satinath Bhaduri ( 27 September 1906 -- 30 March 1965 ) was a Bengali Indian novelist and politician .
Dora Meeson ( 1869 - -1955 ) was an Australian Artist and an elected member of the Royal Institute of Oil Painters in London , England .
Giuseppe Benoni ( 1618 - -1684 ) was an Italian architect , active during the Baroque period , mainly in Venice .
Joshua Percy Flowers ( 1903 -- 1982 ) began purchasing land in the early years of the Great Depression to farm cotton and tobacco , and it produced crops until the 1970s .
Rudolf van Reest ( 12 April 1897 in Rotterdam -- 29 November 1979 in Groenekan ) was the pseudonym of the Dutch writer Karel Cornelis van Spronsen .
Elizabeth Audrey Withers OBE ( 28 March 1905 -- 26 October 2001 ) , known as Audrey Withers , was an English journalist , also active as a member of the Council of Industrial Design .
William Hugh Beeton , CMG ( 14 October 1903 - 26 March 1976 ) was the Chief Commissioner of Ashanti , which became Ghana in 1957 .
Thomas Barrasford ( 1859 - -1910 ) was a 19th - century English business entrepreneur and entertainment impresario , who owned and built a number of theatres across Britain under the Barrasford Halls brand .
John de Vars Hazard MC ( 18 August 1888 -- 12 June 1968 ) was a British Army officer and mountaineer who took part in the 1924 British Mount Everest expedition , most famous for the disappearance of the mountaineers George Mallory and Andrew `` Sandy '' Irvine .
Sir Harold Basil Houldsworth , 2nd Baronet ( 21 July 1922 -- 24 March 1990 ) was a British anæsthetist and Liberal Party politician .
Jesper Mattson Cruus af Edeby ( 1576 - -1622 ) was a Swedish soldier and politician , being appointed Privy Councilor in 1612 , Field Marshal in 1615 , Lord High Treasurer in 1615 , and Governor of Riga in 1621 .
Ahmet Turan Emeksiz ( b. 1940 - d. 28 April 1960 ) was a Turkish university student who was killed in 1960 street demonstrations .
Bhau Kalchuri ( January 13 , 1927 -- 23 October 2013 ) , born Vir Singh Kalchuri , was an Indian author , poet , trust administrator , and one of Meher Baba 's mandali ( close disciples ) .
Joseph E. Hollingsworth ( 1908 - -1975 ) , who went by Joe E. Hollingsworth , was appointed in 1961 to replace Charles Navarro as Los Angeles City Council member for the racially mixed 10th district .
Peter Helck ( 1893 - 1988 ) was an American illustrator who specialized in depicting racecars .
Edward Trollope ( 1817 - -1893 ) was an antiquary and an Anglican Bishop of Nottingham in the Victorian era .
Ezekiel , Freiherr von Spanheim ( also Ézéchiel , and known as Baron Spanheim ) ( 7 December 1629 -- 7 November 1710 ) was a Swiss diplomat and scholar .
Samuel Thomas Bloomfield ( 1790 -- 28 September 1869 ) was an English clergyman and Biblical textual critic .
Christopher Goodman BD ( 1520 - -1603 ) was an English reforming clergyman and writer .
Celestina Sommer ( 1 July 1827 -- 11 April 1859 ) was a Victorian murderess , notorious as much for her escape from the death penalty as for the murder of her only daughter .
Alfred John Jukes - Browne , FRS FGS ( 16 April 1851 - 14 August 1914 ) was a British invertebrate palaeontologist and stratigrapher .
Dou Yizhi ( 竇易直 ) ( died April 29 , 833 ) , courtesy name Zongxuan ( 宗玄 ) , formally Duke Gonghui of Jinyang ( 晉陽恭惠公 ) , was an official of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , serving as a chancellor during the reigns of Emperor Jingzong and Emperor Wenzong .
Jean Servais ( French : ( sɛʁvɛ ) ; 24 September 1910 -- 17 February 1976 ) was a Belgian film and stage actor .
Christopher Urswick ( 1448 ? -- 1522 ) was a priest and confessor of Margaret Beaufort .
Robert Munro , 1st Baron Alness GBE PC KC DL ( 28 May 1868 -- 6 October 1955 ) was a Scottish lawyer , judge and Liberal politician .
Donald MacInnes , born Donald McInnes , ( 26 May 1824 -- 1 December 1900 ) was a Canadian businessman and politician .
Frederick Royden Chalmers CMG , DSO ( 4 January 1881 -- 25 March 1943 ) was an Australian farmer , soldier , businessman , and government administrator .
Boris Smirnoff ( 1903 - 2007 ) was a Franco - Russian cubist , avant - gardist and analytical art painter .
Jyotiba Rao Scindia ( 1726 - January 1760 ) was the third son of Ranoji Rao Scindia and Maina Bai .
Sharon Tandy ( born Sharon Finkelstein ; 18 September 1943 -- 21 March 2015 ) was a South African singer who achieved some success in the United Kingdom in the 1960s as part of the blue - eyed soul and psychedelic movements .
Kurt Hutton , born Kurt Hübschmann ( 1893 - -1960 ) , was a German - born photographer who pioneered photojournalism in England .
Ross Tollerton VC ( 6 May 1890 -- 7 May 1931 ) born in Hurlford , Ayrshire , was a Scottish recipient of the Victoria Cross , the highest and most prestigious award for gallantry in the face of the enemy that can be awarded to British and Commonwealth forces .
Laurents Hallager ( 12 November 1777 -- 2 February 1825 ) was a Norwegian physician and lexicographer .
Demetrios Palaiologos or Demetrius Palaeologus ( Greek : Δημήτριος Παλαιολόγος , Dēmētrios Palaiologos ; ca . 1407 - -1470 ) was a Byzantine prince and Despot .
Mikhail Dmitriyevich Bonch - Bruyevich ( Russian : Михаи́л Дми́триевич Бонч-Бруе́вич ; 24 February ( O.S. 12 February ) 1870 -- 3 August 1956 ) was an Imperial Russian and Soviet military commander , Lieutenant General ( 1944 ) .
Ambrose Fernando ( 1912 -- 11 January 1999 ) was an Indian businessman and politician .
Louisa Lawrence ( 1803 - -1855 ) was an English horticulturist in the second quarter of the 19th century .
Daniel Higford Davall Burr JP DL ( 24 March 1811 -- 29 November 1885 ) was a British Member of Parliament and Justice of the Peace .
Solomon Molcho ( Hebrew : שלמה מולכו‎ Shelomo Molkho ) , or Molko , originally Diogo Pires , ( 1500 -- 13 December 1532 ) was a Portuguese mystic and pseudomessiah .
Mangsong Mangtsen ( Tibetan : མང་སྲོང་མང་བཙན ) , Trimang Löntsen or Khri - mang - slon - rtsan ( r. 650 - -676 CE ) succeeded to the throne after the death of his grandfather , Songtsän Gampo , and was the second emperor of the newly created Tibetan Empire .
William Graham , 7th Earl of Menteith , 1st Earl of Airth ( c.1591 - -1661 ) , was a 17th - century Scottish nobleman .
Michael Keogh , known as Max Keogh ( died April 2001 ) was a nationalist politician and journalist in Northern Ireland .
Thorvald Wilhelmsen ( 14 February 1912 -- 13 September 1996 ) was a Norwegian long - distance runner who specialized in the 10,000 metres .
Elizabeth Smith - Stanley , Countess of Derby ( née Hamilton ; 26 January 1753 -- 14 March 1797 ) was an English peeress .
Navaratna Rama Rao ( May 27 , 1877 -- 1960 ) was an Indian writer based in Mysore .
Charles Hickman ( 1648 -- 18 November 1713 ) , an Anglican divine in the Church of Ireland , was Bishop of Derry from 1703 to 1713 .
Ernest Kidd ( 25 May 1900 -- 1974 ) was a footballer who played in the Football League for Ashington and Wigan Borough .
Nashil Pichen Kazembe ( 1932 - -1991 ) was a Zambian singer from Luapula province ( close to the Congolese ( DRC ) border ) who became an African music star in the 1970s .
Aziz Ali al - Misri ( 1879 - -1965 ) was an Egyptian officer and politician .
Dr. Marguerite Rawalt ( 16 October 1895 -- 16 December 1989 ) was an American writer and lawyer who lobbied in Congress on behalf of women 's rights .
Harry Fainlight ( 1935 - -1982 ) was a British / American poet associated with the Beats movement .
Monroe Dunaway Anderson ( 1873 - -1939 ) was a banker and cotton trader from Jackson , Tennessee .
Lefteri ( ? -died 1872 ) was a 19th - century Greek bandit leader active in the area around the Ottoman capital Constantinople and the region of Bithynia .
Dr Charles Francis Potter ( 1885 - 1962 ) was an American Unitarian minister , theologian and author .
Claudia Testoni ( 19 December 1915 -- 17 July 1998 ) , was an Italian hurdler , sprinter and long jumper .
James Heane CB , CMG , DSO ( 29 December 1874 -- 20 August 1954 ) was an Australian Army colonel and temporary brigadier general in World War I. He retired in 1935 as a brigadier general .
Wolfgang Ludwig Krafft ( 25 August 1743 -- 20 November 1814 ) was a German astronomer and physicist .
Miró II of Cerdanya and I of Besalú ( 878?-927 ) , was count of Cerdanya from 897 to 927 and of Besalú from 920 to 927 .
Coombe Hall ( 1871 - -1932 ) was a Scottish footballer who played in the Football League for Blackburn Rovers .
Hieromartyr Clement , Bishop of Ancyra or simply Clement of Ancyra ( c. 258 - 312 ) ( born in Ancyra present - day Turkey ) was a bishop who served during the rule of Roman emperor Diocletian .
Catherine Winkworth ( 13 September 1827 -- 1 July 1878 ) was an English - language translator from London .
Mayor Manuel Egozcue Cintrón died shortly after in 1906 .
Henry Filmer ( died 1543 ) was a 16th - century English Protestant martyr , one of the Windsor Martyrs , during the reign of Henry VIII . Filmer was a Protestant tailor and church warden of St John 's Church at Windsor who complained about the overly Catholic sermons of the vicar .
Alice Stopford Green ( 30 May 1847 -- 28 May 1929 ) was an Irish historian and nationalist .
George Kinnaird , 1st Lord Kinnaird ( c. 1622 - -29 December 1689 ) was a 17th - century Scottish aristocrat .
Cathal mac Muiredaig Muillethan ( died 735 ) was a King of Connacht from the Uí Briúin branch of the Connachta .
Charles van der Stappen ( also Karl Van der Stappen ; 19 September 1843 -- 21 October 1910 ) , was a Belgian sculptor , born in Saint - Josse - ten - Noode .
Josef Nassy ( 1904 - -1976 ) was a black expatriate artist of Jewish descent .
Moses Soave was an Italian Hebraist ; born in Venice March 28 , 1820 ; died there November 27 , 1882 .
Arthur Raistrick ( 1896 - -1991 ) was a British geologist , archaeologist , academic , and writer .
Dr. John Herbert Claiborne ( March 16 , 1828 -- 1905 ) was a prominent Virginia politician and a leading medical administrator commanding a series of hospitals serving wounded Confederate soldiers during the American Civil War .
Glenn Canfield , Jr. ( September 20 , 1935 - -January 30 , 2006 ) was an American metallurgist and businessman .
Aldo Cláudio Felipe Bonadei , also known as Aldo Bonadei ( São Paulo June 17 , 1906 -- São Paulo , January 16 , 1974 ) was a Brazilian painter of Italian descent .
Fred Fontaine ( 15 July 1874 - 9 December 1957 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Fitzroy in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Rabindra Nath Upadhyay ( 1923 - -2010 ) was an Indian social worker , Gandhian and the founder of Tamulpur Anchalik Gramdan Sangha ( TAGS ) , a non governmental organization working for the social development of the rural people in the Kumarikata village of Assam .
Arcadius Avellanus , born Mogyoróssy Arkád ( 6 February 1851 -- 16 June 1935 ) , was a Hungarian American scholar of Latin and a proponent of Living Latin .
Henry Cort ( ? 1741 -- 23 May 1800 ) was an English ironmaster .
Sarah Kemp ( 1937 -- 9 January 2015 ) was an Australian actress best known for starring in the Australian soap opera Sons and Daughters , playing the highly popular character of socialite Charlie Bartlett , from 1982 to 1987 .
Dong Yuan ( Chinese : 董源 ; pinyin : Dŏng Yuán ; Wade -- Giles : Tung Yüan , Gan : dung3 ngion4 ; c. 934 -- c. 962 ) was a Chinese painter .
John Ewasew ( 13 March 1922 -- 26 March 1978 ) was a Canadian lawyer and senator .
Charles Boutell ( 1 August 1812 -- 31 July 1877 ) was an English archaeologist , antiquary and clergyman , publishing books on brasses , arms and armour and heraldry , often illustrated by his own drawings .
Martin E. Weaver ( 1938 - 2004 ) helped develop the scientific field of architectural conservation in the United States and internationally .
Magnus Nilssen ( 18 July 1871 -- 20 November 1947 ) was Norwegian politician for the Labour and Social Democratic Labour parties .
Moses Michael Hays ( 9 March 1739 -- 9 May 1805 ) was an American banker , merchant , and philanthropist .
Ethel Coleridge ( 14 January 1883 -- 15 August 1976 ) was an English actress , best known for her roles in the original Aldwych farces in the 1920s and 30s .
Max Alvarado ( 19 February 1929 -- 6 April 1997 ) was a FAMAS award - winning Filipino film actor known mainly by his portrayals of villains in a career which spanned six decades .
Franz Mozart ( 3 October 1649 -- 1693 or 1694 ) was a German mason and the grandfather of Leopold Mozart and great - grandfather of Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart .
Gilbert Beith ( 1827 -- 5 July 1904 ) was a Scottish merchant and Liberal politician .
Jean Cailleteau ( 1690 - -1755 ) , known as `` Lassurance '' ( or as `` Lassurance le jeune '' to distinguish him from his architect father Pierre Cailleteau ) , was a French architect .
Antoine Godin ( c. 1805 - 1836 ) , an Iroquois Canadian fur trapper and explorer , is noted primarily for the public murder of a Gros Ventre chief which led to a battle between fur traders and Indians in Pierre 's Hole , now called the Teton Basin , in eastern Idaho .
Harshavarman II ( Khmer : ហស៌វរ្ម័នទី២ ) was an Angkorian king who ruled from 941 to 944 .
Samuel Bowman ( May 21 , 1800 -- August 3 , 1861 ) was a suffragan Episcopal Bishop of Pennsylvania , United States .
K. Ananda Rau ( 21 September 1893 -- 22 January 1966 ) was an eminent Indian mathematician and a contemporary of Ramanujan .
Arthur James F. Bond RSMA , ( 1888 - -1958 ) was an English artist who worked in oils , watercolour and etching .
James Garbett ( 1802 - 1879 ) was a British academic and Anglican cleric who became the Archdeacon of Chichester .
Alter Tepliker was the sobriquet of Rabbi Moshe Yehoshua Bezhilianski ( d. 1919 ) , a learned scholar and leading Breslover Hasid in Uman , Ukraine in the late 19th and early 20th centuries .
Charles William Henry Kirchhoff ( born San Francisco , California , 28 March 1853 ; died Asbury Park , New Jersey , 22 July 1916 ) was a United States editor and steel expert .
A'jiniyaz Qosi'bay Uli ' ( Karakalpak : Әжинияз Қосыбай улы , A'jiniyaz Qosıbay ulı , Uzbek : Ажиниёз Қўсибой ўғли , Ajiniyoz Qoʻsiboy oʻgʻli ) ( 1824 - -1874 ) was a Karakalpak poet , who is also known by his pen name Ziywar .
James Kingsley ( 6 January 1797 -- 10 August 1878 ) was an attorney and mayor of Ann Arbor from 1855 - 1856 .
Dr John Rodney Cove - Smith ( born 26 January 1943 , London -- 3 February 2004 , Middlesbrough ) was the son of Ronald Cove - Smith , a distinguished English physician and captain of the English rugby team .
George Christopher Pepys Cutts ( 29 June 1914 -- 4 April 1974 ) was , from 1964 to 1974 , the fifth Bishop of Buckingham in the Church of England .
Oswell Blakeston was the pseudonym of Henry Joseph Hasslacher ( 1907 - -1985 ) , a British writer and artist who also worked in the film industry , made some experimental films , and wrote extensively on film theory .
The Reverend Augustus Shears ( 25 July 1827 - 25 May 1911 ) was the sixth and youngest son of Daniel Towers Shears ( 1784 - -1860 ) , a partner of James Shears and Sons , and Frances Spurrell ( 1788 - -1834 ) , daughter of John Spurrell of Bessingham , Norfolk .
Florian Siwicki ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈflɔrjan ɕiˈvit͡skʲi ) ; 10 January 1925 -- 11 March 2013 ) was a Polish career military officer , diplomat and a communist politician , as well as a General of the Polish Army .
Satyavati Devi ( 1904 - 1945 ) was a participant in Indian independence movement .
Fitz - John Winthrop ( 14 March 1637 -- 27 November 1707 ) , was the governor of the Colony of Connecticut from 1698 until his death on November 27 , 1707 .
Henry Givens Burgess PC(Ire ) ( 6 April 1859 -- 23 April 1937 ) was an Irish railway executive and politician .
Jean - Baptiste - Henri Féretier ( Nantes , 18 December 1765 - Nantes , 11 January 1832 ) was a French navy officer .
Willie McCartney ( date of birth unknown -- 24 January 1948 ) was a Scottish football referee and manager .
John Rouse ( Rous , Russe ) ( 1574 - -1652 ) was an English librarian , second librarian of the Bodleian in Oxford , and a friend of John Milton .
Joseph Hodkinson ( 1888 -- 18 June 1954 ) was an English international footballer who played as an outside left .
Gustav Schrader ( 1852 , Missolonghi , Greece -- 1942 Alexandria , Egypt ) was a German ornithologist .
Heinrich Leuthold ( 9 August 1827 - -1 July 1879 ) was a Swiss poet and translator , described by one critic as the writer `` most endowed with genius '' of the Munich literary circle , Die Krokodile .
Vera Ducas ( 1912 - -29 March 1948 ) was born to a Jewish family in Austria - Hungary / Czechoslovakia .
Sant Kavi Jagjivan Das ( or Jagiwan Das , 1727 Sardaha , Chas - 1761 ) is the founder of the Satnami denomination of Hinduism in Upper India .
Leonard Typpö ( 29 January 1868 , Rautio - 27 June 1922 ) was a Finnish farmer and lay preacher .
Sir John David Rees , 1st Baronet , KCIE , CVO , MP ( 16 December 1854 -- 2 June 1922 ) was a colonial administrator in British India and subsequently a Member of Parliament at Westminster .
Sorcha Ní Ghuairim ( 11 October 1911 -- 1976 ) was a teacher , writer , and sean - nós singer .
David Nunn Fisher ( 1816 - -1887 ) , was an English actor and musician usually known as David Fisher .
Charles Minor Blackford ( October 17 , 1833 -- 1903 ) was a Virginia lawyer and an author of American Civil War stories .
Louis John Tillett ( born 13 June 1865 , in Sprowston , Norfolk , died 24 November 1929 ) was a Liberal Party politician .
Denise Tolkowsky ( 11 August 1918 -- 9 March 1991 ) was an English - born pianist and composer .
Thomas Amarasuriya , OBE ( 17 June 1907 -- 5 May 1979 ) was a Ceylonese planter and politician .
Thomas E. Keane ( 1906 - 1996 ) was alderman of the 31st Ward of the City of Chicago .
Perry K. Smith , known as P. K. Smith ( September 21 , 1917 -- March 1983 ) , was a businessman from Winnfield , Louisiana , who served a single term in the Louisiana House of Representatives from 1960 to 1964 during the administration of Governor Jimmie Davis .
A. Laurence Lyon ( 1934 - -2006 ) was a prolific composer of music , usually sacred music with a Latter - day Saint theme .
