Sir George Clark Williams , 1st Baronet , QC ( born 1878 , died 1958 ) , was a Queen 's Counsel and Justice of the Peace .
Datu Patinggi Abang Haji Abdillah ( 13 October 1862 -- 21 November 1946 ) was Sarawak 's independence patriot .
Stephen Scandrett ( also Scandret or Scanderet ) ( 1631?--1706 ) was an English nonconformist minister and controversialist .
Ulrich Gering ( active as a printer in Paris from c. 1470 to 1508 ; died 23 August 1510 ) came from Beromünster in the diocese of Constance .
Charles Wells Moulton ( 1859 - -1913 ) was an American poet , critic , and editor .
Nanyang Huizhong ( simplified Chinese : 南阳慧忠 ; traditional Chinese : 南陽慧忠 ; pinyin : Nányáng Huìzhōng ; Japanese : Nanyō Echū ; Korean : Namyang Hyech'ung ; Vietnamese : Nam Dương Huệ Trung ; 675 - 775 CE ) was a Zen monk during the Tang Dynasty .
Salah - Hassan Hanifes ( Hebrew : סאלח - חסן ח'ניפס‎ , born 1 March 1913 , died 16 March 2002 ) was a Druze Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Progress and Work between 1951 and 1959 .
Ferdinand Maria , Elector of Bavaria ( 31 October 1636 -- 26 May 1679 ) was a Wittelsbach ruler of Bavaria and an elector ( Kurfürst ) of the Holy Roman Empire from 1651 to 1679 .
Georg Wolfgang Wedel ( 12 November 1645 -- 6 September 1721 ) was a German professor of surgery , botany , theoretical and practical medicine , and chemistry .
John Samuel Eastwood ( 1857 , Minnesota -- 1924 , California ) was an American engineer who built the world 's first reinforced concrete multiple - arch dam on bedrock foundation at Hume Lake , California , in 1908 .
Yujiulü Chounu ( Chinese : 郁久閭醜奴 ; pinyin : Yùjiǔlǘ Chǒunú ) ( ? -520 ) khan of the Rouran ( 508 - 520 ) with the title of Douluofubadoufa Khan ( 豆羅伏跋豆伐可汗 ) .
Harmen Steenwijck or Harmen Steenwyck ( c.1612 -- after 1656 ) was a Dutch Golden Age painter of still lifes , notably of fruit .
Robert Haswell ( November 24 , 1768 -- 1801 ? ) was an early American maritime fur trader to the Pacific Northwest of North America .
Felix Philipp Kanitz ( Bulgarian and Serbian Cyrillic : Феликс Филип Каниц , 2 August 1829 - 8 January 1904 ) was an Austro - Hungarian naturalist , geographer , ethnographer , archaeologist and author of travel notes .
Malik Joyeux ( 31 March 1980 -- 2 December 2005 ) was an accomplished all - around waterman and a professional Big Wave surfer .
Francis Adekunle Fajuyi , BEM ( 26 June 1926 -- 29 July 1966 ) was a Nigerian soldier of Yoruba origin .
James Calfhill ( also Calfield ) ( 1530?--1570 ) was an Anglican clergyman , academic and controversialist , who died as Archdeacon of Colchester and Bishop - designate of Worcester .
Saint Vukašin Mandrapa ( Serbian Cyrillic : Вукашин Мандрапа ) ( end of 19th century--1943 ) is a saint and a martyr of the Serbian Orthodox Church .
Richard Edes ( or Eedes ) ( 1555 - -1604 ) was an English churchman .
Thomas Hobson ( c. 1544 -- 1 January 1631 ) , was an English carrier , best known as the origin of the expression Hobson 's choice .
Edith Banfield Jackson ( 1895 - -1977 ) was a child psychiatrist who developed the rooming - in model of maternal and infant care .
Julio Nalundasan ( 1894 -- 20 September 1935 , Batac , Ilocos Norte ) was a Filipino politician who was one of the political rivals of Ilocos Norte politician Mariano Marcos , father of Ferdinand Marcos ( who later became the tenth President of the Philippines ) .
Nicholas Bullingham ( or Bollingham ) ( c. 1520 - -1576 ) was an English Bishop of Worcester .
Hill Blackett ( 13 March 1892 -- 6 December 1967 ) was a radio daytime - advertising pioneer who played a major part in the development of the soap opera .
George C. Lindsay ( 1855 - 1945 ) was an American composer and guitarist .
Richard Crawshay ( 1739 -- 27 June 1810 ) was a London iron merchant and then South Wales ironmaster .
Bernard Mizeki ( sometimes spelt Bernard Mzeki ; c. 1861 -- 18 June 1896 ) was an African Christian missionary and martyr .
Achille Falcone ( ca . 1570 - 75 -- 9 November 1600 ) was an Italian composer .
John Hunyadi ( , ; 1406 -- 11 August 1456 ) was a leading Hungarian military and political figure in Central and Southeastern Europe during the 15th century .
William Hannibal Thomas ( 4 May 1843 -- 15 November 1935 ) was an American teacher , journalist , judge , writer and legislator .
José Manuel Ramírez Rosales , ( 1804 , Santiago - 1877 , Valparaíso ) was a Chilean painter who was educated in France .
Khalmurad Sakhatmuradov ( 1898 - -1938 ) served as the second President of the Turkmen SSR , serving from 1925 until August 1928 .
Old Tassel ( or sometimes Corntassel ) ( Cherokee language : Utsi'dsata ) , ( died 1788 ) , was `` First Beloved Man '' ( the equivalent of a regional Cherokee chief ) of the Overhill Cherokee after 1783 .
Jacques Specx ( Dutch : ( ˈʒɑk ˈspɛks ) ; 1585 -- 22 July 1652 ) was a Dutch merchant , who founded the trade on Japan and Korea in 1609 .
Gheorghe Tătaru , ( 5 May 1948 in Bucharest -- 19 December 2004 in Iaşi ) , also known as Tătaru II , was a Romanian football striker , a player of Steaua Bucureşti .
Major - general Sir John Malcolm GCB , KLS ( 2 May 1769 -- 30 May 1833 ) was a Scottish soldier , diplomat , East India Company administrator , statesman , and historian .
William Molyneux , 7th Viscount Molyneux ( 1685 -- 30 March 1759 ) was a Jesuit priest and member of the peerage of Ireland .
Peter Olrog Schjøtt ( 29 July 1833 -- 7 January 1926 ) was a Norwegian philologist and politician .
Emilio J. Pasarell ( 1891 - -1974 ) was a Puerto Rican short - story writer , novelist , essayist and historian .
James Boon Lankershim ( 1850 - -1931 ) was an American heir , landowner and real estate developer .
Constantius I ( Latin : Marcus Flavius Valerius Constantius Herculius Augustus ; 31 March c. 250 -- 25 July 306 ) was Roman Emperor from 293 to 306 , commonly known as Constantius Chlorus ( Greek : Κωνστάντιος Χλωρός , Kōnstantios Khlōrós , lit . `` Constantius the Pale '' ) .
Valentine Bartholomew ( 18 January 1799 -- 21 March 1879 ) was an English flower painter .
Captain Spier Spencer ( c. 1770 -- November 7 , 1811 ) was an Indiana militia officer who commanded a company of mounted riflemen known as the Yellow Jackets at the Battle of Tippecanoe .
Károly Bebo ( c. 1712 -- April 1779 ) was an 18th - century Hungarian sculptor , builder and decorator noted for his stucco work .
Jo Ann Kelly ( 5 January 1944 -- 21 October 1990 ) was an English blues singer and guitarist .
Queenie Watts ( 21 July 1926 -- 25 January 1980 ) was an English actress of film and television , as well as an occasional singer .
Stephen Winthrop ( born 20 December 1806 , Tonbridge , Kent ; died 25 August 1835 , England ) was an English cricketer who was associated with Cambridge University Cricket Club and made his first - class debut in 1829 .
Ralph Boteler , 1st Baron Sudeley and 6th Baron Sudeley KG ( c. 1394 -- 2 May 1473 ) was an English baron and aristocrat .
Karl Albrecht Gottlieb Ringier ( 8 December 1837 - 7 January 1929 ) was a Swiss politician , President of the Swiss Council of States ( 1875 ) and Federal Chancellor ( 1882 - -1909 ) .
Emelia Russell Gurney ( 1823 - -1896 ) was an English activist , patron and benefactor .
Jonathan Joy ( 29 December 1826 -- 27 September 1889 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played for Yorkshire , both as a pre - county club , and for Yorkshire County Cricket Club , in first - class cricket after the foundation of the County Championship .
Wally Colliss ( 22 May 1908 -- 8 October 1977 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Camillo Pabis Ticci ( 1920 - -2003 ) was an Italian bridge player .
Jorma Karhunen ( 17 March 1913 -- 21 January 2002 ) was a Finnish Air Force ace .
General Thomas Edward Capel ( 24 March 1770 -- 3 February 1855 ) was an English soldier and sportsman .
Burton A. Scott ( February 16 , 1935 -- April 2 , 2007 ) was Chief Judge of the Wisconsin Court of Appeals .
Ruth Pryor ( 1906 - 2001 ) was a Chicago ballet dancer and instructor , and the first American ballerina to dance the role of the Swan Queen in Swan Lake , in 1930 .
Ádám Jávorka ( Nagykosztolány , Hungarian Kingdom , 1683 -- Jasło Poland , 19 August 1747 ) was a Hungarian soldier who was a captain of Kuruc forces during the Rákóczi 's War for Independence , later became a French Hussar , and later on Captain of the Polish Army .
Adolf II , Prince of Schaumburg - Lippe ( 23 February 1883 -- 26 March 1936 ) was the last ruler of the small Principality of Schaumburg - Lippe .
John Etherington Welch Rolls ( 4 May 1807 -- 27 May 1870 ) was a High Sheriff of Monmouthshire , art collector , Deputy Lieutenant and Justice of the Peace .
John W. Anson ( 31 July 1817 -- 6 February 1881 ) was a British actor , noted for his work for the welfare of actors .
Paddy Cardiff ( 8 November 1925 -- 3 June 2005 ) was an Irish trade unionist .
Brynjulf Skaugen , Sr . ( 11 June 1918 -- 14 August 2002 ) was a Norwegian business executive .
Langford Lovell Price ( 1862 - 1950 ) was an English economist , born in London .
Sir James Bond , 1st Baronet ( 11 June 1744 -- 2 June 1820 ) was an Irish Member of Parliament of Anglo - Irish descent .
William Craven , 2nd Earl of Craven DL ( 18 August 1809 -- 25 August 1866 ) , styled Viscount Uffington until 1825 , was a British peer .
Stanisław Sedlaczek ( 31 January 1892 -- 3 August 1941 ) , born in Kołomyja , in what is now Ukraine , was a Polish professor and scoutmaster .
Sir Henry de Vic , 1st Baronet ( c. 1599 -- 20 November 1671 ) was a Guernsey born courtier .
John Thrasher ( February 24 , 1818 - -November 13 , 1899 ) was the founder of the city of Norcross , Georgia , an original pioneer of Atlanta , and a well - travelled entrepreneur throughout the American Southeast .
Odd Dahl ( 3 November 1898 -- 2 June 1994 ) was a Norwegian engineer and explorer .
Leo Gburek ( born 18 April 1910 in Bismarckhütte ; died 17 January 1941 in Shetland ) was a German geophysicist and a member of the Third German Antarctic Expedition 1938/39 .
Andrew Ketcham Barnett ( 1852 -- 1914 ) was a mineral collector and dealer in Penzance , Cornwall , in the United Kingdom .
Franz von Suppé or Francesco Suppé Demelli ( 18 April 1819 -- 21 May 1895 ) was an Austrian composer of light operas from the Kingdom of Dalmatia , Austro - Hungarian Empire ( now part of Croatia ) .
James J. Nance ( February 19 , 1900 -- July 1984 ) was an American industrialist who became president of Studebaker Packard .
George Muff , 1st Baron Calverley ( 10 February 1877 -- 20 September 1955 ) was a British Liberal then Labour politician .
Michel Auguste Dupoty ( 1797 - -1864 ) was a French journalist and a politician with republican beliefs .
Thakin Chit Maung ( Burmese : ချစ်မောင် ; 1915 -- 3 March 2005 ) , also known as Widuya Thakin Chit Maung , was a veteran Burmese politician .
Fritz Gassmann ( 1899 - -1990 ) was a Swiss mathematician and geophysicist .
Sir Walter Blake , ( bef . 1672 - -May 1748 ) , 6th Bt . , was a minor Irish aristocrat and politician from County Galway .
John Kettlewell ( 1653 - -1695 ) was an English clergyman , nonjuror and devotional writer .
John Bond Trevor ( 1822 -- 1890 ) was an American financier and Wall Street pioneer .
William Armstrong Fairburn ( 12 October 1876 - 1 October 1947 ) was a noted American author , naval architect , marine engineer , industrial executive , and chemist .
Chaudhari Kumbharam Arya ( 10 May 1914 -- 26 October 1995 ) was a freedom fighter , parliamentarian and popular leader of farmers in Rajasthan , India . Shri Kumbha Ram Arya was a member of Seventh Lok Sabha during 1980 - 84 representing Sikar Parliamentary constituency of Rajasthan .
Gabriel Donne or Dunne ( died 1558 ) was an English Cistercian monk and was the last Abbot of Buckfast Abbey in Devon , before the Dissolution of the Monasteries .
Jørgen Iversen Dyppel ( February 25 , 1638 -- 1683 ) , also called George Iversen or Ifversen , or sometimes Doppel in Knox , was the first governor of the renewed establishment of St. Thomas in the Danish West Indies , from 1672 to 1680 .
Constantius ( Latin : Flavius Constantius Augustus ) ( died 2 September 421 ) , commonly known as Constantius III , was Western Roman Emperor for seven months in 421 .
Alessandro Pinheiro Martins ( 1983 -- December 6 , 2005 ) , nicknamed `` Alessandro '' , was a Brazilian football ( soccer ) player .
Joseph Moses Levy ( 15 December 1812 in London - 12 October 1888 in Ramsgate , Kent ) was a newspaper editor and publisher .
Richard Battley ( 1770 - -1856 ) , was an English chemist .
Alexander Dowie ( 4 September 1827 -- 18 July 1909 ) was a footwear manufacturer and retailer in the early days of South Australia .
Ziaeddin Tavakkoli Bivarzeni ( 1925 - -2009 ) , was a Northern Iranian politician and merchant .
Arthur Langen ( born 13 January 1858 in Berlin ; died 25 October 1927 in Solingen ) was a German magistrate with the Berlin Government and privately active in the theater industry .
Thomas Luraas ( 1799 - -6 June 1886 ) was a Norwegian rose painter and clarinetist .
Major Thomas Beckford ( d. 1685 ) was a London clothworker and slopseller who became Sheriff of London .
Dietrich of Horne ( b. in Horneburg ( Westendorf ) -- d. 19 January 1402 in Osnabrück ) was a German nobleman .
Maciej Grabowski ( died 1750 ) was a Polish - Lithuanian nobleman and politician , Treasurer of the Crown Court from 1738 .
Edgar Powell ( 6 January 1899 -- 1955 ) was a Welsh footballer who played in the Football League for Accrington Stanley , Barrow , Merthyr Town and Stoke .
John James Cole ( died 24 May 1959 ) was an Irish politician , farmer and auctioneer .
Francesco Croce ( 1696 - 1773 ) was an Italian baroque architect .
Robert Byron Boyd ( August 31 , 1864 -- 1941 ) was an American politician and businessperson from Maine .
Miles Balmford Sharp ( 1897 - -1973 ) was an artist , born in Brighouse , Yorkshire , England .
John I Sanudo ( or Giovanni ; died 1362 ) was the sixth Duke of the Archipelago from 1341 to his death .
Richard James Strachan Harman ( 14 April 1826 -- 26 November 1902 ) was trained as a civil engineer .

John Bargrave ( 1610 - -1680 ) , was an English author and collector and a canon of Canterbury Cathedral .
Peter Pierse ( died 4 September 1991 ) was an Australian rugby league referee .
Philip Maxwell ( April 3 , 1799 - November 5 , 1859 ) was an American physician and politician .
Claude de Sainctes ( b. at Perche , 1525 ; d. at Crèvecoeur , 1591 ) was a French Catholic controversialist .
Miguel Salinas Arteche ( 4 June 1926 -- 22 July 2012 ) , best known as Miguel Arteche , the name he adopted after legally reversing his maternal and paternal surnames in 1972 , was a Chilean poet and novelist .
Attilio Teruzzi ( 5 May 1882 -- 26 April 1950 ) was an Italian soldier , colonial administrator , and Fascist politician .
Prynce Hopkins ( March 5 , 1885 - August 1970 ) , who was born Prince Charles Hopkins , was an American Socialist , pacifist and author of numerous psychology books and periodicals .
Milko Brezigar ( 6 October 1886 -- 25 April 1958 ) was a Slovene and Yugoslav liberal economist .
Cú Ceanain mac Tadhg , Prince of Uí Díarmata , ancestor of the Concannon family , died 991
Alessandro Mantovani ( 1814 -- 1892 ) was an Italian painter , best known for his decorative frescoes and restorations .
Lynne Carter ( ca.1924 -- January 11 , 1985 ) was a prominent entertainer , actor , and female impersonator .
Thomas Foxcroft ( 1697 - -1769 ) was a minister of the First Church in Boston , Massachusetts in the 18th century .
Carson Brewer ( February 2 , 1920 -- January 15 , 2003 ) was an American journalist and conservationist , best known for his work documenting the folk life of Knoxville and the surrounding Appalachian communities in East Tennessee .
Ernest William Lyons Holt or E.W.L. Holt ( 17 October 1864 -- 10 June 1922 ) was an eminent English marine naturalist and biologist who specialized in ichthyology , the study of fish .
Nicolae Minovici ( 23 October 1868 -- 26 June 1941 ) was a Romanian forensic scientist and criminologist who served as head of his country 's anthropometric service .
Carlo Pezzati ( October 28 , 1892 - -1944 ) was an Italian politician , the mayor of the Italian city of Piacenza .
Oluf Braren ( 25 February 1787 -- 22 March 1839 ) was a painter of naïve art from the north Frisian island of Föhr .
William McKenzie Thomson MC , DFC ( 15 September 1898 -- 9 July 1987 ) was a Canadian First World War flying ace , officially credited with 26 victories .
Giaches de Wert ( also Jacques / Jaches de Wert , Giaches de Vuert ; 1535 -- 6 May 1596 ) was a Franco - Flemish composer of the late Renaissance , active in Italy .
Zhou Lianggong ( Chinese : 周亮工 ; Wade -- Giles : Chou Liang - kung , 1612 - -1672 ) was a Chinese poet , born in Kaifeng was an essayist and art historian , and had long family ties to Nanjing .
Mas Tirtodarmo Haryono ( 20 January 1924 -- 1 October 1965 ) was a general officer in the Indonesian Army who was killed during an attempt to kidnap him from his home by members of the 30 September Movement in the early hours of October 1 , 1965 .
Margaret Gillies ( 1803 - -1887 ) was a Scottish painter , known for miniatures and water - colours .
R. P. Sethu Pillai ( Tamil : ரா. பி. சேது பிள்ளை ) ( 1896 - -1961 ) , was a Tamil scholar , writer and professor of Tamil at the University of Madras .
Frederikke Louise Stolberg ( 1746 - -1824 ) , was a Danish Salonist , playwright and letter writer .
Robert Morgan Fink ( 1915 - 2012 ) was an American biochemist who was a professor at University of California , Los Angeles .
Hugh Fortescue , 2nd Earl Fortescue KG , PC ( 13 February 1783 -- 14 September 1861 ) , styled Viscount Ebrington from 1789 to 1841 , was a British Whig politician .
R. Narayanaswami ( 1919 - 1992 ) , popularly known by his pen name Karichan Kunju , was a Tamil short - story writer and novelist who wrote mainly on historical themes .
Samer Saadi ( died 29 September 2005 ) was a leading figure in the Al - Aqsa Martyrs ' Brigades in Jenin .
Chauncey Loomis ( ca . 1783 -- April 6 , 1817 Albany , New York ) was an American politician from New York .
Rupert D'Oyly Carte ( 3 November 1876 -- 12 September 1948 ) was an English hotelier , theatre owner and impresario , best known as proprietor of the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company and Savoy Hotel from 1913 to 1948 .
King Andriamasinavalona ( 1675 - -1710 ) , also known as Andrianjakanavalondambo , was a King of Imerina in the central highlands of Madagascar .
Lydia Sellon or Priscilla Lydia Sellon ( 1821 -- 20 November 1876 ) was a British founder of an Anglican women 's order .
Dr Jimione Samisoni died on April 2007 .
Ivan Ratkaj ( 22 June 1647 -- 26 December 1683 ) , also Ivan Rattkay , was a Croatian Jesuit missionary and explorer .
Saint Lazarus Zographos(died 867 ) was a monk and painter from Constantinople who opposed the religious policy of iconoclasm during the reign of Byzantine Emperor Theophilus .
George Shima ( 1864 - -1926 ) was a Japanese American businessman in California who became the first Japanese American millionaire .
Aage Samuelsen ( 23 January 1915 -- 29 November 1987 ) was a Norwegian evangelist , singer and composer .
Captain Charles Fitzgerald ( 1791 - - 29 December 1887 ) was the Governor of The Gambia from 1844 until 1847 , then Governor of Western Australia from 1848 to 1855 .
Alexandre Miniac ( 5 July 1885 -- 3 December 1963 ) was a French architect and watercolorist .
Lorenzo Sansone ( 1881 - -1975 ) was a horn player , a member of major North American symphony orchestras , an editor of horn music , an author of instructional methods , an educator , and a horn manufacturer .
Parara Napaltjarri ( c. 1944 - -2003 ) was a Pintupi - speaking Indigenous artist from Australia 's Western Desert region .
Maredudd ab Owain ab Edwin ( died 1072 ) was a prince of the kingdom of Deheubarth in south west Wales .
Hans Tank ( 10 August 1742 -- 17 March 1804 ) was a Norwegian skipper , merchant and endowment founder , born in Bergen .
Frank Keppel ( 8 December 1899 -- 4 February 1975 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Mustafa Shalabi was a founder of several charities alleged to have links to terrorism who was found murdered on February 25 , 1991 .
Esmat Dowlatshahi ( 1904 -- 24 July 1995 ) was an Iranian aristocrat and the fourth and last spouse of Reza Shah .
Lars - Jacob Krogh ( 26 September 1938 -- 14 April 2010 ) was a Norwegian anchorman and television presenter .
Thomas Joseph Gerard Victory ( 24 December 1921 -- 14 March 1995 ) was a prolific Irish composer .
Ralph Josselin ( January 23 , 1617 -- 1683 ) was the vicar of Earls Colne in Essex from 1640 until his death in 1683 .
Enríquez de Valderrábano ( c. 1500-after 1557 ) was a Spanish vihuelist and composer .
Daniel Bellamy , the younger ( c. 1715- 16 February 1788 ) was an English divine and miscellaneous writer .
Éric Remacle ( Forest , Brussels , 1960 - 22 May 2013 ) was a Belgian scientist and professor at the Department of Political Sciences of the Universite Libre de Bruxelles ( ULB ) .
Louis the Pious ( 778 -- 20 June 840 ) , also called the Fair , and the Debonaire , was the King of Aquitaine from 781 .
Olivier Charbonneau ( France , Aunis c. 1613 Île de Montréal 20 November 1687 ) was a frontiersman who lived in Old Montreal in New France .
Ramón Marrero Aristy Beltré ( 13 July 1913 -- 17 July 1959 ) was a Dominican author , journalist and politician and historian .
Clark Rampling ( 1793 -- 7 March 1875 ) was an English architect who worked from offices in London .
Cecil Edgar Tilley FRS ( 14 May 1894 -- 24 January 1973 ) was an Australian - British petrologist and geologist .
Jane Arbor was the pseudonym used by Eileen Norah Owbridge ( 8 September 1903 -- 4 February 1994 ) a British writer of 57 romance for Mills & Boon from 1948 to 1985 .
Ivan Ladislav Galeta ( 9 May 1947 -- 7 January 2014 ) was a Croatian multimedia artist , cinematographer and film director .
Badi ' al - Zaman Mirza ( Persian : بدیع الزمان‎ ; died 1517 ) was a Timurid ruler of Herat from 1506 to 1507 .
Tristão Vaz Teixeira ( c. 1395 - -1480 ) was a Portuguese navigator and explorer who , together with João Gonçalves Zarco and Bartolomeu Perestrelo , was the official discoverer and one of the first settlers of the archipelago of Madeira ( 1419 - -1420 ) .
Mark Muir Mills ( August 8 , 1917 - -April 7 , 1958 ) was an American nuclear physicist and a developer of atomic bombs .
Alain Polaniok ( 19 September 1958 -- 12 September 2005 ) was a French footballer .
George Kellogg ( June 19 , 1812 -- 1901 ) was an American inventor and patent expert .
Sir John Stokell Dodds , KCMG , ( 1848 -- 23 June 1914 ) was an Australian politician and Chief Justice of Tasmania .
Eliza Salmon ( 1787 -- 1849 ) was an English vocalist .
Richard Rooke Michell ( 31 December 1810 in Marazion , Cornwall - 15 April 1872 in Wimpole Street , London ) was an English mines proprietor .
Robert Jacobus Forbes or Robert James Forbes ( 21 April 1900 , Breda -- 13 January 1973 , Haarlem ) was a Dutch chemist and historian of science .
Hugh Barron ( c. 1746 - 1791 ) was an English portrait painter and amateur musician .
Jules Horrent ( 11 April 1920 - 11 September 1981 ) was a Belgian scientist , who was awarded the Francqui Prize in 1968 on Human Sciences for his historical work
Yu Qin ( Chinese : 于钦 , 1284 - -1333 ) was a well - known Chinese geographer living in the Mongol Yuan Dynasty .
Mohamed Sedky Mahmoud ( Arabic : محمد صدقي محمود‎ , December 12 , 1914 - 1984 ) is an Egyptian military leader .
Sir Thomas de Littleton or de Lyttleton ( c.1407 -- 23 August 1481 ) was an English judge and legal writer from the Lyttelton family .
Johannes Cuspinianus ( December 1473 -- 19 April 1529 ) , born Johan Spießhaymer ( or Speißheimer ) , was an Austrian humanist , scientist , diplomat , and historian .
Mimi Chakib ( 1913 -- 1983 ) ( Arabic : ميمي شكيب‎ ) was an Egyptian actress who appeared in some 15 films mostly in the 1940s and 1950s .
George Bigg ( 24 July 1861 -- 27 October 1931 ) was an English cricketer who played for Lancashire .
Henri Robin ( 1811 - -1874 ) , born Henrik Joseph Donckel , was a Dutch illusionist .
Henry of Niemodlin ( Polish : Henryk Niemodliński ; after 1345 -- 14 September 1382 ) , was a Duke of Niemodlin since 1365 until his death ( with his brothers as co - rulers until 1369 ) .
General Fritz Lindemann ( 11 April 1894 -- 22 September 1944 ) was a German Artillery officer and member of the resistance to Adolf Hitler .
William Francis Casey ( 2 May 1884 -- 20 April 1957 ) was a journalist and newspaper editor , notably spending most of his working life employed by British newspaper , The Times .
Janet Blunt ( 1859 - -1950 ) was a folklorist .
Franz Schmitz ( 12 October 1918 -- 10 June 1985 ) was a highly decorated German Sanitäts - Unteroffizier in the Wehrmacht during World War II and an Oberstabsfeldwebel in the Bundeswehr .
Colin Milburn ( nicknamed Ollie ; 23 October 1941 -- 28 February 1990 ) was an English cricketer , who played in nine Test matches for England , before an accident led to the loss of much of his sight and prompted his retirement .
Richard Harry Graves ( 17 July 1897 -- 3 February 1971 ) was an Irish - born Australian poet and novelist .
Edward Western ( 12 May 1845 -- 16 October 1919 ) was an English cricketer who played first - class cricket for Somerset in 1882 and 1884 and for Marylebone Cricket Club in 1882 .
Charles Ernest Tatham ( 1905 -- 14 August 1997 ) was a Canadian theologian and missionary .
Friedrich Staphylus ( 27 August 1512 -- 5 March 1564 ) was a German theologian , at first a Protestant and then a Catholic convert .
Isobel of Huntingdon ( 1199 - -1251 ) , also known as Isobel the Scot , was the daughter of David of Scotland , 8th Earl of Huntingdon , grandson of David I of Scotland , and Matilda of Chester .
Charles Gottlieb Raue or Charles Gottlieb Raue or Charles Godlove Raue ( 11 May 1820 -- 6 August 1896 ) was a United States homeopathic physician .
Henri Dreyfus ( or Henry Dreyfus , 1882 - -1944 ) was a Swiss chemist .
John Duncan Forsyth ( 1886 or 1887 - -1963 ) was a Scottish - American architect who became prominent in Oklahoma .
Shah Niyaz Ahmad was born on 6th Jumada al - Thani 1155 Hijri ( 7 August 1742 ) and died on 6th Jumada al - Thani 1250 Hijri ( 9 October 1834 ) .
Thomas Bedingfeld ( born 1760 died 1789 ) , poet , second son of Edward Bedingfeld , Esquire , of York , and Mary , daughter of Sir John Swinburne , of Capheaton , Northumberland , was born at York on 18 February 1760 , and educated at the University of Liége .
Buster Pearson ( 4 May 1941 - 14 October 2012 ) , born Stedman Pearson in Jamaica , was a musician and producer , best known for being the father and former manager of British pop group Five Star .
Cormac Mac Carthaig ( died 1138 ) was King of Munster .
Giovacchino Cantini ( c. 1780 - 1844 ) was an Italian engraver , active in Florence as one of Raffaello Sanzio Morghen 's most successful pupils .
Nicholas of Capraia ( died 1274 ) was the Judge of Arborea from 1264 to his assassination ten years later .
Bernard Middleditch ( 1870 -- 3 October 1949 ) was an English international footballer , who played as a right half .
Captain Cornelius Mitchell ( died 1749 ) was a Royal Navy officer who served as Commander - in - Chief of the Jamaica Station .
Gordon Burleigh ( 24 March 1889 -- 7 July 1956 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played for Geelong in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) now known as the Australian Football League ( AFL ) .
Constantine Meliteniotes ( Greek : Κωνσταντῖνος Μελιτηνιώτης , fl . 1240s -- 2 April 1307 ) was a Greek ecclesiastical writer in the Byzantine Empire and a prominent supporter of the Union of Lyons between the Greek Orthodox Church and the Roman Catholic Church .
Lin Chieh - liang ( Chinese : 林杰樑 , 30 June 1958 -- 5 August 2013 ) was a Taiwanese physician , nephrologist and toxicologist .
Furia Sabinia Tranquillina ( ca . 225 -- aft . 244 ) was the Empress of Rome and wife of Emperor Gordian III . She was the young daughter of the Praetorian Prefect Timesitheus by an unknown wife .
Vin Batchelor ( 17 February 1900 -- 4 September 1981 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Urho Kähönen ( 6 July 1910 , Terijoki - 3 August 1984 ) was a Finnish agronomist , civil servant and politician .
William Mansfield Poole ( 6 April 1871 -- 13 December 1946 ) was an educationalist and author of several widely held academic text books .
Greta Hopkinson ( born Greta Karin Louise Stromeyer , 4 October 1901 - September 1993 ) was a British wood sculptor .
John Brodribb Bergne ( 1800 - -1873 ) was an English official , numismatist and antiquary .
Catherine Zaccaria or Catherine Palaiologina ( Greek : Αἰκατερίνα Παλαιολογίνα ; died 26 August 1462 ) was the daughter of the last Prince of Achaea , Centurione II Zaccaria .
Abraham Solomon ben Isaac ben Samuel Catalan ( born in Catalonia ; died 1492 ) was the author of a work treating the eternity of the world , Providence , prophecy , immortality , and the resurrection , and also dealing with mathematical , physical , and cabalistic subjects .
John Dampier ( 1750 -- 18 August 1826 ) was an English amateur cricketer who made three appearances in first - class cricket matches from 1785 to 1787 .
Øyvind Bjørnson ( 1 January 1950 -- 3 December 2007 ) was a Norwegian historian who specialized in labor history and the history of the welfare state .
Jerzy Matałowski ( 1 February 1948 -- 1 December 2013 ) was a German - born Polish film , stage and television actor .
Claude Charles ( 1661 - -1747 ) was a French historical and decorative painter .
Skip Weshner ( 1927 -- 1995 ) was a disc jockey on stations in New York and Los Angeles from the mid-1950s until the mid-1980s .
Viktor Puskar VR I/1 ( 7 May ( O.S. 25 April ) 1889 in Viljandi - 12 April 1943 in Tartu ) was an Estonian military commander ( Colonel ) during the Estonian War of Independence .
Ethel Muckelt ( 30 May 1885 -- 13 December 1953 ) , was a British figure skater who competed in singles and pairs .
John J. Graham ( September 25 , 1923 - -June 12 , 1994 ) was an American graphic artist who designed and created both the NBC peacock logo ( 1956 ) and the NBC `` snake '' logo ( 1959 ) .
Sir De Villiers Graaff , 2nd Baronet ( 8 December 1913 -- 4 October 1999 ) ( first name De Villiers , surname Graaff ) known as Div Graaff , was a South African politician who succeeded his father , Sir David Pieter de Villiers Graaff , 1st Baronet , to his baronetcy in 1931 .
Rajendra Mullick ( Bengali : রাজেন্দ্র মল্লিক ) ( 24 June 1819 - 1887 ) was an Indian art lover and philanthropist .
John F. West , ( 1920 - 2001 ) , was an environmental activist in Marin County , California .
Johnny Hunter ( 21 July 1925 - -1980 ) was an Australian rugby league footballer of the 1940s and ' 50s .

Amin ud - din Ahmad Khan ( 23 March 1911 -- 12 June 1983 ) was the last Nawab of princely state of Loharu , ruling from 1926 to 1947 .
Étienne Heudelet de Bierre ( 12 November 1770 -- 20 April 1857 ) joined the French army as a volunteer lieutenant in 1792 .
Li Huaiguang ( Chinese : 李懷光 ; 729 -- September 19 , 785 ) was a leading general of the Chinese dynasty Tang Dynasty , of Mohe extraction .
Subodh Oraon ( 1953 - 5 December 1988 ) , also written Subodh Barwa , was an Indian politician belonging to the Revolutionary Socialist Party ( RSP ) .

William Paston , 2nd Earl of Yarmouth ( 1654 -- 25 December 1732 ) was a British peer and politician .
Maurice Lefèvre ( 1863 - 1917 ) was a Belgian poet , playwright and songwriter .
Fannie Pearson Hardy Eckstorm ( 1865 - -1946 ) was an American writer , ornithologist and folklorist .
Erwin Ding - Schuler was arrested by U.S. troops on 25 April 1945 and committed suicide on 11 August 1945 .
Jean Lepage ( 1779 - -1822 ) was a well - known French gunsmith .
Sir John Thomas Briggs ( 4 June 1781 - 3 February 1865 ) , was accountant - general of the Royal Navy .
John Herbert Cooke ( 3 August 1867 -- 30 July 1943 ) was an Australian politician , invariably referred to as `` J. Herbert Cooke '' or `` J. H. Cooke '' .
Sir Henry Brooke , 1st Baronet ( died 1664 ) was an English soldier and politician .
Lois Tobío Fernández ( Viveiro , 13 June 1906 - Madrid , 13 March 2003 ) was a Galician diplomat , writer , translator and philologist .
Edward Stiles Stokes ( 1840 - -1901 ) was the owner of a New York oil refinery who in 1872 shot and killed his business partner and love rival James Fisk .
Maria de Lourdes Teixeira ( 25 March 1907 -- 1989 ) was a Brazilian writer , translator , biographer and journalist best known for having received the Prize Jabuti of Literature for Best Novel in 1961 and 1970 by Rua Augusta and Pátio das Donzelas respectively .
Ernest Newman ( 30 November 1868 -- 7 July 1959 ) was an English music critic and musicologist .
Paul Huillard ( 15 February 1875 -- 11 February 1966 ) was a French designer and architect who collaborated on many projects with Louis Süe .
John Mordaunt , 1st Baron Mordaunt ( died 18 August 1562 ) was an English politician and peer .
Nils Robert af Ursin ( 18 April 1854 , Kuopio - 8 May 1936 ) was a Finnish secondary school teacher and politician .
George Child Villiers , 5th Earl of Jersey GCH , PC ( 19 August 1773 -- 3 October 1859 ) , styled Viscount Villiers until 1805 , was a British courtier and Conservative politician from the Villiers family .
Antti Valkama ( 31 July 1889 -- 26 July 1974 ) was a Finnish sports shooter .
Alexander Salkind ( 2 June 1921 -- 8 March 1997 ) was the second of three generations of successful international film producers .
Gregory the Patrician ( Greek : Γρηγόριος , Latin : Flavius Gregorius , died 647 ) was a Byzantine Exarch of Africa ( modern Tunisia and eastern Algeria ) .

Augustus Russell Street ( 5 November 1792 - 12 June 1866 ) was a philanthropist who made significant donations to Yale University .

Camilla Faà di Bruno , also da Casale , also Camilla Faà Gonzaga ( c. 1599 -- 14 July 1662 ) was an Italian noblewoman who was married secretly , briefly and morganatically to Ferdinando the Gonzaga Duke of Mantua and Duke of Montferrat .
Amund Rydland ( 25 November 1888 - 16 February 1967 ) was a Norwegian stage and film actor and theatre director .
Gino Meneghetti ( Italian pronunciation : ( ˈdʒino meneˈɡetti ) ; 1 July 1878 - 23 May 1976 ) was an Italian thief who spent much of his criminal career in Brazil .
Gustav Mevissen , after 1884 known as Gustav von Mevissen , ( 20 May 1815 -- 13 August 1899 ) , was a German businessman and politician .
Wernher von Homberg ( also Werner ; Hohenberg , 1284 -- 21 March 1320 ) was a knight in the service Emperor Henry VII , and later of Frederick the Fair .
Edwin Field ( 16 December 1871 -- 9 January 1947 ) was an English rugby union forward who played club rugby for Cambridge University , Clifton R.F.C. , Richmond , Barbarians and Middlesex Wanderers and international rugby for England .
Johan Lorensen ( also John Lorentz ) ( died 1702 ) was a lieutenant and interim Governor - General of The Danish West Indies during two short periods , respectively October , 1689 to September 17 , 1692 and from April 7 , 1693 to February 19 , 1702 .
Hugh Hare , 1st Baron Coleraine ( 1606 -- 19 October 1667 ) , was an English courtier .
Bonnie Davis , born Gertrude Melba Smith ( June 10 , 1920 -- August 1976 ) , was an American R&B singer most popular in the 1940s .
Yehuda Sha'ari ( Hebrew : יהודה שערי‎ , 8 February 1920 -- 18 September 1997 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for Liberal Party and the Independent Liberals between 1961 and 1977 .

Philippe Arthuys ( 22 November 1928 -- 6 January 2010 ) was a French composer and film director .
Frank E. Edbrooke ( 1840 - -1921 ) , also known as F.E. Edbrooke , was a 19th and early 20th century architect in Denver , Colorado who has been termed the `` dean '' of Denver architecture .

Paolo Quagliati ( c. 1555 -- 16 November 1628 ) was an Italian composer of the early Baroque era and a member of the Roman School of composers .

Kakaji Maharaj ( 1918 - -1986 ) was an Indian philosopher and thinker .
Vittal Mallya ( 1924 - -1983 ) was an Indian entrepreneur , best known as the former Chairman of the India - based United Breweries Group .
Herman Major Schirmer ( 20 June 1845 -- 11 April 1913 ) was a Norwegian architect and historian of art . Born in Kristiania , the son of an architect , he preferred teaching and studying architecture to designing structures , and is hailed as `` one of the chief ideologues '' of Norwegian romantic nationalism .
Elias Smith ( 17 June 1769 -- 29 June 1846 ) was a preacher , physician , journalist and clergyman .
Natan Spigel ( also : Nathan , Szpigiel / Spiegel / Szpigel ) ( 1886 - -1942 ) was a Jewish artist painter born in Poland .
Robert Raglan ( 7 April 1909 -- 18 July 1985 ) was a British actor best known for his semi - regular role in Dad 's Army as Colonel Pritchard .
Christen Gran Bøgh ( 11 June 1876 -- 4 September 1955 ) was a Norwegian jurist , tourism promoter and theatre critic .

Ted Peterson MBE ( 6 May 1916 -- 19 December 2005 ) was a baseball ( British / Welsh ) player , whose unparalleled achievements in the sport earned him the title `` Mr Baseball '' .
George Brough ( /ˈbrʌf/ BRUF ) ( 21 April 1890 -- 12 January 1970 ) , was a motorcycle racer , world record holding motorcycle and automobile manufacturer , and showman .

Richard Wilmot DD ( 1703 - -1772 ) was a Canon of Windsor from 1748 - -1772
Johnny Mullagh ( born Unaarrimin ) ( 13 August 1841 -- 14 August 1891 ) was a leading Victorian cricketer who led the famous 1868 Aboriginal cricket tour of England .
Eric Spear ( 18 April 1908 -- 3 November 1966 ) was an English composer of film music most noted for writing the theme tune to the ITV soap opera Coronation Street .
Theophilus Weeks ( 1708 -- January 1772 ) was an early settler in the British colony of Province of North Carolina .
Samuel Palmer ( 27 January 1805 -- 24 May 1881 ) was a British landscape painter , etcher and printmaker .
Mark Carlisle , Baron Carlisle of Bucklow QC DL PC ( 7 July 1929 --14 July 2005 ) was a Conservative British politician and was Member of Parliament ( MP ) for Runcorn 1964 - 1983 and Warrington South 1983 - 1987 .
Hedy Lamarr ( /ˈhɛdi/ ; born Hedwig Eva Maria Kiesler , 9 November 1914 -- 19 January 2000 ) was an Austrian and American film actress and inventor .
Randolph H. Guthrie ( 1905 -- 11 September 1989 ) was an American lawyer and businessman who became the chairman of the Studebaker corporation .
Tommy Noble ( 4 March 1897 -- 1 April 1966 ) was a British boxer who was British bantamweight champion between 1918 and 1919 , and European champion in 1919 .
Gøsta af Geijerstam ( 22 August 1888 -- 20 August 1954 , also Gösta , Gustaf ) was a Swedish - Norwegian author and painter .
Arthur Leslie Noel Douglas Houghton , Baron Houghton of Sowerby CH PC ( 11 August 1898 -- 2 May 1996 ) was a British Labour politician .
Simon Luttrell , 1st Earl of Carhampton ( 1713 -- 14 January 1787 ) was an Anglo - Irish politician and nobleman .
Pupienus ( Latin : Marcus Clodius Pupienus Maximus Augustus ; born c. 165/170 -- 29 July 238 ) , also known as Pupienus Maximus , was Roman Emperor with Balbinus for three months in 238 , during the Year of the Six Emperors .

William Yandell Elliott ( 1896 - -1979 ) was an American historian and political advisor to six U.S. presidents .
Jesse Babcock Ferguson ( January 19 , 1819 - -September 3 or September 4 , 1870 ) was an American Christian preacher who developed Spiritualist leanings in the 1840s and 1850s while serving as the preacher at the Nashville , Tennessee Church of Christ .
Jan Malm was CEO of the Swedish telecom company Ericsson in China 2000 - -2004 .
Ezra Ichilov ( Hebrew : עזרא איכילוב‎ , 10 June 1907 -- 25 June 1961 ) was an Israeli politician who served as a member of the Knesset for the General Zionists and the Liberal Party between 1951 and 1961 .
Edward Greenly ( 3 December 1861 -- 4 March 1951 ) was an English geologist known for his a detailed geological survey of the island of Anglesey .
Ramberto Malatesta ( died January 1330 ) was a son of the ill - fated Paolo ' il Bello ' Malatesta and brother of the Archpriest Guido Malatesta .
Mingrui ( Chinese : 明瑞 , Burmese : မင်းယွီ , Burmese pronunciation : ( mɪ́ɴ jwì ) ; ? -- March 1768 ) was the first General of Ili from October 1762 to March 1767 and then Governor - general of Yunnan and Guizhou from April 1767 to March 1768 .

Aberra Kassa ( 1905 -- 21 December 1936 ) was an army commander and a member of the Royal family of the Ethiopian Empire .
William Augustus Hinton ( 15 December 1883 , Chicago , Illinois -- 1959 , Canton , Massachusetts ) was an American bacteriologist , pathologist and educator .
Hiram Sinsabaugh ( c. 1832 - -1892 ) was a Methodist Episcopal minister and banker who served on the Los Angeles , California , Common Council , the legislative branch of the city , in the 19th century .
Ken Hedt ( 15 November 1936 - 16 May 2006 ) was an Australian rules footballer , who played in the Victorian Football League for Collingwood .
Dr. Edwin Caldwell ( August 12 , 1867 in Chapel Hill , North Carolina - 1932 ) was an African American physician who served patients in Central North Carolina around the turn of the twentieth century .

Giuseppe Piamontini ( 1664 - 1742 ) was an Italian sculptor , born and active in Florence .
Jonathan Belcher ( 8 January 1681/2 -- 31 August 1757 ) was a merchant , businessman , and politician from the Province of Massachusetts Bay during the American colonial period .
Sir Walter George Kent CBE ( 1858 -- 11 November 1938 ) was chairman and managing director of the engineering firm George Kent Ltd which was started by his father George Kent in 1838 .
José Miguel García Lanza ( 17??--1828 ; also José Miguel Lanza ) was a hero of the Bolivian wars of independence .

José Manuel Machado ( 1756 - 1852 ) was a Spanish soldier , ranchero , early citizen and regiador on the ayuntamiento of the pueblo of San Diego .
Nils Arntzen Ramm ( 13 August 1903 -- 22 April 1974 ) was a Norwegian engineer , military captain , and businessperson .
Gao Huaide ( 高懷德 ) ( c. 926 -- 982 ) courtesy name Cangyong was a general in ancient China , first in the Later Zhou military and later in the Northern Song military .
Michele Deconet ( b. 1713 - d. 1799 ) was a traveling violinist in Paris and Venice , the latter of which he resided in until his death .
Wellwood Herries Maxwell ( 15 October 1817 -- 13 August 1900 ) was a Scottish Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1868 to 1874 .
Wilhelm Reublin ( 1484 -- c. 1559 ) was a leading figure of the Swiss Brethren movement .
Amatsukaze Masao , born Masao Miyanaga ( 1 December 1937 -- 30 April 2013 ) , is a former sumo wrestler from Monzen , Ishikawa , Japan .
Antoine Janis ( March 26 , 1824 - -1890 ) was a 19th - century French - American fur trader and an early white homesteader in Larimer County , Colorado , in the United States .
Khan Bahadur Nawab Sir Liaqat Hayat Khan KBE KCIE OBE ( also sometimes ' Liaquat Hyat Khan ' ) , ( February 1887 -- 1948 ) was an Indian official who served for most of his career as a minister and later Prime Minister of Patiala State , in British India .
Lila Katzen ( 30 December 1925 , in Brooklyn , NY -- 20 September 1998 , in New York , NY ) , born Lila Pell , was an American sculptor of fluid , large - scale metal abstractions .
George Reginald Starr DSO MC ( 6 April 1904 -- 2 September 1980 ) was a British mining engineer and one of the Special Operations Executive 's best secret agents during World War II .
John Glen Wardrop ( c. 1920 - c. 1989 ) was an English transport analyst who developed Wardrop 's first and second principles of equilibrium .
David Litvinoff ( sometimes Litvinov ; born David Levy ; 3 February 1928 -- 8 April 1975 ) was a consultant for the British film industry who traded on his knowledge of the low life of the East End of London .

Henryk Wieniawski ( ( vʲɛˈɲafskʲi ) ; 10 July 1835 -- 31 March 1880 ) was a Polish violinist and composer .
Richard Nelthorpe ( died 1685 ) was an English lawyer , a conspirator in the Rye House Plot .
Petru Bogdan ( 29 January 1873 , Iași -- 28 March 1944 , Mediaș ) was a Romanian chemist , educator and politician .
Nicholas Fish ( 1758 - -1833 ) was an American Revolutionary War soldier .
Abulhair Khan , Abul Khair Khan ( Kazakh : Әбілқайыр хан , Äbilqayır xan ) ( 1693 - -1748 ) was leader of the Kazakh Little jüz in present - day western Kazakhstan .
Terence Cooper ( 5 July 1933 -- 16 September 1997 ) was a British film actor , best known for his roles in Australian and New Zealand television and film .
Georg Gyssling ( 16 June 1893 -- 8 January 1965 ) was German consul to the United States from 1927 until 1941 , since 1933 in Los Angeles .
William Henry Howe ( 1846 in Ravenna , Ohio -- 1929 ) was an American painter active in Bronxville .
Anne McDonald ( 11 January 1961 -- 22 October 2010 ) was an Australian author and an activist for the rights of people with communication disability .
Daniş Karabelen ( 1898 - 1983 ) was a Turkish Army general who was the founder of Turkey 's Tactical Mobilisation Group in 1952 , and served as its chief until his retirement in 1960 .
Blago Zadro ( 31 March 1944 -- 16 October 1991 ) was a commander of the northern part of Croatian defense forces in Vukovar ( Croatia ) during the Croatian War of Independence .
Miles Morgan ( 1616 -- 28 May 1699 ) was a Welsh colonist of America , a pioneer settler of what was to become Springfield , Massachusetts .
John Droxford ( sometimes John Drokensford ; died 9 May 1329 ) , was a Bishop of Bath and Wells .
Sir George Gustavus Walker KCB JP DL ( 1831 - 5 August 1897 ) was a Conservative Member of Parliament ( MP ) .
Carlo de Tocco ( 11 August 1592 - 14 February 1674 ) , titular Duke of Leucada and Prince of Montemiletto , was an Italian aristocrat , nobleman and military officer .
Richard Beale Blaize ( 1844 - -1904 ) was a West African businessman of Sierra Leonean and Nigerian heritage .
Nişancı Ahmed Pasha ( died February 1753 ) , also called Şehla Ahmed Pasha or Hacı Şehla Ahmed Pasha or Kör Vezir Ahmed Pasha ( `` Ahmed Pasha the Blind Vizier '' ) , was an Ottoman Grand Vizier during the reign of Mahmud I. He was also the Ottoman governor of Egypt from 1748 to 1751 .
Thomas Gerald Pickavance , CBE , FRS ( 19 October 1915 -- 12 November 1991 ) was a British nuclear physicist who was a leading authority on the design and use of particle accelerators .
Bobby Jaspar ( 20 February 1926 -- 28 February 1963 ) was a Belgian cool jazz and hard bop saxophonist , flautist and composer .
Thomas Hebblethwaite ( 1629 -- June 1668 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons between 1660 and 1668 .
Fernando Cortés ( October 4 , 1909 -- 1979 ) was a Mexican ( Puerto Rican by birth ) film actor , writer and director .
David McMackon ( 19 March 1858 -- 10 December 1922 ) was a Canadian sports shooter .
August Bellanca ( born 1880 -- 1969 ) was an American labor activist who was a founder and three - time vice president of the Amalgamated Clothing Workers of America ( ACWA ) .
Parviz Yahaghi ( Persian : پرویز یاحقی ‎‎ ) ( September 22 , 1936 -- February 2 , 2007 ) was a distinguished Iranian composer and violinist .
Henry Somerset , 1st Marquess of Worcester ( 1577 -- 18 December 1646 ) was an English aristocrat , who was a prominent and financially important Royalist during the early years of the English Civil War .
Pir Ilahi Bux died on 8 October 1975 leaving behind him 5 sons and 2 daughters .
Pedro de Calatayud ( 1 August 1689 in Navarre , Spain -- 27 February 1773 in Bologna , Papal States ) was a Jesuit missionary .
Billie Barry ( d. 30 September 2014 ) was an Irish singer , dancer and choreographer who founded the Billie Barry Stage School in 1964 .
Vladimir Naglič ( 1896 -- 1966 ) was a Slovene mariner and translator , known for his contribution to a Slovene Nautical Dictionary ( Pomorska Slovenščina ) published in 1961 in cooperation with Janez Gradišnik and contributor of nautical terms to the Dictionary of Slovene Literary Language .
Annibal Camoux ( 1638 ? -- 1759 ) was a former French soldier from Marseilles who was noted for his longevity .
Sir Henry de Grey of Grays Thurrock , Essex ( 1155 - 1219 ) , was a favourite courtier of King John of England .
Blessed Catherine Jarrige ( 4 October 1754 -- 4 July 1836 ) , known as Catinon Menette , a beatified third - order Dominican of the Catholic Church .
Fernando Ayala ( 2 July 1920 -- 11 September 1997 ) was an Argentine film producer , film director , screenwriter and film producer of the classic era .
Zein al - Sharaf Talal ( 2 August 1916 -- 26 April 1994 ) was the Queen of Jordan and wife of King Talal .
John Belfour ( 1768 - 1842 ) , was an English orientalist and miscellaneous writer , of whom little is recorded , except that he was a member of the Royal Society of Literature , and that he died in the City Road , London , in 1842 , at the age of seventy - four .
Niels Sigfred Nebelong ( 14 October 1806 -- 9 October 1871 ) was a Danish architect who worked in the Historicist style .
Dawson Dawson - Watson ( 1864 - -1939 ) as a British - born Impressionist painter who became famous in 1927 for winning the largest cash prize in American art , the Texas Competitive Wildflower Competition .
Roy Alfred ( May 14 , 1916 -- 2008 ) was an American Tin Pan Alley lyricist whose successful songs included `` The Hucklebuck '' , `` Rock and Roll Waltz '' , and `` Let 's Lock the Door ( And Throw Away the Key ) '' .
Solomon Klein ( October 14 , 1814 at Bischheim , Alsace -- November 10 , 1867 at Colmar , Alsace ) , was a French rabbi .
Embrik Strand ( 2 June 1876 -- 3 November 1947 ) was an arachnologist who classified many insect and spider species , including the greenbottle blue tarantula .
Frank Lewis Marsh ( 18 October 1899 , Aledo , Illinois -- 14 July 1992 ) was an American Seventh - day Adventist biologist , educator and young Earth creationist author .
Derrick Norman Lehmer ( 27 July 1867 -- 8 September 1938 ) was an American mathematician and number theorist .
Herbert Sanders ( 20 September 1878 -- 18 May 1938 ) was a Canadian organist , pianist , conductor , composer , writer on music , and music educator of English birth .
Piet Hesse ( 2 December 1872 -- 4 March 1936 ) was a Dutch comedian of the late 19th and early 20th century .
Theodor von Jürgensen ( 11 April 1840 -- 8 May 1907 ) was a German internist who was a native of Flensburg , Schleswig - Holstein .
Captain Sir Geoffrey de Havilland OM CBE AFC RDI FRAeS ( 27 July 1882 -- 21 May 1965 ) was a British aviation pioneer and aircraft engineer .
André Tulard ( 1899 - -1967 ) was a French civil administrator and police inspector .
Saint Amato Ronconi ( 1225 - 8 May 1292 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic who became a professed member of the Secular Franciscan Order due to his desire to follow in the footsteps of Saint Francis of Assisi .
Percy Fairclough ( 1 February 1858 -- 22 June 1947 ) was an English amateur footballer who made one appearance for England in 1878 .
Ron McCarthy ( 3 November 1934 -- 20 January 1989 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Footscray in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) during the 1950s .
Norman Joseph Fetbrod ( February 18 , 1925 -- 11 May 2007 ) , better known by his professional name Norman Frank , was an American public relations executive and politician who helped the Patrolmen 's Benevolent Association ( PBA ) defeat a civilian complaint review board proposed by New York City Mayor John V. Lindsay .
Nils Wallerius ( Stora Mellösa 1 January 1706 -- Funbo 16 August 1764 ) was a Swedish physicist , philosopher and theologian .
Eric Segelberg ( 20 December 1920 Nykoping , Sweden -- 17 October 2001 Uppsala , Sweden ) was theologian and a priest of the Lutheran Church of Sweden .
Eve Annabel Farjeon ( 19 March 1919 - 8 February 2004 ) was a British ballerina and author .
Amit Golan ( 1964 - 2010 ) ( Hebrew : עמית גולן ) was an Israeli pianist , composer , and jazz educator .
Daniel Dancer ( 1716 - -1794 ) was a notorious English miser whose life was documented soon after his death and continued in print over the following century .
Peter Engelmann ( b. Pfalz , Rhenish Prussia , 1823 in -- d. 1874 ) was a German American educationist , writer and founder of the German - English Academy ( today University School of Milwaukee ) .
Edmund Gunter ( 1581 -- 10 December 1626 ) , was an English clergyman , mathematician , geometer and astronomer of Welsh descent .
Charles I , Duke of Münsterberg - Oels ( also : Charles I of Podebrady , Czech : Karel z Minstrberka , German : Karl I. von Münsterberg ; 2 or 4 May 1476 , Kladsko -- 31 May 1536 , Frankenstein ) was a member of the House of Poděbrady .
Sir John Robin Ibbs , KBE ( 21 April 1926 -- 27 July 2014 ) was an English business executive , government advisor and Royal Navy officer .
Arvid Emanuel Kallen ( July 24 , 1895 -- April 1969 ) was a General Motors executive until his retirement in 1959 .
Ron Kershaw ( 1945 -- July 1989 ) was an American television news executive responsible for several television news innovations .
Sir John Penington ( 1584?--1646 ) was an English admiral who served under Charles I of England .
Carl Wilhelm Scheele ( 9 December 1742 -- 21 May 1786 ) was a Swedish Pomeranian and pharmaceutical chemist .
Chapman Cohen ( 1 September 1868 -- 4 February 1954 ) was a leading English atheist and secularist writer and lecturer .
Ida Aalberg ( 4 December 1857 -- 17 January 1915 ) was the most notable and internationally known Finnish actress of her time .
James McGiffen ( 30 January 1904 -- 3 August 1929 ) was an English footballer who played as an outside left in the Football League for Darlington .
Frank Caine ( 28 July 1881 -- 19 January 1930 ) was an Australian rules footballer in the Victorian Football League .
Sir Archibald Douglas of Glenbervie ( 1513 -- 18 September 1570 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
Sir John Wittewrong , 1st Baronet ( 1 November 1618 -- 23 June 1693 ) was an English parliamentarian colonel and squire of Rothamsted Manor .
John IV of Werle - Goldberg , ( before 1350 -- between 13 March and 14 December 1374 ) was from 1354 until his death Lord of Werle - Goldberg .
Li Shanlan ( 李善蘭 , courtesy name : Renshu 壬叔 , art name : Qiuren 秋紉 ) ( 1810 -- 1882 ) was a Chinese mathematician of the Qing Dynasty .
Fr . Elie Melia ( Georgian : ილია მელია ) ( February 20 , 1915 -- 1988 ) was a Georgian Orthodox priest in France and church historian .
Zhao Erxun , or Chao Erh - sun , ( simplified Chinese : 赵尔巽 ; traditional Chinese : 趙爾巽 ; 1844 - -1927 ) was the brother of Zhao Erfeng .
Stephen McGonagle ( 17 November 1914 -- 4 March 2002 ) was a Northern Irish and Irish trade unionist .
Ubay ibn Ka'b ( died 649 ) , also known as Abu Mundhir ( the father of Mundhir ) , was a companion of the Islamic prophet Muhammad and a person of high esteem in the early Muslim community .
Albert Inkpin ( 16 June 1884 -- 1944 ) was a British communist and the first General Secretary of the Communist Party of Great Britain ( CPGB ) .
Julius Klinger ( May 22 , 1876 -- 1942 ) was an Austrian Painter , draftsman , illustrator , commercial graphic artist , typographer and writer .
Jenő Ghyczy de Ghicz , Assakürt et Ablánczkürt ( 4 May 1893 -- 18 January 1982 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Foreign Affairs between 1943 and 1944 .
Charles Skinner Hallpike , CBE , FRS ( 19 July 1900 -- 26 September 1979 ) was an English otologist .
Charles N. Riotte ( 1814 - -1887 ) was an American diplomat who served as US ambassador to Costa Rica and Nicaragua under the administration of Abraham Lincoln and Ulysses S. Grant .
Karl Eusebius , Prince of Liechtenstein ( 11 April 1611 -- 5 April 1684 ) was the Prince of Liechtenstein .
Anne Hutchinson , born Anne Marbury ( 1591 - -1643 ) , was a Puritan spiritual adviser , mother of 15 , and an important participant in the Antinomian Controversy that shook the infant Massachusetts Bay Colony from 1636 to 1638 .
Karl - Heinz Marsell ( 1 August 1936 -- 23 September 1996 ) was a German professional cyclist who was active between 1955 and 1966 , predominantly in motor - paced racing .
Sir Joseph Ashe , 1st Baronet ( 1618 -- 15 April 1686 ) was an English Whig politician and merchant .
Joseph Katz ( 1912 - -2004 ) allegedly worked for Soviet intelligence from the 1930s to the late 1940s as one of its most active liaison agents .
Josias Nottidge ( 1828 - 1873 ) was an English rower who twice won Silver Goblets at Henley Royal Regatta .
Johan Andreas Altenburg ( 1763 - -1824 ) was a Norwegian merchant and shipowner , who belonged to the patriciate of the port town of Skien .
Henrik Johan Walbeck ( 1794 - 1823 ) was a Finnish geodesist studying the size and figure of the Earth by means of grade measurement .
William Ohly ( 31 August 1883 -- 22 July 1955 ) was a British ethnographic art collector and gallery owner , whose Berkeley Galleries and Abbey Art Centre and Museum were important features of the mid-20th century London art scene .
Marcus Ummidius Quadratus Annianus ( 138 CE - 182 CE ) was a wealthy Roman Politician and the nephew of the Roman emperor Marcus Aurelius .
Wes Gallagher ( died October 11 , 1997 ) was an American journalist for the Associated Press .
Chokkanatha Nayak ( 1662 - -1682 ) succeeded his father Muttu Alkadri Nayak , as the ruler of the Madurai Nayak dynasty , when he was sixteen years old .
Saints Exuperius and Zoe ( died 127 AD ) are 2nd century Christian martyrs .
Usher Lee was Dean of Waterford from 1804 until his death in 1850 .
Simcha Dinitz ( Hebrew : שמחה דיניץ‎ , born 23 June 1929 , died 23 September 2003 ) was an Israeli statesman and politician .
Sangram Shah ( 1500 - -1542 CE ) was a king of the Garha - Katanga Kingdom , now in the Narsinghpur district within the state of Madhya Pradesh , India .
Elna Lassen ( 1901 -- 1930 ) was a Danish ballerina who was the premiere danseuse of the Royal Danish Ballet .
John Backwell ( 20 April 1654 -- 15 April 1708 ) was an English politician , the son of the financier Edward Backwell .
Mr Commissioner Robert Malcolm Kerr LL.D ( 5 June 1821 - -21 November 1902 ) , was a British judge of the late Victorian era .
General of the Infantry Jakob Friedrich von Rüchel - Kleist ( 25 January 1778 , Segenthin -- 15 March 1848 , Danzig ) was a Prussian officer during the Napoleonic Wars and a governor of Danzig ( Gdansk ) .
James Bucknall Bucknall Estcourt ( 1803 - 1855 ) , was a major - general and MP .
Christina Charlotta Cederström ( née Mörner af Morlanda ) ( 2 March 1760 -- 22 February 1832 ) was a Swedish dilettante artist , salon hostess , and baroness .

George Drought Warburton ( 1816 - -1857 ) was an Irish soldier , politician and writer on Canada .

Jakob Horn ( 14 February 1867 -- 24 February 1946 ) was a German mathematician who introduced Horn functions .
Cut Nyak Meutia ( 1870 -- 24 October 1910 ) , also known as Cut Meutia , is an Indonesian national hero from Aceh .
Count Adamo Chiusole ( ( 1728 - 1787 ) was an Italian painter and art historian . He mainly painted subjects with animals , landscapes and capricci .
Eugene List ( July 6 , 1918 -- March 1 , 1985 ) was an American concert pianist and teacher .
Sir John Hardy , 1st Baronet ( 23 February 1809 -- 9 July 1888 ) , was a British Conservative Member of Parliament .
Dr Eric Cunningham Dax , AO , BSc Lond , HonMD , FRACP , FRANZCP , HonFRCPsych ( 18 May 1908 -- 29 January 2008 ) was a British - born Australian psychiatrist .
Gustaf Adolf Vive Sparre af Söfteborg ( 4 September 1802 -- 26 April 1886 ) was a Swedish nobleman , civil servant and politician .
Félix Cottrau , a French painter , was born in Paris in 1799 , and died in the same city in 1852 .
Tom B. Coughran ( March 18 , 1906 , near Visalia , California -- October 2 , 1993 ) was an American banker , soldier and public servant .
Auguste Pierre Chouteau ( 9 May 1786 -- 25 December 1838 ) was a member of the Chouteau fur - trading family who established trading posts in what is now the U.S. state of Oklahoma .
Ernst Plassmann ( 14 June 1823 -- 28 November 1877 ; alternate spelling , Plassman ) was a German - American sculptor and carver .
Francis Joseph Neptune ( 1735 - -1834 ) was chief of the Passamaquoddy tribe during the American Revolutionary War .
Theophilus Polwhele or Polwheile ( died 1689 ) was an English ejected minister .
Richard Annesley , 2nd Earl Annesley PC ( Ire ) ( 14 April 1745 -- 9 November 1824 ) , styled The Honourable from 1758 to 1802 , was an Anglo - Irish politician and noble .
Madeleine Simms ( 6 September 1930 -- 3 October 2011 ) was a British social campaigner and one of the architects of the Abortion Act 1967 .
Corneliu E. Giurgea ( 6 January 1923 , Bucharest -- 30 December 1995 , Brussels ) was a Romanian psychologist and chemist .
Lieutenant Colonel Henry Milling ( died 30 December 1822 ) was a British Army officer who fought in the Napoleonic Wars .
Richard Sampson ( died 25 September 1554 ) was an English clergyman and composer of sacred music , who was Anglican bishop of Chichester and subsequently of Coventry and Lichfield .
Samuel Simmons ( 1640 - -1687 ) was an English printer , best known as the first publisher of several works by John Milton .
Sir John Hody ( died 1441 ) was an English judge and Chief Justice of the King 's Bench
Xu Ming ( Chinese : 徐明 ; pinyin : Xú Míng ; April 1971 -- 4 December 2015 ) was a Chinese entrepreneur and onetime billionaire .
Boris Mokrousov ( Russian : Бори́с Андре́евич Мокроу́сов ; 27 February 1909 -- 27 March 1968 ) was a Soviet composer .
King Hye of Baekje ( died 599 ) ( r. 598 - -599 ) was the 28th king of Baekje , one of the Three Kingdoms of Korea .

Spencer Leigh Hughes ( 21 April 1858 -- 22 February 1920 ) was a British , engineer , journalist and Liberal politician .
Heinrich Gattineau ( 6 January 1905 in Bucharest -- 27 April 1985 ) was a German economist , Sturmabteilung ( SA ) leader , director of IG Farben and defendant during the Nuremberg trials .
Sir Charles Wolseley , 7th Baronet ( 20 July 1769 - 3 October 1846 ) was one of the Wolseley baronets of Staffordshire .
Marius Plamondon ( 1914 - -1976 ) was a Canadian sculptor and stained glass artist who made a significant contribution to the revival of the art of stained glass in Quebec during his lifetime .
Donald Carroll ( 12 December 1940 -- 30 December 2010 ) was an American author , editor , poet , columnist and humourist .
Robert Templeton ( 12 December 1802 -- 2 June 1892 ) was a Naturalist , artist , and entomologist , and was born at Cranmore House , Belfast , Ireland .
Like his grandfather , Bishan Singh died in this bitterly cold region ( 31 December 1699 ) after serving a bigoted and thankless master .

El Gran Senor ( 21 April 1981 -- October 2006 ) was an American - bred Thoroughbred race horse , foaled at Windfields Farm in Maryland .
Sir John Trott , 1st Baronet ( ca . 1615 -- 14 July 1672 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1672 .
Martin Henry Freeman ( 1826 - -1889 ) was the first Black president of an American college , as well as later serving as president of Liberia College .
George Manson ( 3 December 1850 - 27 February 1876 ) was a Scottish watercolour painter born in Edinburgh .
Hans Holmboe ( 8 October 1798 - 23 May 1868 ) was a Norwegian educator and politician .
Franceschetto Cybo ( baptized Francesco ) ( c. 1450 -- 25 July 1519 ) was an Italian nobleman , the illegitimate son of Pope Innocent VIII ( Giovanni Battista Cybo ) .
Mohammad Barkatullah ( 1898 -- 1974 ) , a Bangladeshi author , was born in Sirajganj .
Isabella Mercia McDonagh ( 1899 - -1982 ) , also known as Marie Lorraine , was an Australian actress who often worked in collaboration with her sisters Paulette and Phyllis .
Christian Fleischer ( 1713 -- 21 March 1768 ) was a Danish civil servant in the naval administration .
Edmund Whitelocke ( 1565 - -1608 ) was an English soldier , royal courtier and suspected conspirator .
Arcangelo Corelli ( /kɔːˈrɛli/ ; 17 February 1653 -- 8 January 1713 ) was an Italian violinist and composer of the Baroque era .
M.C. Davar ( 24 April 1913 -- 9 November 1977 ) was a freedom fighter and associate of Jawaharlal Nehru who is remembered for his opposition to the Partition of India , his work among the refugees from Pakistan and his championing the idea of a confederation of India and Pakistan .
Thomas Francis McNulty ( 1858 or 1859 -- 1932 ) was an American Democratic Party ( United States ) political operative and epithetist .
James Moss Cardwell ( 17 January 1926 - 11 April 1990 ) , who used the pen name Adobe James , was an American writer and educator .
Henrik von Rehbinder ( 1604 - -1680 ) was a Swedish soldier and Friherre of the Udriku estate in Swedish Estonia .
Jean - François Batut ( 26 June 1828 in Castres - 21 May 1907 ) was a French painter known for his portraits , with subjects including Ferdinand de Lesseps and Gustave Eiffel .

Charles George Harper ( 1863 -- 1943 ) was an English author and illustrator .
Heukchi Sangji ( Hangul : 흑치상지 , Hanja : 黑齒常之 , pinyin : Heichi Changzhi ) ( 630 - -689 ) was a Baekje general who became a leader of the Baekje Revival Movement , and later a Tang Dynasty general .

Saints Julian and Basilissa ( died ca . 304 ) were husband and wife .
John Chauderon ( French : Jean Chauderon ; died 1294 ) was the Baron of Estamira and Grand Constable of the Principality of Achaea , the strongest of the principalities of Frankish Greece .

John Sommerfield ( 25 June 1908 -- 13 August 1991 ) was a British writer and left - wing activist known for his influential novel May Day , which fictionalised a Communist upheaval in 1930s London .

Adolph Carl von de Heyde Süssmilch ( 12 February 1875 -- 6 December 1946 ) , also known as Adolph Carl Süssmilch , was an Australian geologist and educationist .

Cândido da Fonseca Galvão , also known as Dom Obá II D'África ( Lençóis , 1845 - 1890 ) , was a Brazilian military and nobleman .
Walter Hussey Burgh ( 1742 - -1783 ) was an Irish statesman , barrister and judge ; he sat in the Irish House of Commons , and was considered to be one of its outstanding orators ; he served briefly as Chief Baron of the Exchequer at the end of his life .
Stella Schmolle , ( 1908 - 1975 ) was a British painter , known for the paintings she produced while serving in the Auxiliary Territorial Service during World War II and for her post - war portrait paintings .
Andrés Curruchich ( full name Andrés Curruchich Cúmez , sometimes called `` Andrew '' ) ( 19 January 1891 - 18 February 1969 ) was a Guatemalan naïve painter of the Kaqchikel people from the Kaqchikel town of San Juan Comalapa .
Nicola Veronica a portrait artist , photograph engraver for The Chicago Tribune newspaper , and art instructor at Palette and Chisel Academy of Fine Art in Chicago , Illinois , was born 15 August 1905 in Italy , and died September 1979 .
Octavio Gaona ( 1907 - -1996 ) was a Mexican Luchador , or professional wrestler , known for his participation in the first ever high profile Lucha de Apuesta , or wager fight , against Murciélago Velázquez .
Paolo Falconieri ( 1638 - -1704 ) was an Italian architect , painter and mathematician , from a noble family of Florence , whose intellectual interests were wide - ranging , one of the viruosi of the first scientific century .
Richard Risley ( before 1615 - 1648 ) was an early Puritan settler in the Massachusetts Bay Colony and one of the founders of Hartford , Connecticut .
Ami Perrin ( died 1561 ) was a Swiss Libertine and one of the most powerful figures in Geneva in the 16th century as chief opponent of religious reformer John Calvin 's rule of the city .

Benjamin Franklin Williams ( 1819 - 1886 ) was a Methodist minister and Republican politician who served three terms in the Texas Legislature .

Robert Moorhouse ( 7 September 1866 -- 7 January 1921 ) was an English first - class cricketer , who played 206 matches for Yorkshire County Cricket Club between 1888 and 1899 .
Manuel Zapata Olivella ( Santa Cruz of Lorica , Córdoba , 17 March 1920 - Bogota , 19 November 2004 ) was a doctor , anthropologist and Colombian writer .

James Tassie ( 1735 - -1799 ) was a Scottish gem engraver and modeller .
Arthur Montagu Brookfield ( 18 March 1853 -- 3 March 1940 ) was a British army officer , diplomat author and Conservative politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1885 to 1903 .
Sumitra Charat Ram ( 17 November 1914 -- 8 August 2011 ) was noted Indian arts patron , impresario and the founder of Shriram Bharatiya Kala Kendra ( SBKK ) established in 1952 .
Eochocán mac Áedo ( died 883 ) was a Dál Fiatach king of Ulaid , which is now Ulster , Ireland .
Norman St John - Stevas , Baron St John of Fawsley , PC , FRSL ( /ˌsɪndʒən ˈstiːvəs/ sin - jən - STEE - vəs ; 18 May 1929 -- 2 March 2012 ) was a British politician , author , constitutional expert and barrister .
Hans von Baysen or Jan Bażyński ( c. 1394 -- 1459 ) was a Prussian knight and statesman , leader of the Prussian Confederation and the first Polish governor of Royal Prussia .

Henry Smith Carhart , Ph . B. ( 1844 - -1920 ) was an American physicist and university professor .
Sir Thomas Dick Lauder of Fountainhall , 7th Baronet , FRSE FSA(Scot ) ( 13 August 1784 -- 29 May 1848 ) was a Scottish author .
Jim Adamson ( 1 August 1905 -- 22 August 1991 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with North Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) for over a decade .
Wulfoald ( died 680 ) was the mayor of the palace of Austrasia from 656 or 661 , depending on when Grimoald I was removed from that office ( accounts vary : see his article for details ) , to his death and mayor of the palace of Neustria and Burgundy from 673 to 675 .
Howard Steel ( 14 May 1911 -- 12 February 1987 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Abdul Samad Abdulla ( died 25 August 2013 ) was a Maldivian politician and the Minister of Foreign Affairs .
Richard Edward Geoffrey Howe , Baron Howe of Aberavon CH PC QC ( 20 December 1926 -- 9 October 2015 ) , known from 1970 to 1992 as Sir Geoffrey Howe , was a British Conservative politician .
Subodh Ghosh ( Bengali : সুবোধ ঘোষ ) ( 1909 - -1980 ) was a noted Bengali author and journalist with Kolkata - based daily newspaper Ananda Bazar Patrika .
George Austin ( fl . 1780s ) was one of two gardeners trained at the Royal Botanic Gardens , Kew , in London and sent by Joseph Banks to care for plants on a voyage to the British colony in New Holland ( Australia ) in 1789 .
William Gandy ( died 1729 ) , was an English portrait - painter .
Harriet Whitney Frishmuth ( September 17 , 1880 , Philadelphia , Pennsylvania -- January 1980 , Waterbury , Connecticut ) was an American sculptor known for her works in bronze .
Imrich Barta ( 1925 in Šamorín -- 1999 in Bratislava ) , was a famous Slovak painter and architect of Greek ancestry .
Fritz Feigl ( 15 May 1891 -- 23 January 1971 ) was a Jewish Austrian - born chemist .
Sir Henry Kenyon Stephenson , 1st Baronet ( 16 August 1865 - 20 September 1947 ) was a British politician and businessperson .
Morris Goldseker ( December 24 , 1898 - June 1973 ) was a real estate business tycoon , broker , and philanthropist .
Alfred Zachariewicz ( 26 August 1871 -- 11 July 1937 ) , was a Polish architect .
Henrik Rohmann ( 4 August 1910 , Bátaapáti -- 13 October 1978 , Budapest ) was a Hungarian harpist and harp teacher .
Charles Kynard ( 20 February 1933 - -8 July 1979 ) was an American soul jazz / acid jazz organist born in St. Louis , Missouri .
François Beaulieu II was a chief of the Yellowknife tribe ( 1771 -- November 1872 ) .
Lieven Cruyl , or Lievin Cruyl ( name variations : Levin Cruijl , Lievin Cruijl , Levin Cruyl , Livinus Cruylius , Cruylius Livinus ) ( 1634 , Ghent -- before 1720 , Ghent ) was a Flemish priest , architect , designer and engraver .

Lal Waterson ( 15 February 1943 -- 4 September 1998 ) was an English folksinger and songwriter .
Bent Holtsmark ( 1823 - -1903 ) was a Norwegian agriculturalist and politician .
David de Caires ( 31 December 1937 -- 1 November 2008 ) was a Guyanese solicitor .
Richard Herron ( 1890 -- 1917 ) was an English footballer who played for Stoke .
Geoffrey Kerr ( 26 January 1895 -- 1 July 1971 ) was a British stage and film actor and writer , during the middle of the 20th century , part of a British family with a strong stage and theatre tradition spanning several generations .
Dame Penelope Jessel ( 2 January 1920 - -2 December 1996 ) , DBE was a British Liberal Party politician .
Cormac Cruinn Ó Máille ( died 1384 ) was an Irish noble .
Janusz Aleksander Sanguszko ( 5 May 1712 , Lubartów -- 14 September 1775 , Dubno ) was a magnate in the Polish - Lithuanian Commonwealth .
John Phillip Boehm ( 1683 - -1749 ) was a school teacher and an early leader in the German Reformed Church ( now the Reformed Church in the United States )
Georg Nees ( 23 June 1926 -- 3 January 2016 ) was a German academic who was a pioneer of computer art and generative graphics .
Arthur Minasy ( 1925 -- 9 May 1994 ) was an American inventor .
Žarko Mihajlović ( 4 March 1920 -- 16 September 1986 ) was a Yugoslav football coach who managed BSK Beograd , FK Crvena Zvezda , OFK Beograd , PAOK , Fenerbahçe , Ethnikos Piraeus , Apollon Kalamarias , Doxa Dramas , Karşıyaka , Qadsia SC , and the Turkey national football team .
Henry Scott Riddell ( 23 September 1798 -- 1870 ) was a Scottish poet and songwriter .
Mary Rose Tully MPH IBCLC ( 29 July 1946 -- 20 January 2010 ) was an American lactation consultant , director of the Department of Lactation Services at the University of North Carolina 's Women 's Hospital , and an adjunct clinical instructor of pediatrics at the University of North Carolina 's School of Medicine .
Charlotte Sophia Burne ( Shropshire , 1850 - -1923 ) was an English author and editor , and the first woman to become president of the Folklore Society .

Åke Gerhard ( Utansjö , Ångermanland , 26 March 1921 - 20 August 2009 ) was a Swedish songwriter .
Nito Alves ( 1945 - -1977 ) was an Angolan politician who served as the Interior Minister of Angola from independence , on November 11 , 1975 , until President Agostinho Neto abolished the position in October 1976 .
Reşit Galip ( Rhodes , 1893 -- Ankara , 5 March 1934 ) was a Turkish politician in the early years of the Turkish Republic .
Tim Griek ( Haarlem , 1944 -- Ursem , 13 February 1988 ) was a Dutch musician and producer .
Logan Hay ( died 1942 ) was a prominent Illinois lawyer .
Nicholas Hayman ( died 1606 ) , of Totnes ; later of Dartmouth , Devon , was an English merchant and politician .
Esme Melville ( born Esme Grace Mount - Melville , 23 July 1918 -- 14 September 2006 ) was an Australian theatre , television and film actress .
Baldassare Aloisi , or Baldassare Galanino ( 12 October 1578 - -1638 ) , was an Italian history and portrait painter and engraver .
Zoltán Rónai ( 16 August 1880 - 17 May 1940 ) was a Hungarian politician and jurist , who served as People 's Commissar of Justice in 1919 during the Hungarian Soviet Republic .
Władysław Szuszkiewicz ( 12 November 1938 in Wilno -- 14 November 2007 ) was a Polish sprint canoer who competed from the mid-1960s to the early 1970s .
Adam Lux ( 27 December 1765 -- 4 November 1793 ) was a German revolutionary and sympathiser of the French Revolution .
Bartolomeo Gosio ( 17 March 1863 - 13 April 1944 ) was an Italian medical scientist .
Rosendo Ruiz Suárez ( 1 March 1885 -- 1 January 1983 ) was a Cuban singer , guitarist and composer , considered one of the founders of the trova .
Cathleen Nesbitt , CBE ( 24 November 1888 -- 2 August 1982 ) was a British actress of stage , film and television .
Veene Sheshanna ( Kannada : ವೀಣೆ ಶೇಷಣ್ಣ ) ( 1852 - 1926 ) was an exponent of the Veena , an Indian string instrument , which he played in the classical Carnatic music style .
Alexander Griggs ( 1838 - -1903 ) was an American steamboat captain .
John Ashburnham , 1st Baron Ashburnham ( 15 January 1656 -- 21 January 1710 ) was an English landowner and politician .
Robert Murray Keith ( died 1774 ) was a British diplomat .
