Gladys Thayer ( also known as Gladys Thayer Reasoner ) ( 1886 - 1945 ) was an American painter and teacher .
Filipe de Magalhães ( ca . 1571 - -1652 ) was a Portuguese composer of sacred polyphony .
Kenneth Higgins ( 26 December 1919 - 22 January 2008 ) was a British cinematographer who worked on both television and film .
Martin Travers ( born Howard Martin Otho Travers , in Margate , Kent on 19 February 1886 -- died in London on 25 July 1948 ) was an English church artist and designer .
Ma Qianling ( 1824－1909 ) was a Chinese Muslim General who defected to the Qing Dynasty in 1872 during the Dungan revolt along with his superior General Ma Zhanao and General Ma Haiyan .
Richard Leech ( 24 November 1922 -- 24 March 2004 ) , born Richard Leeper McClelland , was an Irish actor .
George Williams Fulcher ( 1795 - -1855 ) , was an English poet and miscellaneous writer .
Albert Henry Ross ( 1881 -- 14 September 1950 ) , ( pseudonym Frank Morison ) , was an English advertising agent and freelance writer .
Reginald Edward Enthoven CIE ( 1869 - -1952 ) was an administrator in the Indian Civil Service of the British Raj and an author of publications related to India , including the three volumes entitled The Tribes and Castes of Bombay that formed a part of the Ethnographic Survey of India .
Mary Borden ( 1886 - -1968 ) was an early 20th - century , Anglo - American novelist .
Sophia Dobson Collet ( 1 February 1822 -- 27 March 1894 ) was a 19th - century English feminist freethinker .
Sir Donald Neil MacCormick , QC , FBA , FRSE ( 27 May 1941 -- 5 April 2009 ) , was a Scottish legal philosopher and politician .
Médard Tytgat ( 1871 - -1948 ) was a Belgian painter , lithographer , book illustrator and poster artist known for portraits , nudes , and landscapes .
Arai Osui ( 新井奥邃 ) ( 1846 - -1922 ) was a prominent Japanese disciple of the 19th century cult leader , Thomas Lake Harris .
Leonard Frank Meares ( 13 February 1921 -- 4 February 1993 ) was an Australian writer of western fiction .
Anna Maria Rüttimann - Meyer von Schauensee ( 6 October 1772 in Luzern -- 19 August 1856 ) was a politically influential Swiss salonist during the Helvetian Republic .
Pablo Pontons ( 1606 - -1670 ) was a Spanish painter of the Baroque period .
Judson Worthington Hastings , born on June 13 , 1853 in Suffield , Connecticut and died in 1923 , was a physician and public official .
Daniel Soreau ( c.1560 -- 28 March 1619 ) was a German Baroque still life painter .
Don Lane ( 13 November 1933 -- 22 October 2009 ) , born as Morton Donald Isaacson , was a Gold Logie winning American - born talk show host and singer .
Charles Émile Egli ( known as Carlègle ; 30 March 1877 - 11 January 1937 ) was a Swiss - born illustrator and painter who spent most of his life in Paris .
Paul Gundani ( 1967 -- 3 November 2015 ) was a Zimbabwean professional football player .
John Dollard ( 29 August 1900 -- 8 October 1980 ) was an American psychologist and social scientist best known for his studies on race relations in America and the frustration - aggression hypothesis he proposed with Neal E. Miller and others .
Stephen G. Haines ( 1945 - -2012 ) was an American organizational theorist , management consultant , author of books on management and systems thinking .
Bill McGuffie ( 11 December 1927 -- 22 March 1987 ) was a pianist who went on to become a film composer and conductor .
Anne of Bavaria ( or of the Palatinate ; Czech : Anna Falcká ; 26 September 1329 -- 2 February 1353 ) was a queen consort of Bohemia .
Yaşar Doğu ( 1913 - 8 January 1961 ) , was a renowned Turkish World and Olympic champion sports wrestler in Greco - Roman and Freestyle .
William B. Snow ( San Francisco , 16 May 1903 - 5 October 1968 ) was a sound engineer .
Christophe Butkens ( 1590 - -1650 ) was a Cistercian abbot from Antwerp , historian and genealogist .
William L. Grout ( 1833 - -1908 ) was an U. S. industrialist and pioneer manufacturer of sewing machines and automobiles .
Helmuth von Pannwitz ( 14 October 1898 -- 16 January 1947 ) was a German general who distinguished himself as a cavalry officer during the First and the Second World Wars .
Daniel Silvan Evans ( 11 January 1818 -- 12 April 1903 ) was a Welsh scholar and lexicographer .
Roop Nath Singh Yadav died on 13 February 2001 at Allahabad , Uttar Pradesh at the age of 83 .
Dr. Joseph Stayman was born in 1817 and died in 1903 .
Gottfried Finger ( ca . 1655 - 6 -- buried 31 August 1730 ) , also Godfrey Finger , was a Moravian Baroque composer .
Luis MacGregor Cevallos ( 1887 - -1965 ) was a Mexican architect as well as an author of book on Colonial Mexican architecture .
Estefanía Ramírez ( died 1183 ) , daughter of Count Ramiro Fróilaz , was the wife of Count Ponce de Minerva .
R. Stanton Avery ( 13 January 1907 -- 12 December 1997 ) was an inventor , most known for creating self - adhesive labels ( modern stickers ) .
Ímar Ua Ruaidín , Bishop of Kilmacduagh , died 1176 .
Postumus the Younger would have been killed together with his father in 268 , during the rebellion of Laelianus ( called Lollianus in the Historia ) .
Gordon McKeag ( 1928 -- 29 September 2005 ) was an English solicitor and former chairman of Newcastle United .
Frederick E. Turnage ( 1936 - 2011 ) is the former mayor of Rocky Mount , North Carolina .
Daniel le Pelley , 12th Seigneur of Sark ( died 1752 ) was Seigneur of Sark from 1742 to 1752 .

Andreas Kneller ( variants : Kniller , Knöller , Knüller ) ( 23 April 1649 -- 24 August 1724 ) was a German composer and organist of the North German school .
Bruno Dallansky ( 19 September 1928 -- 5 August 2008 ) was an Austrian actor who was best known for his roles on television and stage .
Jerzy Adam Brandhuber ( 23 October 1897 -- 19 June 1981 ) was a Polish painter and a survivor of the Auschwitz concentration camp .
George Levis ( November 22 , 1894 -- October 1980 ) was an American college basketball player and coach during the 1910s and 1920s , respectively .
Ferdinand Tobias Richter ( 22 July 1651 -- 3 November 1711 ) was an Austrian Baroque composer and organist .
Doctor Pellegrino Matteucci ( 12 October 1850 -- 8 August 1881 ) was an Italian explorer known for his expeditions to Africa .
Nikos Tsiforos ( Greek : Νίκος Τσιφόρος ; 1912 -- 6 August 1970 ) was a Greek screenwriter and film director .
David Lindsay , 2nd Lord Lindsay of the Byres ( died 1490 ) was a Scottish lord of parliament and supporter of King James III of Scotland .
Timothy Armitage ( died 1655 ) , was in the year 1647 `` chosen pastor of the first independent ( or congregational ) church in the city of Norwich '' .
Arthur Holbrook Wellman ( October 30 , 1855 -- 1948 ) was a member of the Massachusetts General Court and a professor at Boston University School of Law .
Magdalen Dacre , Viscountess Montagu ( January 1538 -- 8 April 1608 ) was an English noblewoman .
Ephraim Douglass Adams ( December 18 , 1865 in Decorah , Iowa -- September 1 , 1930 in Stanford , California ) was an American educator and historian , regarded as an expert on the American Civil War and British - American relations .
William Robertson Coe II ( 28 November 1926 -- 23 November 2009 ) was an American academic , archaeologist and Mayanist scholar , renowned for his extensive field work and publications on pre - Columbian Maya civilization sites .
John G. Nichols ( 1812 -- 1898 ) was a businessman , builder , and politician .
Hugh May ( 1621 -- 21 February 1684 ) was an English architect in the period after the Restoration of King Charles II . He worked in the era which fell between the first introduction of Palladianism into England by Inigo Jones , and the full flowering of English Baroque under John Vanbrugh and Nicholas Hawksmoor .
Piotr Baryka ( 1600 - -1675 ) , was a seventeenth - century Polish soldier and writer , most probably of burgher origin , of whom very little is known .
Glenn Cannon ( 21 November 1932 - 20 April 2013 ) was a Hawaii - based actor and educator best known for his roles on Hawaii Five - O and Magnum , P.I. He also appeared on Lost in a pair of different roles .
Giuseppe Loretz ( Milan , 4 March 1860 -- Rubbiano , 15 January 1944 ) was an Italian cyclist .
Robbie Benoit ( ? --2007 ) was a Canadian poet and writer .
Robin Warwick Gibson OBE ( 3 May 1944 -- 9 August 2010 ) was a British gallery curator and art historian best known for his work at the National Portrait Gallery in London between 1968 and 2001 , including eight years as Chief Curator .
Sukumar Bose ( Bengali : সুকুমার বসু , Hindi : सुकुमार बोसे ) ( 12 May 1912 -- 10 November 1986 ) was a notable Indian artist based in Delhi who was trained in the tradition of the Bengal School under Asit Kumar Haldar .
Fred MacDonald ( 1895 - -1968 ) , was an Australian actor best known for playing Dave Rudd opposite Bert Bailey on stage and screen , starting with the original 1912 production of On Our Selection .
Sir Alan Herries Wilson ( 2 July 1906 -- 30 September 1995 ) , was a British mathematician and industrialist .
Jeff Mayo ( 7 October 1921 , London -- 17 April 1998 , Barnstaple ) was an English astrologer and astrology teacher / writer .
Rowland Plumbe , also known as Roland Plumbe ( 2 February 1838 , Whitechapel -- 2 April 1919 , Willesden ) , was an English architect , famous for being the author of many residential schemes across London , many being considered the first examples of the Victorian Garden City .
Sam Hanna Bell ( 1909 -- 1990 ) was a novelist , short story writer , playwright , and broadcaster who lived in Northern Ireland .
He Yizhen ( 1910 - 2008 ) was a physicist in China .
Liang Na ( Chinese : 梁妠 ; 116 - -150 ) , formally Empress Shunlie ( 順烈皇后 , literally `` the kind and achieving empress '' ) , was an empress during the Han Dynasty .

Petrus Vulcanius otherwise Pieter De Smet ( born c. 1503 - -1571 ) was a humanist scholar and local government official of Bruges .

Neville Hamilton ( 19 April 1960 -- 9 February 2009 ) was an English footballer and coach .
Bayram Pasha ( died 26 August 1638 ) was an Ottoman grand vizier from 1637 to 1638 and the Ottoman governor of Egypt from 1626 to 1628 .

Frank Wayman ( 30 December 1931 − 7 February 2008 ) was an English footballer .

William Thomas Shave Daniel ( 1806 - -1891 ) was vice - chairman of the Incorporated Council of Law Reporting .
Ada Boni , née Giaquinto , ( 1881 -- 1973 ) was an Italian magazine editor , food writer and book author .
Gopal Mittal was 87 years old when he died in Delhi on 15 April 1993 .
Iztok Puc ( 14 September 1966 -- 20 October 2011 ) was a Slovenian handball player , who was one of the world 's top players of the 1980s and 1990s .

Major General Ronald Dare Wilson , CBE , MC ( 3 August 1919 - 15 August 2014 ) was a senior British Army officer , author , and park warden .

Bajo Topulli ( 1868 - -1930 ) was an Albanian nationalist figure of the Albanian National Awakening .
Stan Moon ( 8 January 1927 -- 3 August 2012 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Collingwood in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .

Adolf III of Schauenburg ( German : Adolf von Schaumburg ) ( 1511 - -1556 ) was the Archbishop - Elector of Cologne from 1547 to 1556 .
Sophie of Brandenburg ( 6 June 1568 -- 7 December 1622 ) was a Princess of Brandenburg and by marriage Electress of Saxony .
Count József Zichy de Zich et Vásonkeő ( 13 November 1841 -- 11 November 1924 ) was a Hungarian politician , who served as Minister of Agriculture , Industry and Trade between 1872 and 1874 and as Minister of Public Works and Transport from 1873 to 1875 .
Zoé - Laure de Chatillon , née Delaune ( 1826 -- 1908 ) was a French painter .

Angela Brazil ( pronounced `` brazzle '' ) ( 30 November 1868 -- 13 March 1947 ) was one of the first British writers of `` modern schoolgirls ' stories '' , written from the characters ' point of view and intended primarily as entertainment rather than moral instruction .
Ferenc Keresztes - Fischer ( 18 February 1881 -- 3 March 1948 ) was a lawyer and a Hungarian politician .
Mojżesz David Kirszbraun ( 1903 or 1904 - -1942 ) was a Polish mathematician , mostly known for the Kirszbraun theorem on extensions of Lipschitz maps .
He Zhiqiang ( Chinese : 和志强 ) ( 1934 - -2007 ) was a People 's Republic of China politician .
Georg , Prince of Schaumburg - Lippe ( 10 October 1846 -- 29 April 1911 ) was a ruler of the small Principality of Schaumburg - Lippe .

Donald Forbes ( 1935 -- 12 April 2008 ) was a Scottish convicted murderer .
Eliza Davis Aria ( 1866 - -1931 ) was an English fashion writer and gossip columnist known as `` Mrs Aria '' .
Dr. Alfred Edgar Wigg ( 2 February 1857 -- 1 May 1914 ) was a prominent South Australian medical practitioner born in North Adelaide .

Cecilia Costello ( née Kelly , 24 October 1884 - -20 April 1976 ) was an English traditional singer whose repertoire of folk songs was recorded by folk music scholars in the 1950s and 1960s .

Baby John ( 1917 -- 27 January 2008 ) was a senior leader of the Kerala Revolutionary Socialist Party ( Baby John ) .
Walter Lindley ( 1852 - -1922 ) was a medical doctor in Los Angeles , California , in the 19th and 20th centuries who was known for his charitable and civic works and for founding or overseeing the development of early medical and educational institutions in Southern California .
Ida G. Athens ( 23 February 1882 -- 4 November 1977 ) was the author of a collection of poetry titled Brethren .

Hilde Spiel ( 19 October 1911 -- 30 November 1990 ) ( pseudonyms : Grace Hanshaw and Jean Lenoir ) was an Austrian writer and journalist who received numerous awards and honours .
Manuel Palafox ( born Puebla , 1886 - -1959 ) was a Mexican politician , soldier and intellectual .
Thomas Dacre , 6th Baron Dacre of Gilsland ( 27 October 1387 -- 5 January 1458 ) , was born at Naworth Castle , Cumberland , on 27 October 1387 , the son of William Dacre , 5th Baron Dacre of Gilsland , by Joan Douglas , the illegitimate daughter of Sir William Douglas , 1st Earl of Douglas .
Duncan McNeill , 1st Baron Colonsay FRSE ( 20 August 1793 -- 31 January 1874 ) was a Scottish advocate , judge and Tory politician .

Giacomo Albertolli ( 1761 -- June 6 , 1805 ) was a Swiss - born architect who was active in Italy during the Neoclassical period .
Margareta Stafhell , also called Staffhell , Stafell and Staffhell - Åkerman , ( 1720 - 1762 ) , was a Swedish Chalcography artist .

John P. Cohalan ( March 17 , 1873 Brooklyn , Kings County , New York -- 1950 ) was an American lawyer and politician from New York .

Francisco António de Araújo e Azevedo ( 21 December 1772 ; Angra - 4 April 1821 ) was a Portuguese military officer and colonial administrator .

Johann Baptist Pflug ( 13 February 1785 , Biberach an der Riß - 30 May 1866 , Biberach an der Riß ) was a German genre painter .
Yvan Delporte ( 24 June 1928 -- 5 March 2007 ) was a Belgian comics writer , and was editor - in - chief of Spirou magazine between 1955 and 1968 during a period considered by many the golden age of Franco - Belgian comics .
Rolland Fairley ( 7 December 1904 -- 10 June 1930 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with South Melbourne and Hawthorn in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
John William Weidemeyer ( b. in Fredericksburg , Virginia , 26 April 1819 ; d. 1896 ) was an author and entomologist .
Aodh Buidhe Mac an Bhaird , O.F.M. ( aka Aedh Buidh Mac an Bhaird or Hugh Ward ; c.1593 -- 8 November 1635 ) , was an Irish Franciscan friar who was a noted poet , historian and hagiographer .
Major - General Sir Henry Wheatley , 1st Baronet CB , GCH ( 1777 -- 21 March 1852 ) , was the Keeper of the Privy Purse for King William the Fourth and Queen Victoria from 1830 to 1846 .
Julius Tannen ( 16 May 1880 -- 3 January 1965 ) was a comedian -- or monologist , as those of his era were known -- who had a long and successful career in vaudeville .
Johannes of Jerusalem ( 1042 - -1119 ) , born Jehan de Vezelay , was the abbot of the monastery at Vézelay , France .
The Venerable Canon Brough Maltby ( 29 September 1826 -- 30 March 1894 ) was Archdeacon of Nottingham .
Richard Bullock Andrews ( 11 May 1823 -- 26 June 1884 ) , commonly referred to as `` Mr. Justice Andrews '' , was an Australian politician and judge .
Charles Vacher ( 1818 - -1883 ) was a British painter in watercolours .
Chester Williams Rice ( December 16 , 1888 -- 1951 ) was an electrical engineer , who was the joint inventor in 1925 of the moving coil loudspeaker along with Edward W. Kellogg .
Gabriel Acquin ( c. 1811 -- 2 October 1901 ) was known by a variety of names ;
Ernest Hinton ( 16 March 1946 -- 18 November 1999 ) was a British civil engineer and engineering professor .
Aubrey Brabazon ( 7 January 1920 - 30 September , 1996 ) was a horse racing jockey born in The Curragh , Ireland .
Cornelius Berenberg ( 1634 -- 1711 ) was a Hamburg grand burgher , merchant banker , a member of the Berenberg family , and owner of Berenberg Bank .
Vito D'Anna ( 14 October 1718 -- 13 October 1769 ) was an Italian painter , considered the most prominent painter of Palermitan rococo and one of the most important artists of Sicily .
Harold de Andrado ( 30 December 1927 -- 5 November 2004 ) was a Sri Lankan cricket writer and journalist .
Dirk Willem van Krevelen ( 8 November 1914 , Rotterdam -- 27 October 2001 , Arnhem ) was a prominent Dutch chemical engineer , coal and polymer scientist .
Thomas Darcy , 1st Earl Rivers ( c.1565 - 25 February 1640 ) was an English peer and courtier .
K. N. Ezhuthachan ( 21 May 1911 -- 28 October 1981 ) was an Indian writer and scholar of Malayalam literature .
Billie Ritchie ( 14 September 1878 -- 6 July 1921 ) was a Scottish comedian who first gained transatlantic fame as a performer for British music hall producer Fred Karno -- this , a full decade before Stan Laurel and Charlie Chaplin took a similar career path .
Walter Blandford ( 1616 in Melbury Abbas , Dorset , England -- 1675 ) was an English academic and bishop .
Edward Ward , 9th Baron Dudley and 4th Baron Ward ( 16 June 1704 -- 6 September 1731 ) was the only son of Edward Ward , 8th Baron Dudley and 3rd Baron Ward and his wife Diana daughter and heiress of Thomas Howard of Ashtead , Surrey .
Marian Bowley ( 1911 - -2002 ) was an economist and historian of economic thought .
Josef Kuchynka ( 4 August 1894 -- 9 January 1979 ) was a Czechoslovak football manager and former player of German ethnicity .
Hippocrates of Chios ( Greek : Ἱπποκράτης ὁ Χῖος ) was an ancient Greek mathematician , geometer , and astronomer , who lived c. 470 -- c. 410 BCE .
Murakuni Oyori ( 村国男依 ) ( died 676 ) was a military commander of ancient Japan , who fought in the Jinshin War as a servant of Prince Ō - ama .
Peter Woulfe ( 1727 -- 1803 ) was an Irish chemist and mineralogist .
Natalia Tułasiewicz ( 9 April 1906 -- 31 March 1945 ) was a teacher in Poznań , Poland and a leader in the Catholic lay apostolate .
John Scougal ( 1645 - -1730 ) was a Scottish painter .
Birger Ekstedt , ( 1921 - 1972 ) , was a Swedish politician ( Christian democrat ) and a priest .
Hans Haslum ( 8 November 1789 -- 5 July 1875 ) was a Norwegian farmer and elected official .
Syed Hammad Raza Shaheed ( 9 January 1970 -- 14 May 2007 ) , Additional Registrar , Supreme Court of Pakistan , was a civil servant belonging to the elite District Management Group of Central Superior Services of Pakistan .
John Renbourn ( 8 August 1944 -- 26 March 2015 ) was an English guitarist and songwriter .
Paul of Samosata ( lived from 200 to 275 AD ) was Bishop of Antioch from 260 to 268 .
Anne d'Escars de Givry ( 29 March 1546 -- 19 April 1612 ) was a French Benedictine churchman , supporter of the Ligue , and Cardinal .
Phil Furlong ( 18 February 1893 -- 27 November 1930 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Joseph Alcide Simard ( 25 October 1907 -- 21 December 1984 ) was a Ralliement créditiste member of the Canadian House of Commons .
Hoàng Tích Chù ( Từ Sơn ; 1912 in Bắc Ninh -- 20 October 2003 ) was a Vietnamese painter .
Muirgus mac Domnaill ( died 985 ) was 35th King of Uí Maine .
Thorleif Haug ( 28 September 1894 -- 12 December 1934 ) was a Norwegian skier who competed in nordic combined and cross - country .
Robert William Rankin ( 3 June 1907 -- 4 March 1942 ) was a Royal Australian Navy officer who was killed in action during the Second World War .
Saint Juvenal of Benevento ( died 132 AD ) is a 2nd - century saint honored in Narni , Italy .
Jonas Virakas ( 5 September 1905 -- 30 April 1988 ) was born in the town of Seredžius in the Kaunas district .
Thomas Grey , 2nd Earl of Stamford PC ( c. 1654 -- 31 January 1720 ) was a British peer and politician .
Baron Sándor Hatvany - Deutsch ( 1852 , Arad - 1913 , Budapest ) was a leading Hungarian industrialist and art patron .
Jordan Óge de Exeter ( fl . 1269 - -1319 ) was an Anglo - Irish knight and Sheriff of Connacht .
Cliff Bruner ( né Clifton Lafayette Bruner ; 25 April 1915 -- 25 August 2000 ) was a fiddler and bandleader of the Western Swing era of the 1930s .
Eino Viljami Panula ( 10 March 1911 -- 15 April 1912 ) was a young Finnish boy who died during the sinking of the RMS Titanic .
El - Hadji Malick Sy ( Fula : Allaaji Maalig Si , 1855 - -1922 ) was a Senegalese religious leader and teacher in the Tijaniyya Sufi malikite and ash'arite brotherhood .
Rupert I of Legnica ( Polish : Ruprecht I Legnicki ) ( 27 March 1347 -- by 12 January 1409 ) was a Duke of Legnica since 1364 until his death , and also regent over half of the Duchy of Głogów - Żagań during 1397 - -1401 .
Catherine Seaton Skirving ( Ewart ) , ( 10 March 1818 -- 7 May 1897 ) , was a noted Canadian philanthropist and volunteer .
Ernest Ewart Unwin ( 13 July 1881 -- 20 September 1944 ) was an Australian Quaker educationist .
Raj Rajeshwari Devi ( died 5 May 1806 ) , was a Queen consort and twice regent of Nepal .
David Douglas , 7th Earl of Angus ( c. 1515 - 1558 ) was a Scottish nobleman .
James Gerrard Lennon ( 1907 - -February 1976 ) , known as Gerry Lennon , was a solicitor and Irish nationalist politician .
Sir William O'Brien Lindsay KBE ( 8 October 1909 -- 20 October 1975 ) was the Chief Justice of the Sudan from 1954 to 1955 , during the period when it was administered as an Anglo - Egyptian condominium .
Mohammed al - Rudani ( Abu Abdallah Muhammad ibn Sulayman ( Muhammad ) al - Fasi ibn Tahir al - Rudani al - Susī al - Maliki al - Maghribi ) ( born ca . 1627 , died 1683 ) was an astronomer born in Taroudannt , Morocco .
Colonel Richard Meinertzhagen , CBE , DSO ( 3 March 1878 -- 17 June 1967 ) was a British soldier , intelligence officer and ornithologist .
Jon Tvedt ( 29 June 1966 -- 11 January 2009 ) was a Norwegian orienteering competitor and athlete who specialized in mountain running .
Bert Lithgow ( 19 March 1881 -- 22 April 1951 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Carlton in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hymie Jacobson , also known as Hy Jacobson ( 1895 - -1952 ) , was an American Jewish actor and composer in Yiddish vaudeville , films and theater .
Sydney Sipho Sepamla ( 1932 - 9 January 2007 ) was a contemporary South African poet and novelist .
Datu Magat Salamat ( 1550 - -1595 ) was one of the four sons of Lakan Dula .
William Macarmick ( baptised 15 September 1742 -- 20 August 1815 ) was Lieutenant - Governor of Cape Breton and a MP .
Philip Mackie ( 26 November 1918 -- 23 December 1985 ) was a British film and television screenwriter .
Falcon Stuart ( 27 March 1941 -- 27 February 2002 ) was a British photographer , retailer , filmmaker , and music producer associated with X - Ray Spex , Adam and the Ants , and Danielle Dax amongst others .
Niels Andreas Vibe ( 2 July 1759 -- 9 September 1814 ) was a Norwegian military officer and civil and royal servant .
Jacques - Nicolas Tardieu , called `` Tardieu fils '' or `` Tardieu the younger '' , ( 2 September 1716 -- 9 July 1791 ) was a French engraver .
Marcus Peducaeus Plautius Quintillus ( d. 205 ) was a two - time consul of the Roman Empire , in 177 with the future emperor Commodus as his colleague , and once again with Commodus at an unknown date .
Peter Liechti ( January 8 , 1951 -- 4 April 2014 ) was a Swiss movie director .
William Corden the Elder ( 21 January 1795 -- 18 June 1867 ) was an English portrait painter and miniaturist known for his commissions from the Royal Family in the mid nineteenth century .
Rachel Katznelson - Shazar ( Hebrew : רחל כצנלסון - שזר‎ ) , also known as Rachel Shazar , ( born 24 October 1885 , died 11 August 1975 ) was an active figure in the Zionist movement .
Erik Krag ( 13 January 1902 -- 13 May 1987 ) was a Norwegian literary historian , translator , novelist and playwright .
S.M. Banerjee ( 31 August 1919 - 26 December 1987 ) was a former Indian politician .
Sir William Young , 2nd Baronet , FRS , FSA ( December 1749 -- 10 January 1815 ) was a British colonial governor , politician and sugar plantation owner .
Stanisław Dobosiewicz ( 1910 - -2007 ) was a Polish writer and school teacher .
Antonios Kalamogdartis ( Greek : Αντώνιος Καλαμογδάρτης , 1810 - -1856 ) was a Greek revolutionary leader and a politician which he was elected many times .
Luis de Torres ( died 1493 ) , perhaps born as יוסף בן לוי העברי , Yosef ben Levi Ha - Ivri , ( `` Joseph , Son of Levi , the Hebrew '' ) was Christopher Columbus 's interpreter on his first voyage and the first person of Jewish origin to settle in America .
Vladimír Čech ( born 6 July 1951 -- 22 March 2013 ) was a Czech actor , presenter and former politician .
Sheikh Ubeydullah ( died 1883 ) ( Kurdish : Şêx Ubeydullayê Nehrî , شێخ وبه‌يدوڵاي نهری ) , also known as Sayyid Ubeydullah , was the leader of the first modern Kurdish nationalist struggle .
Thomas Bataill ( died ca . 1396 ) , of Otes in High Laver and Matching , Essex .
Donald Obeyesekere ( 1888 - -1964 ) was a prominent colonial era legislator from Ceylon .
William Anthony Furness , 2nd Viscount Furness ( 31 March 1929 -- 1 May 1995 ) was a British peer .
Sarah St. John ( December 1669 -- April 1755 ) was an English clergyman 's wife who owned , and maintained over many years , a manuscript recipe book .
Surya Prasad Upadhyaya ( 14 September 1907 - 15 July 2014 ) , a Nepalese politician .
William Ramsay Hutchison ( died 22 March 1918 ) was a Scottish rugby union player .
Jacques - Louis Soret ( 30 June 1827 -- 13 May 1890 ) was a Swiss chemist who in 1878 , along with Marc Delafontaine , first observed holmium spectroscopically .
Ras Prince Monolulu ( 26 October 1881 -- 14 February 1965 ) , whose real name was Peter Carl Mackay ( or McKay ) , was a horse - racing tipster , and something of an institution on the British racing scene from the 1920s until the time of his death .
Count Fyodor Ivanovich Tolstoy ( Russian : Фёдор Ива́нович Толсто́й ) , also known as the `` American '' ( Американец ) ( 17 February 1782 -- 5 November 1846 ) was a Russian nobleman from the well - known Tolstoy family .
Jorge Lankenau Rocha ( 16 April 1944 -- 16 June 2012 ) was a Mexican banker and businessman who was arrested in 1997 on fraud and tax evasion charges for shifting $ 179 million to the Cayman Islands and Paraguay and served eight years in prison .
Joseph - Octave Villeneuve ( 4 March 1836 -- 27 June 1901 ) was a Canadian businessman , provincial politician , and senator .
Carl August Adlersparre ( 7 June 1810 Kristinehamn Municipality , Värmland - 5 May 1862 Stockholm ) was a Swedish count ( 1835 ) , chamberlain ( 1838 ) , poet , novelist and historian .
Napoleone Nani ( Venice 1841- Verona , 1899 ) was an Italian painter , active in Venice , where he became professor of the Accademia di Belle Arti .
Solomon Winter , Hungarian philanthropist ; born in the county of Zips , Hungary , in 1778 ; died at Hunsdorf , in the same county , February 24 , 1859 , after laboring for sixty years for the advancement of the Jewish race in his locality .
Li Baiyao ( simplified Chinese : 李百药 ; traditional Chinese : 李百藥 ) ( 564 - -647 ) , courtesy name Zhonggui ( 重規 ) , formally Viscount Kang of Anping ( 安平康子 ) , was a Chinese historian and an official during the Chinese dynasties Sui Dynasty and Tang Dynasty .
Finghin MacCarthy Reagh ( Irish : Fínghin Mac Carthaigh Riabhach ) was the 8th Prince of Carbery from 1477 to his death in 1505 .
Lucas Moreira Neves O.P. ( 16 September 1925 -- 8 September 2002 ) was a Brazilian Cardinal Bishop and Prefect of the Congregation for Bishops .
Mojola Agbebi ( 1860 - -1917 ) was a Nigerian Yoruba Baptist minister .
James Orrock RI ( 1829 -- 10 May 1913 ) , was a prominent Scottish collector of art and oriental ceramics , illustrator and landscape watercolourist .
Oddvar Berrefjord ( born 20 March 1918 in Vardø , died 25 November 1999 ) was a Norwegian jurist and politician for the Labour Party .
Jozef Božetech Klemens ( 8 March 1817 in Liptovský Mikuláš -- 17 January 1883 in Vienna ) was a Slovakian portrait painter , sculptor , photographer , inventor and naturalist .
Jacob Holm ( 29 September 1770 -- 3 August 1845 ) was a Danish industrialist , ship owner and merchant .
Ian Roger Vanderfield AO OBE ( 1928 -- 25 September 2008 ) was an Australian doctor , and a rugby union referee and administrator .
Daniel Waggoner ( 1828 - 1902 ) was an early American settler and rancher in Texas .
Paul Augustin Mayer , OSB ( 23 May 1911 -- 30 April 2010 ) was a German Cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church .
Jennett Humphreys ( 1829/30 - -1917 ) was an English author , poet , and contributor to major reference works .
Sophie de Choiseul - Gouffier ( Lithuanian : Sofija Tyzenhauzaitė de Šuazel - Gufjė ; 1790 -- 28 May 1878 ) was a Lithuanian novelist .
John Smith alias Dyer ( 1498/1499 - 1571 ) , of Ipswich , Suffolk , was an English politician .
Adrian Henri ( 10 April 1932 -- 20 December 2000 ) was a British poet and painter best remembered as the founder of poetry - rock group the Liverpool Scene and as one of three poets in the best - selling anthology The Mersey Sound , along with Brian Patten and Roger McGough .
John Sargeaunt ( 1857 - -1922 ) was a noted classical scholar and schoolmaster of whom The Times wrote : `` he will be long remembered for his profound scholarship and his genius as a teacher '' .
Sir William Sterndale Bennett ( 13 April 1816 -- 1 February 1875 ) was an English composer , pianist , conductor and music educator .
Gabriel Nicolas de la Reynie ( 1625 -- 14 June 1709 ) is considered to be the founder of the first modern police force .
Martha Foley ( 1897 - -1977 ) cofounded Story magazine in 1931 with her husband Whit Burnett .
Kristian Friis Petersen ( 17 September 1867 -- 5 April 1932 ) was the Norwegian Minister of Social Affairs 1914 - 1916 and Minister of Trade 1916 - 1919 .
Cormac Ó Comáin ( aka Cormac Dall , Blind Cormac , Cormac Common ) , Irish seanchai , May 1703 -- 1813 .
Ferchar mac Connaid was king of Dál Riata ( in modern Scotland ) from about 642 until 650 .
Les Eyre ( 7 January 1922 -- 19 November 1991 ) was a footballer who was born in Ilkeston , Derbyshire , England and played for Norwich City .
Karl Gurakuqi ( 1895 - 1971 ) was an Albanian linguist and folklorist .
Thomas Graham Balfour ( 18 March 1813 -- 17 January 1891 ) was a Scottish physician noted for his work with medical statistics , and a member of Florence Nightingale 's inner circle .
Gaspard Jean - Baptiste Brunet ( 14 June 1734 -- 15 November 1793 ) commanded the French Army of Italy during the French Revolutionary Wars and was executed during the Reign of Terror .
Kittur Chennamma ( 23 October 1778 -- 21 February 1829 ) was the Queen of Kittur , a princely state in South India .
Luigi Villari ( 1876 - -1959 ) was an Italian historian , traveler and diplomat .
Maria Erhart , née Kirner ( 1944 -- 2 September 2011 ) , was an Austrian international bridge player , who had the rare distinction of playing for her country 's Open team as well as for the Women 's team .
Octavius Eaden ( born 15 December 1808 at Cambridge ; died 1832 at Cambridge ) was an English cricketer who was associated with Cambridge Town Club and made his first - class debut in 1827 .
Cornelia Toppen , known as Keet Zwenke , ( 1730 , Beekbergen - 6 March 1800 , Rotterdam ) , was a Dutch Orangist and the instigator of the 1784 riots of Rotterdam .
Guy Wharton ( 5 December 1916 , Darfield , England -- 1990 ) was a professional footballer who played as a wing half .
Tiloukaikt ( also Tilokaikt or Teelonkike ) ( unknown - 1850 ) was a Native American leader of the Cayuse tribe in the northwestern United States .
Herbert Marvin Ohlman ( 1927 - -2002 ) is the inventor of permutation indexing , or Permuterm and is one of the pioneers of Information Science and Technology .
Yves Blais ( June 5 , 1931 -- November 22 , 1998 ) was a politician in the Canadian province of Quebec .
Hugh Macdonald Sinclair , FRCP ( 4 February 1910 -- 22 June 1990 ) was a doctor , medical researcher , and expert in human nutrition .
Clifford McLaglen ( 15 June 1892 -- 9 September 1978 ) was a Stepney , London - born British film actor .
John Fortune ( born John C. Wood ; 30 June 1939 -- 31 December 2013 ) was an English satirist , comedian , writer , and actor , best known for his work with John Bird and Rory Bremner on the TV series Bremner , Bird and Fortune .
Henry C. Pearson ( October 8 , 1914 -- December 3 , 2006 ) was an American abstract and modernist painter .
Arthur Roy Clapham , CBE FRS ( 24 May 1904 -- 18 December 1990 ) , was a British botanist .
John Ponet ( c. 1514 -- August 1556 ) , sometimes spelled John Poynet , was an English Protestant churchman and controversial writer , the Bishop of Winchester and Marian exile .
Adib Masud Hassan Rizvi ( 1893 - 1975 ) was an Indian author and a scholar of Urdu literature .
Konstantinos Kollias ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Κόλλιας ) ( 1901 -- 13 July 1998 ) was a former Greek Attorney General who was proclaimed Prime Minister by the Greek military junta of 1967 - -74 that overthrew Panagiotis Kanellopoulos ' government on 21 April 1967 .
Edgar Kendall Taylor CBE , FRCM , Hon FRAM ( 27 July 1905 -- 5 December 1999 ) was a British pianist , who had an international career as a solo concert pianist .
Elizabeth Greenleaf Pattee ( 1893 - -1991 ) was an American architect , landscape architect , and architecture professor in the Northeast whose career spanned a half century .
Suitbert Bäumer ( 28 March 1845 -- 12 August 1894 ) was a Benedictine monk and historian of the Breviary and one of the most scholarly patrologists of the nineteenth century .
John Rhea Barton ( April 1794 , Lancaster , Pennsylvania -- 1 January 1871 , Philadelphia ) was an American orthopedic surgeon remembered for describing Barton 's fracture .
Tang Caichang ( Chinese : 唐才常 ; pinyin : Táng Cáicháng ; 1867 -- 22 August 1900 ) was a late Qing reformer and political activist .
Rosalie Loveling ( 20 March 1834 -- 4 May 1875 ) was a Flemish author of poetry , novels and essays .
Elisha Johnson ( 1785 - -1866 ) was an engineer and early resident of Rochester , New York .
Sir Lewis Bellenden of Auchnole and Broughton , Knt . , ( c. 1552 - 27 August 1591 , Edinburgh ) , knighted about 1577 , was the eldest son of his father Sir John Bellenden of Auchnole & Broughton , whom he succeeded as Lord Justice Clerk on 15 March 1577 .
Barnet Burns ( November 1805 -- 26 December 1860 ) was an English sailor , trader , and showman who became one of the first Europeans to live as a Pākehā Māori and to receive the full Māori facial tattoo .
Antonio Rubino ( 15 May 1880 -- 1 July 1964 ) was an Italian illustrator , cartoonist , animation director , screenwriter , playwright , author and poet .
Robbie Millar ( 26 April 1967 -- 13 August 2005 ) was a head chef and restaurateur from Ballycarry in County Antrim , Northern Ireland .
Jules Marchal ( 1924 - 21 June 2003 ) was a Belgian diplomat and historian , who wrote extensively on the history of colonial exploitation in the Belgian Congo .
Bennett Scott ( 1875 - -1930 ) was a writer of music hall songs .
Meduri Nageswara Rao ( 31 March 1910 -- 13 January 1998 ) was an Indian independence activist , politician and Member of Parliament .
Gustaf Storgårds ( 11 December 1869 in Lapinjärvi -- 11 November 1945 ) was a Finnish Lutheran clergyman and politician .
Vsevolod I Svyatoslavich ( Russian : Всеволод Святославич ) , also known as Vsevolod Aurochs ( Russian : Буй-тур ) and Vsevolod the Fierce ( died 1196 ) , was a Prince of Kursk and Prince of Trubchevsk from a Rurikid family in Kievan Rus .
Sophiya Haque ( 14 June 1971 -- 17 January 2013 ) was an English actress , singer , video jockey and dancer .
Lucretia Magnusdotter ( Gyllenhielm ) ( 1562 - 1624 ) , was the illegitimate daughter of the Swedish prince Magnus , Duke of Östergötland , and Valborg Eriksdotter .
Li Xiaogong ( 591 - -640 ) , posthumously known as Prince Yuan of Hejian , often referred to by his earlier title as the Prince of Zhao Commandery , was an imperial prince and general of the Tang dynasty .
Thomas Shine , second Bishop of Middlesbrough , died at the Sisters of Mercy Nursing Home at Whitby on 22 November , 1955 , in his 84th year .
Gunning S. Bedford ( 1806 - 5 September 1870 ) was a medical writer , teacher and founder of the United States ' first obstetrical clinic for those too poor to pay a doctor 's fee .
William John Parry ( 28 March 1842 - 1927 ) was a Welsh businessman , politician and author .
Philip Thorp ( 6 May 1911 -- December 2006 ) was an English cricketer who played two first - class games for Worcestershire in 1935 .
Wenceslaus II , Duke of Opava - Ratibor ( also known as Wenceslaus I of Ratibor and Krnov ; Czech : Václav IV . Ratibořský ; c. 1405 -- 29 October 1456 ) was a member of the Opavian branch of the Přemyslid dynasty .
Martin Stephani ( 2 November 1915 -- 9 June 1983 ) was a German conductor and professor .
Frank Hall Crane ( 1 January 1873 -- 1 September 1948 ) was an American stage and film actor and director .
Mícheál Ó Siochfhradha ( 1900 - -1986 ; Irish pronunciation : ( mʲiːˈhaːl̪ˠ oː ʃʊˈxɾˠuː ) ) , and Pádraig ( An Seabhac ) Ó Siochfhradha were brothers who were writers , teachers and Irish language storytellers , from County Kerry , Ireland .
Les Mitchell ( 15 April 1891 -- 5 August 1957 ) was a former Australian rules footballer who played with Melbourne in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Hendrik Trajectinus , Count of Solms , ( b. 1636 in Utrecht -- 13 July 1693 in Neerwinden ) was a Dutch lieutenant - general .
Hilaire Vanbiervliet ( 29 October 1890 - -1981 ) was a Belgian painter belonging to the Flemish expressionists .
Sir William Chichele Plowden KCSI ( 1832 -- 4 September 1915 ) was a Civil Servant and Member of the Legislative Council in India , and subsequently a Liberal politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1886 to 1892 .
Tyronne Fernando PC ( Sinhala:ටිරොන් ෆර්නැන්ඩො ) ( 8 August 1941 -- 26 February 2008 ) was a Sri Lankan politician who served as Foreign Minister from 2001 until 2004 .
Gwen Lux Creighton ( professionally Gwen Lux , 1908 - -1987 ) was among America 's pioneer women sculptors ( McBrien 2004 ) .
Valivitta Thevar ( 1889 - -1927 ) was an Indian social reformer and teacher .
Basil the Copper Hand ( Greek : Βασίλειος ὁ Χαλκόχειρ , died c. 932 ) was a Byzantine rebel leader active in Bithynia in the 920s and early 930s .
John Spenser ( 1559 - -1614 ) was an English academic , president of Corpus Christi College , Oxford .
Jack Penn ( 14 August 1909 -- 27 November 1996 ) , M.B. , Ch . B. , F.R.C.S.(E. ) .
James J. Metcalfe ( Sept 16 , 1906 - March 1960 ) was an American poet whose `` Daily Poem Portraits '' were published in more than 100 United States newspapers during the 1940s and 1950s .
`` Spearthrower Owl '' ( or Atlatl Cauac ) ( ? -- 439 AD ) is the name commonly given to a Mesoamerican personage from the Early Classic period , who is identified in Maya inscriptions and iconography .
Ludwig Hupfeld ( 26 November 1864 - 8 October 1949 ) was a musical instrument maker and industrialist .
James Mudie ( 1779 - -1852 ) was a Scottish - born free settler of Australia who became an officer of marines , large landowner , and author .
Ralph Waldo Tyler ( 1860 - -1921 ) was an African - American journalist , war correspondent , government official , and race man .
James Webber was the Dean of Ripon from 1828 until his death on 3 September 1847 .
Homer G. Balcom ( 1870 - -1938 ) was a structural engineer who was responsible for designing the Empire State Building .
Livia della Rovere ( 16 December 1585 -- 6 July 1641 ) was an Italian noblewoman of the House of della Rovere and a Duchess of Urbino .
William West Durant ( 1850 -- 1934 ) was a designer and developer of camps in the Adirondack Great Camp style , including Camp Uncas , Camp Pine Knot and Sagamore Camp which are National Historic Landmarks .
Einar Nerman ( 6 October 1888 in Norrköping -- 1983 ) was a Swedish artist .
Andreas Lauritz Thune ( 9 April 1848 -- 20 April 1920 ) was a Norwegian engineer and businessman , associated with the company Thunes Mekaniske Værksted .
Bernard O'Higgins ( ? --1564 ) was an Irish Roman Catholic bishop .
Ruaidrí Ua Conchobair ( died 1118 ) ( anglicised Roderic O'Connor ) , called Ruaidrí na Saide Buide ( Ruaidrí of the Yellow Birch ) was King of Connacht , perhaps twice .
Ammar Abadah Nasser al - Wa'eli ( Arabic : ) ( 1977 - 3 June 2011 , born in Yemen ) became wanted in 2002 , by the United States Department of Justice 's FBI , which was then seeking information about his identity and whereabouts .
Eben Ezra Roberts ( 1866 - -1943 ) was an American architect known for his work in the early modern Prairie style , pioneered by Frank Lloyd Wright , as well as other traditional residential styles .
Gaspard Rigaud ( 1 June 1661 - 28 March 1705 ) was a French painter and portraitist .
Prithivi Nath Kaul Bamzai ( 1910 - -2007 ) was a Kashmiri scholar and historian who wrote several books on the history of Kashmir and related topics .
Sir William Skeffington ( c. 1465 -- 31 December 1535 ) , was a Lord Deputy of Ireland .
Murchadh Reagh Ó Madadhan , Chief of Síol Anmchadha , died 1475 .
Dursun Aksoy was the Turkish administrative attaché in Brussels , Belgium , who was assassinated in 1983 .
Chitrananda Abeysekera ( 1930 - -1992 ) was a veteran broadcaster , poet , writer and an administrator .
Theodore de Lemos ( 1850 , Holstein , German Confederation -- 12 April 1909 , New York City , New York , United States ) , son of Hermann and Maria Grothe De Lemos of Holstein , was an architect .
To Lua Foto ( died 614 ) was Abbot of Clonmacnoise .
Seán Ó Cionnaith ( born July 1938 near Ballinasloe , County Galway , died 16 February 2003 in Dublin ) was an Irish socialist republican politician , and a prominent member of The Workers ' Party .
Chandra Gurung ( died 23 September 2006 ) , also Chandra Prasad Gurung , was a leader in conservation and sustainable field of Nepal .
Arthur Spry ( 4 February 1612 - 17 September 1685 ) was an English politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1660 to 1679 .
Henry Percy , 3rd Earl of Northumberland , ( 25 July 1421 -- 29 March 1461 ) was an English magnate .
Joseph Whiting Stock ( January 30 , 1815 -- 1855 ) was an American painter known for his portraits , miniatures , and landscape paintings , many of which he did on commission .
Józef Nawrot ( 24 September 1906 -- 24 September 1982 ) was a Polish international footballer who played for the national team during the 1920s and 1930s .
Johann Christoph Pepusch ( 1667 -- 20 July 1752 ) , also known as John Christopher Pepusch and Dr Pepusch , was a German - born composer who spent most of his working life in England .
Lulama Masikazana ( 6 February 1973 -- 7 October 2011 ) was a South African cricketer who played first - class cricket as a wicketkeeper for Eastern Province from 1993 to 2000 .
Ustad Abed Hossain Khan ( 1929 -- 1996 ) was a Bangladeshi musician , music composer and music director .
Alexander Aaronsohn ( Hebrew : אלכסנדר אהרנסון‎ ; Romania , 1888 - -Palestine , 1948 ) was an author and activist who wrote about the plight of people living in Palestine ( now Israel ) in his book , With the Turks in Palestine .
Charles Dadant ( 20 May 1817 -- 26 July 1902 ) was a French - American beekeeper .
James Maina Boi ( 4 April 1954 -- 15 July 2004 ) was a Kenyan middle distance runner .
Lindsay Smail ( 15 September 1910 -- 3 March 1988 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Albert Benjamin Prescott ( 1832 - 1905 ) was an American chemist , born in Hastings , New York .
Sita Chan ( Chinese : 陳僖儀 , 10 March 1987 -- 17 April 2013 ) was a Hong Kong Cantopop singer and actress .
Pietro Pintor ( 1880 -- 7 December 1940 ) was an Italian general during World War II . Pintor was the uncle of the antifascist journalist Giaime Pintor .
Edmond de Caillou or Raymond de Caillou , ( also spelt Calhou , Calhau , Cailow etc.)(d . 1316 ) was a Gascon soldier who fought during the First War of Scottish Independence .
Thomas Penrose ( 1742 - -1779 ) was an English cleric and poet .
Fergus Crawford ( 1933 - -1985 ) was an Irish professional footballer .
Konstantinos Kozanitas ( Greek : Κωνσταντίνος Κοζανιτάς , 1880 -- 1954 ) was a Greek gymnast .
Ivor Frederick Wentworth Schofield CMG ( 5 July 1904 - 25 September 1979 ) was a British colonial administrator in West Africa .
Charles Silvester Horne ( 1865 - -1914 ) was a late 19th century and early 20th century Congregationalist minister , who additionally served as Liberal M.P. for Ipswich , and was a noted orator .
Wilhelm Eduard Brodtbeck ( 25 September 1873 in Liestal - 12 April 1957 , in Liestal ) was a famous Swiss architect from Liestal canton Basel - Country .
Saint Mochta , Mochtae , or Mahew ( died 20 August 535 ) , in Latin sources Maucteus or Mauchteus , was the last surviving disciple of St. Patrick .
Muriki or Maurice Spata ( Albanian : Muriq Shpata , Greek : Μουρίκης Σπάτας ; fl . 1399 - -1414 ) was the ruler of Arta from late 1399/early 1400 until his death in 1414 or 1415 .
Ah Ken ( fl . 1858 - -1896 ) was a Chinese American businessman and popular figure in Chinatown , Manhattan during the mid - to late 19th century .
Hubert Le Blon ( 21 March 1874 -- 2 April 1910 ) was a French automobilist and pioneer aviator .
Luise Marie of the Palatinate ( Luise Marie von der Plafz ; 23 July 1647 -- 11 March 1679 ) was a Bavarian princess who married Charles Theodore , the Prince ( Fürst ) of Salm - Salm .
Elicius Benedict Bernard Placid Quirk Carrington Dwyer ( 3 May 1876 -- 19 October 1912 ) , better known as E. B. Dwyer , was an Australian cricketer who played first - class cricket in England for Sussex County Cricket Club .
Iwo Odrowąż ( died 21 August 1229 ) was a medieval Polish humanist , statesman , and bishop .
Ludwig Wrede ( 28 October 1894 -- 1 January 1965 ) was an Austrian figure skater in both pairs and singles skating .
Ketevan Pkheidze ( Georgian : ქეთევან ფხეიძე ; died 1744 ) was a Georgian princess of the family of Pkheidze ( also known as Mkheidze ) hailing from Imereti .
Sir Charles Tyrrell Giles KC ( 2 February 1850 -- 16 January 1940 ) , was a British lawyer and Conservative politician who represented Wisbech .
Otto Wilhelm Sonder ( 18 June 1812 , Bad Oldesloe -- 21 November 1881 ) was a German botanist and pharmacist who was a native of Holstein .
T G Purvis ( 12 April 1861 -- 17 January 1933 ) was a British marine artist .
Sir John Ingilby , 1st Baronet FRS ( 9 May 1758 -- 13 May 1815 ) of Ripley Castle , Yorkshire was a British politician .
Takeshi Taketsuru ( Japanese : 竹鶴威 , 6 March 1924 -- 17 December 2014 ) was a Japanese whisky distiller .
Comes Bonifacius ( anglicized as Count Boniface ) ( died 432 ) was a Roman general and governor of the Diocese of Africa .
Aquila Walsh ( 15 May 1823 -- 6 March 1885 ) was a Canadian civil engineer , politician , and civil servant .
Anthony Bleecker ( October 1770 -- 13 March 1827 ) was a lawyer and author who was a friend of Washington Irving and William Cullen Bryant .
Count Ignazio Alessandro Cozio di Salabue ( 1755 - -1840 ) was an Italian count known as the first great connoisseur and collector of violins .
Åsa Solberg Iversen ( born 7 April 1929 in Overhalla , Nord - Trøndelag , died 3 February 2009 in Fredrikstad ) was a Norwegian politician ( Ap ) .
Nguyễn Nhạc ( 阮岳 , died 1793 ) was the founder of the Tây Sơn Dynasty , reigning from 1778 to 1793 .
Nazzareno Orlandi ( May 29 , 1861 in Ascoli Piceno , Italy -- 1952 in Buenos Aires , Argentina ) was an Italian - Argentine painter .
Salvatore di Pietro , S.J. , ( 15 June 1830 -- 23 August 1898 ) was an Italian Bishop in the Catholic Church .
Maciej Płażyński ( Polish pronunciation : ( ˈmatɕɛj pwaˈʐɨɲskʲi ) ; 10 February 1958 -- 10 April 2010 ) was a Polish liberal - conservative politician .
Alain Le Bussy ( 1947 -- 14 October 2010 ) was a prolific Belgian author of science fiction who won the Prix Rosny - Aîné in 1993 for his novel Deltas .
Jay Appleton ( 1919 -- 27 April 2015 ) was a British geographer who proposed ' habitat theory ' and advanced the notion of ' prospect - refuge ' .
Shalva Maglakelidze ( also spelled as Maghlakelidze ; Georgian : შალვა მაღლაკელიძე , German : Schalwa Maglakelidse , French : Chalva Maglakelidzé ) ( 1893 - -1976 ) was a Georgian jurist , politician and military commander .
Nicholas Battely ( 1648 - 1704 ) was an English clergyman and antiquary , editor of William Somner 's Cantuaria Sacra and brother of John Battely .
Geng Yan ( Chinese : 耿弇 ; 3 - -58 AD ) was a Chinese general of the Eastern Han Dynasty .
Robert Garrison was an American sculptor ( May 30 , 1895 -- 1943 ) .
Józef Teodorowicz ( Armenian : Յովսէփ Թէոֆիլ Թէոդորովիչ ; 25 August 1864 -- 4 December 1938 ) was the last Armenian Catholic Archbishop of Lviv .
Michael Alfred Rufus Isaacs , 3rd Marquess of Reading ( 1916 - 1980 ) was an English aristocrat and banker .
Ivan Vasilievich Argamakov ( Russian : Иван Васильевич Аргамаков ; 1763 - 1834 ) was a commander of the Imperial Russian Army during the Napoleonic Wars .
Álvaro Rodríguez ( fl . 1129 - -1166 , died January 1167 ) was a Galician magnate during the reigns of Alfonso VII and Ferdinand II . Álvaro was the son of Rodrigo Vélaz and Urraca Álvarez , perhaps a daughter of Álvar Fáñez and Mayor Pérez , daughter of Pedro Ansúrez .
Agustín Viesca ( 1790 - -1845 ) was a governor of the Mexican state of Coahuila y Tejas in 1835 .
William Drummond , 4th Viscount Strathallan ( 1690 -- 16 April 1746 ) was a Scottish Jacobite army officer and fourth son of Sir John Drummond of Machany and Margaret , daughter of Sir William Stewart of Innernytie .
Bartolomé Baca ( c. 1767 -- 30 April 1834 ) was Governor of the territory of Santa Fe de Nuevo México ( New Mexico ) from August 1823 until September 1825 .
Richard Peek ( 3 October 1782 - 7 March 1867 ) was a tea merchant in London from modest beginnings in Loddiswell in Devon .
Robert Bowyer ( /ˈboʊjər/ ; bap . 18 June 1758 -- 4 June 1834 ) was a British miniature painter and publisher .
Gaetano Cara ( 1803 -- 1877 ) was an Italian archaeologist and naturalist primarily interested in ornithology .
Veliyan Parushev Mitev ( Bulgarian : Велиян Пaрушев Митев ) ( 20 March 1968 - 29 January 2013 ) was a Bulgarian footballer .
Darrell Ware ( 1906 - 1944 ) was an American screenwriter and film producer .
Koca Musa Pasha ( usually referred to as just Musa Pasha ; died 22 January 1647 , near Euboea ) was an Ottoman statesman .
Adrian Nicholas ( 4 March 1962 -- 17 September 2005 ) was a British skydiver who completed more than 8,000 jumps in 30 countries .
Jack Hylton ( 2 July 1892 -- 29 January 1965 ) was an English band leader and impresario who rose to prominence during the British dance band era .
Jean - Pierre Sydler ( 1921 - 1988 ) was a Swiss mathematician and a librarian , well known for his work in geometry , most notably on Hilbert 's third problem .
Gyula Válent ( 27 September 1926 -- 10 September 2010 ) is a Hungarian swimmer who won a silver medal in the 100 m backstroke at the 1947 European Aquatics Championships .
Jehan Rajab ( neé Welborne , 1934 -- 5 April 2015 ) was a Brazil - born Kuwaiti author of British origin .
Olivier Le Jeune ( buried 10 May 1654 ) was the first recorded slave purchased in New France .
Frederic Lord ( 15 November 1886 -- 15 August 1945 ) was an English choral conductor , organist , composer , and music educator .
Samuel Shelley ( 1750 - -1808 ) was an English miniaturist and watercolour painter .
Julian Rix ( 1850 - -1903 ) was an American landscape artist .
Joachim Thibault de Courville ( died 1581 ) was a French composer , singer , lutenist , and player of the lyre , of the late Renaissance .
Wompatuck ( died 1669 ) , known to English settlers as Josiah Sagamore , was a leader of the Mattakeesett tribe of the Massachusetts Indians .
Silvester of Valdiseve ( or Valdisieve ) ( 1278 - -1348 ) was a medieval monk who is not yet recognized as a saint by the Roman Catholic Church , but rather a Blessed .
Enzo Martinelli ( 11 November 1911 -- 27 August 1999 ) was an Italian mathematician , working in the theory of functions of several complex variables : he is best known for his work on the theory of integral representations for holomorphic functions of several variables , notably for discovering the Bochner--
Rev. James Noyes ( born 1608 , Wiltshire , England -- died 22 October 1656 , Newbury , Massachusetts Bay Colony , 22 October 1656 ) was an English clergyman who emigrated to Massachusetts .
George Gordon Belt ( 1828 - -1869 ) , soldier , 49er , businessman , judge , Confederate sympathizer who organized the Mason Henry Gang in California during the American Civil War .
Edward Vansittart Neale , BA , MA ( 2 April 1810 -- 16 September 1892 ) , was an English barrister , co - operator and Christian Socialist .
Théophile Rudolphe Studer ( 27 November 1845 -- 12 February 1922 ) was a Swiss ornithologist and marine biologist .
Viola Grosvenor , Duchess of Westminster ( 10 June 1912 -- 3 May 1987 ) was the wife of Robert Grosvenor , 5th Duke of Westminster .
Frank Damrosch , Jr. ( 1888 - 1966 ) was an Episcopal priest , author , and writer .
Mahendra Lal Wadhwa ( October 2 , 1900 -- August 1988 ) was an Indian freedom fighter from the town of Muzafargarh .
William S. Kaufman ( 1849 - -1916 ) was an American architect known for designing a number of public buildings , primarily in Indiana and Ohio .
Harry Gorodetzer ( 1914 - -2002 ) was a cellist for the Philadelphia Orchestra for 50 seasons during a period in which the orchestra received world - wide acclaim for its `` Philadelphia Sound '' .
Paul Walden ( 6 June 1964 -- 28 December 2015 ) , commonly known as Guru Josh , was a Jersey musician , active in the British post - acid house scene , best known for his début single `` Infinity '' , initially released in 1989 on Walden 's record label , Infinity Records .
John Ortell Kingston ( May 19 , 1919 -- August 25 , 1987 ) was the leader of the Latter Day Church of Christ of Mormon fundamentalists in Davis County , Utah , from 1948 until his death in 1987 .
Roger Anger ( 24 March 1923 -- 15 January 2008 ) was a French architect He was the architect on the Auroville project , designed by Mirra Alfassa and endorsed by UNESCO and the Government of India .
Leif Longum ( 19 November 1927 -- 5 May 1997 ) was a Norwegian essayist and literary researcher .
Charles Flaxman ( 25 December 1806 -- November 1869 ) was employed by George Angas as his chief clerk .
Alan Randall ( 24 April 1925 -- 24 May 2000 ) was an Australian rules footballer who played with Essendon in the Victorian Football League ( VFL ) .
Isidore of Miletus ( Greek : Ἰσίδωρος ὁ Μιλήσιος ) was one of the two main Byzantine Greek architects ( Anthemius of Tralles was the other ) that Emperor Justinian I commissioned to design the church of Hagia Sophia in Constantinople from 532 - 537 .
Maximilien Chaudoir , or Maximilien , baron de Chaudoir , ( 12 September 1816 , Ivnitsa , near Zhitomir - 6 May 1881 , Amélie - les - Bains ) was a Russian entomologist .
Haidar Malik Chadurah ( died 1627 ) was an administrator , and soldier in Kashmir in the service of Salim Nuruddin Jahangir , the fourth Mughal Emperor from 1605 until his death in 1627 .

Taishi Ci ( 166 - -206 ) , courtesy name Ziyi , was a military general who lived in the late Eastern Han Dynasty .
