Commonwealth Televiews was a Canadian documentary television series which aired on CBC Television from 1957 to 1958 .
Polygrapha is a Neotropical nymphalid butterfly genus in the subfamily Charaxinae .
Lipoptena is a genus of Hippoboscidae , known as louse flies or keds .
Calandrella is a genus of lark in the Alaudidae family .
The Clear Creek gambusia ( Gambusia heterochir ) is a species of fish in the Poeciliidae family endemic to the United States , particularly Menard County , Texas .
The Sphecinae is a subfamily of the digger wasp family Sphecidae .
Pegoplata , sometimes known as Nupedia , is a genus of flies within the family Anthomyiidae .
Caprella is a large genus of skeleton shrimps belonging to the subfamily Caprellinae of the family Caprellidae .
The Valley Carpenter Bee , Xylocopa varipuncta , is one of three species of carpenter bee found from western New Mexico to southern California .
The Isla De La Juventud tree hutia or southern hutia ( Mysateles meridionalis ) is a species of rodent in the family Capromyidae .
Turanovia incompleta is an extinct species of earwigs , in the genus Turanovia , the family Protodiplatyidae , the suborder Archidermaptera , and the order Dermaptera .
Cynognathus is an extinct genus of large - bodied cynodont therapsid that lived in the Early and Middle Triassic .
Pearcea is a South American genus of 17 species of tropical herbs in the flowering plant family Gesneriaceae .
Crawfordina is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Cancellariidae , the nutmeg snails .
Pseudepidalea is a genus of toads in the family Bufonidae , the true toads .
The Sonora chub ( Gila ditaenia ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Labenopimplinae are an extinct subfamily of the parasitic wasp family Ichneumonidae .
Comactinia is a genus of crinoids , characteristically with 10 arms , belonging to the family Comasteridae .
Perrottetia is a genus of flowering plants in the family Dipentodontaceae described as a family in 1824 .
The family Campanulaceae ( also bellflower family ) , of the order Asterales , contains nearly 2400 species in 84 genera of herbaceous plants , shrubs , and rarely small trees , often with milky non - toxic sap .
Equisetum ( /ˌɛkwᵻˈsiːtəm/ ; horsetail , snake grass , puzzlegrass ) is the only living genus in Equisetaceae , a family of vascular plants that reproduce by spores rather than seeds .
Sparnodus is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish in the family Sparidae .
Kloss 's squirrel or Kloss squirrel ( Callosciurus albescens ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Eupolypods II is a clade of ferns in the order Polypodiales , under the class Polypodiopsida .
The Skomer vole ( Myodes glareolus skomerensis ) is a subspecies of bank vole endemic to the island of Skomer , off the west coast of Wales .
The Indian vulture ( Gyps indicus ) is an Old World vulture and is closely related to the griffon vulture , G. fulvus .
Clytopsis dimidiaticornis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Clytopsis .
Halotthia is a genus of fungi in the family Zopfiaceae ; according to the 2007 Outline of Ascomycota , the placement in this family is uncertain .
Zenostephanus is true ammonite genus from the lower part of the Upper Jurassic of eastern England and Scotland belonging to the ammonitid family , Perisphinctidae .
Tropaeolum speciosum ( common names flame flower and flame nasturtium ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Tropaeolaceae native to Chile , where it is known locally as coralito , quintralito , or voqui .
Vitagonum apterum is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Vitagonum .
Allison 's anole ( Anolis allisoni ) , also known as the blue - headed anole , is a species of anole .
Cyanopica is a genus of magpie in the family Corvidae .
The São Paulo tyrannulet ( Phylloscartes paulista ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Cimolodontidae is a family of fossil mammals within the extinct order Multituberculata .
The Hunter Island penguin ( Tasidyptes hunteri ) is an extinct penguin , subfossil remains of which were found in a Holocene Aboriginal midden at Stockyard Site on Hunter Island , in Bass Strait 5 km off the western end of the north coast of Tasmania , Australia .
Russalpia is a genus of Orthoptera which belongs to the Acrididae family .
Pellacalyx is a genus of trees in the family Rhizophoraceae .
Vaccinioideae is a flowering - plant subfamily in the family Ericaceae .
Poss 's scorpionfish , Scorpaenopsis possi , is a scorpionfish from the Indo - Pacific .
Chaetogenys straneoi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Chaetogenys .
Arcticodactylus is a genus of basal pterosaur living during the Late Triassic in the area of present Greenland .
Fungia is a genus of mushroom , disc or plate corals in the family Fungiidae .
The Cossinae are the nominate subfamily of the Cossidae ( carpenter or goat moths ) .
Brumback 's night monkey ( Aotus brumbacki ) is a species of night monkey found in Colombia .
Myrmeocorus allodapus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Myrmeocorus .
The Gundlach 's hawk ( Accipiter gundlachi ) is a species of bird of prey in the Accipitridae family .
Mazapilitinae is a subfamily of Upper Jurassic ammonites included in the Oppeliidae .
Oxycheilopsis cretacicus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Oxycheilopsis .
The Bornean whistler ( Pachycephala hypoxantha ) is a species of bird in the Pachycephalidae family .
Baliochila is a genus of butterfly , commonly called buffs , in the family Lycaenidae .
Hume 's hawk - owl ( Ninox obscura ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
The Viti Levu snipe ( Coenocorypha miratropica ) was a species of austral snipe endemic to Fiji .
Desmarestiaceae is a family of brown algae , one of two families in the order Desmarestiales .
Aliptina acheronae is a species of very small sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Cerithiopsidae , and the only species in the genus Aliptina .
Brilliant rasbora ( Rasbora einthovenii ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Rasbora .
The Ward 's flycatcher ( Pseudobias wardi ) , also known as Ward 's flycatcher - vanga is a species of bird in the Vangidae family .
Ciliopagurus is a genus of hermit crabs , of the family Diogenidae , which are sometimes referred to as the `` left - handed hermit crabs '' , because in contrast to most other hermit crabs , the left chela ( claw ) is enlarged instead of the right .
The Indian hairy - footed gerbil , Gerbillus gleadowi , is a species of gerbil found mainly in Pakistan and northwestern India , They inhabit dry , sandy , and rocky country with sparse vegetation .
Phascolonus was a genus of prehistoric Australian marsupials in the wombat family .
Solenomelus is a genus of South American ( Argentina + Chile ) species of flowering plants in the family Iridaceae .
The Val 's gundi ( Ctenodactylus vali ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenodactylidae .
Camaenidae is a family of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Helicoidea , the typical snails and their allies .

Reesa is a monotypic genus of beetles in the family Dermestidae , the skin beetles .
The plant tribe Phaseoleae is one of the subdivisions of the legume subfamily Faboideae .
Distylium ( Winter - hazel ) is a genus of about 18 species of evergreen shrubs and trees in the witch hazel family Hamamelidaceae , native to eastern and southeastern Asia .

Brandt 's hedgehog ( Paraechinus hypomelas ) is a species of desert hedgehog native to the Middle East and Middle Asia .

Dacryoconarida is an extinct subclass of free living animals from the Tentaculita class , which were common in the Devonian oceans ( Fisher , 1962 ) .
Petasina is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial animal pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Hygromiidae , the hairy snails and their allies .
Holocneminae is a subfamily of cellar spiders ( family Pholcidae ) .
Armbruster 's wolf ( Canis armbrusteri ) is an extinct species of canid which was endemic to North America and lived during the Irvingtonian stage of the Pleistocene epoch 1.8 Mya--300,000 years ago , existing for approximately 1.5 million years .
Oligoceras is a plant genus of the family Euphorbiaceae , first described as a genus in 1924 .
Gymnomyza is a genus of birds , in the honeyeater family Meliphagidae , which are restricted to a few islands in the southwest Pacific Ocean .
The Bolivian river dolphin ( Inia geoffrensis boliviensis ) , a mammal , is a subspecies of the Amazon river dolphin .
Millet 's leopoldamys ( Leopoldamys milleti ) is a species of rodent from the family Muridae .
The Tasmanian clingfish ( Aspasmogaster tasmaniensis ) is a clingfish of the family Gobiesocidae , found around the western and southern coasts of Australia including Tasmania .
Lazuardia is a monotypic genus of cup fungi in the family Pyronemataceae .
The Blue Mountains water skink ( Eulamprus leuraensis ) is a species of skink in the family Scincidae .
The Carnivora , Creodonta , Pholidota , and a few other extinct orders are informally grouped together in the clade Ferae .
Atlantic herring ( Clupea harengus ) is a herring in the family Clupeidae .
The Palau swiftlet ( Aerodramus pelewensis ) is a species of swift in the Apodidae family .
The Bale shrew ( Crocidura bottegoides ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .

Streblus is a genus of flowering plant in the mulberry family , Moraceae .
Cataegidae is a family of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Seguenzioidea .
Apis andreniformis or the black dwarf honey bee is a relatively rare species of honey bee whose native habitat is the tropical and subtropical regions of southeast Asia .
Xiphidium is a genus of herbs in the family Haemodoraceae first described as a genus in 1775 .
The Spanish imperial eagle , Iberian imperial eagle or Adalbert 's eagle ( Aquila adalberti ) is a threatened species of eagle that only occurs in central and south - west Spain , adjacent areas of Portugal and possibly northern Morocco , although the latter is disputed .
Squaliolus is a genus of deep - sea dogfish sharks in the family Dalatiidae .
Coronavirinae is one of two subfamilies in the family Coronaviridae .
Rydingia is a genus of plants in the Lamiaceae family , first described in 2007 .

Lacertamoeba is a subgenus of the genus Plasmodium - all of which are parasitic protozoa .

Megabraula is a fly genus in the family Braulidae ( Diptera ) , or bee lice .

Guillardia is a genus of flagellate cryptomonad algae belonging to the family Geminigeraceae , containing a secondary plastid within a reduced cytoplasmic compartment that contains a vestigial nucleomorph .
Boloria is a brush - footed butterfly ( Nymphalidae ) genus .
The Spalacidae , or spalacids , are a family of rodents in the large and complex superfamily Muroidea .
Lamini ( members are called laminoids ) is a tribe of the subfamily Camelinae .
Fraas ' lizard ( Parvilacerta fraasii , syn . Lacerta fraasii ) is a species of lizard in the family Lacertidae .

Elodina is a genus of butterflies in the Pieridae family .
The Indian egg - eating snake or Indian egg - eater ( Elachistodon westermanni ) is a rare species of egg - eating snake found in the Indian subcontinent .
The Argentine snake - necked turtle , also known as the South American snake - necked turtle ( Hydromedusa tectifera ) is a species of turtle , known for the long neck which gave it its name .
The Arabian warbler , Red Sea warbler or Blandford 's warbler ( Sylvia leucomelaena ) , is a species of Old World warbler in the Sylviidae family .
Biantidae are included in the superfamily Samooidea , which mainly radiated in South America .
Scoliodon is a genus of requiem shark , and part of the family Carcharhinidae .
Underwood 's mussurana ( Clelia errabunda ) is an extinct species of snake formerly endemic to the Caribbean island of Saint Lucia .
As the family Halosauridae , halosaurs are one of two families within the order Notacanthiformes ; the other being the deep - sea spiny eels , Notacanthidae .
The Little Colorado River Sucker or Little Colorado Sucker ( Catostomus sp.3 ) is a fish very similar to the Flannelmouth Sucker ( Catostomus latipinnis ) but without the Flannelmouth 's distinct fleshy lips .
The Cuban vireo ( Vireo gundlachii ) is a species of bird in the Vireonidae family that is endemic to Cuba .
The Hebrew character ( Orthosia gothica ) is a species of moth in the family Noctuidae .
Protulophila is a genus of symbiotic or commensal colonial Hydrozoa , known from very small hydroids .
Paracynarctus is an extinct genus of the Borophaginae and a terrestrial canine ( bear - dog ) which inhabited most of North America during the Early Hemingfordian stage of the Early Miocene subepoch through the Early Barstovian stage of the Middle Miocene subepoch 20.6 - -13.6 Ma , existing for approximately 7 million years .
Fossil wings have been discovered in the Permian of Kansas which have a close resemblance to wings of Mastotermes of the Mastotermitidae , which is the most primitive living termite .
The Australian green tree frog , simply green tree frog in Australia , White 's tree frog , or dumpy tree frog ( Litoria caerulea ) is a species of tree frog native to Australia and New Guinea , with introduced populations in the United States and New Zealand , though the latter is believed to have died out .
The Chinese grosbeak or yellow - billed grosbeak ( Eophona migratoria ) is a species of finch in the Fringillidae family .
Biondia is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1905 .
Capnodium is a genus of sooty molds in the family Capnodiaceae .
Lorma is a genus of herbivorous Coccinellidae containing a single species , L. haliki , described from Sao Paulo , Brazil .
The Pecos pupfish ( Cyprinodon pecosensis ) is a species of Pupfish in the Cyprinodontidae family .
The Hudson Bay toad ( Anaxyrus americanus copei ) is a rare subspecies of the American toad .
Turneria is a genus of ants that belongs to the subfamily Dolichoderinae .
The Mangrove red snapper ( commonly called mangrove jack within Australia ) , Lutjanus argentimaculatus is a species of snapper .
Yefremov named the family Phthinosuchidae in 1954 to include Phthinosaurus and the newly named Phthinosuchus , which was described on the basis of a crushed partial skull .
The phylogenetic analysis of the original description of Zapatadon found it as a part of a clade that contains to the subfamilies Eilenodontidae ( Toxolophosaurus , Eilenosaurus ) and Sphenodontinae ( Sphenodon , Cynosphenodon ) , in an unresolved polytomy with the genus Opisthias and this subfamilies , within the family Sphenodontidae .
The Migadopinae are a subfamily of beetles in the family Carabidae , containing these genera :
The Rio Grande darter ( Etheostoma grahami ) is a species of darter endemic to the lower Rio Grande drainage of the United States and Mexico .
Bernard 's wolf ( Canis lupus bernardi ) , also known as the Banks Island tundra wolf , Banks Island wolf , and the Victoria 's Island wolf , was a subspecies of the gray wolf , Canis lupus , that was limited to the Banks and Victoria Island of the Canadian arctic .
Sonan 's salamander , Hynobius sonani , is a species of salamander in the Hynobiidae family , endemic to Taiwan , where it occurs in the Central Mountain Range above 2,750 m ( 9,020 ft ) .
Talarurus was assigned to the Ankylosauridae by Maleev in its original description in 1952 .
The Manusela mosaic - tailed rat ( Melomys fraterculus ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Archiearinae is a subfamily of the geometer moth family ( Geometridae ) .
Bloomeria , a geophyte in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Brodiaeoideae , was named for Hiram Green Bloomer ( 1819 - -1874 ) an early San Francisco botanist .
Fegimanra is a small genus of trees in the subfamily Anacardioideae of the cashew and sumac family Anacardiaceae .
The Malabar grey hornbill ( Ocyceros griseus ) is a hornbill endemic to the Western Ghats and associated hills of southern India .
The La Selle thrush ( Turdus swalesi ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
Melientha is a genus of plants in the family Opiliaceae described as a genus in 1888 .
Parandraceps turnbowi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Parandraceps .
Sepiadariidae is a family of cephalopods in the order Sepiida .
The Mindoro hawk - owl ( Ninox mindorensis ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Leptomerycinae is an extinct subfamily within the ruminant family Leptomerycidae .
Metaliomys is an extinct genus of Heteromyidae that existed in the United States during the Late Miocene period .
Aphelenchoididae is a nematode family in the order Aphelenchida .
The American bullfrog ( Rana catesbeiana ) , often simply known as the bullfrog in Canada and the United States , is an amphibious frog , a member of the family Ranidae , or `` true frogs '' .
Padogobius nigricans , the Arno goby , is a species of goby endemic to Italy .
Mesocyon is an extinct genus of terrestrial carnivore within the family Canidae , subfamily Hesperocyoninae , which inhabited North America from the Early Oligocene 33.9 - -20.6 Ma , existing for approximately 18 million years .
Serpenticaulis bowkettiae , the striped snake orchid ( previously Bulbophyllum bowkettiae ) is a species of orchid from Queensland , Australia .
Betaentomopoxvirus is a genus of viruses , in the family Poxviridae , in the subfamily Entomopoxvirinae .
Chimonanthus ( wintersweet ) is a genus of flowering plants in the family Calycanthaceae , endemic to China .
Neumann 's starling , or Neumann 's red - winged starling ( Onychognathus neumanni ) is a bird native to Africa .
The Mormon cricket ( Anabrus simplex ) is a large insect that can grow to almost 8 cm ( 3 inches ) in length .
Orzolina thalassophila is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Orzolina .
The Manitoba wolf ( Canis lupus griseoalbus ) , also known as the grey - white wolf , is a subspecies of the gray wolf , Canis lupus , that used to roam in Alberta , Manitoba , and Saskatchewan .
Neotyphlus franzi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Neotyphlus .
The Nubian flapshell turtle ( Cyclanorbis elegans ) is one of two species of softshell turtle in the genus Cyclanorbis of the Trionychidae family .
APG II places Stylidiaceae and Donatiaceae in the Asterales .
Chironex is a genus of box jellyfish in the Chirodropidae family .
The Zempoaltepec ( Peromyscus melanocarpus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Cephalocarida are a class in the subphylum Crustacea comprising only 12 benthic species .
The McGregor 's cuckooshrike or sharp - tailed cuckooshrike ( Coracina mcgregori ) is a species of bird in the Campephagidae family .
The Galapagos crake or Galapagos rail ( Laterallus spilonota ) is a small rail endemic to the Galapagos Islands .
The Sclater 's antwren ( Myrmotherula sclateri ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
The Timor roundleaf bat ( Hipposideros crumeniferus ) is a species of bat in the family Hipposideridae .
Ambulyx is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , described by Westwood in 1847 .
Nototeredo is a genus of ship - worms , marine bivalve molluscs of the family Teredinidae .
Aulacaspis , is a scale insect genus in the family Diaspididae .
The Chinese highland shrew ( Sorex excelsus ) is a species of shrew in the family Soricidae .
Acanthoscelides is a genus of bean weevils , beetles of the subfamily Bruchinae .
Wallago is a genus of catfishes order Siluriformes of the family Siluridae , or sheatfish .
Pseudomorphinae is a subfamily of ground beetles ( family Carabidae ) .
The Australian golden whistler ( Pachycephala pectoralis ) is a species of bird found in forest , woodland , mallee , mangrove and scrub in Australia ( except the interior and most of the north ) and in mountain forest in the Snow Mountains in the Papua Province of Indonesia .
The South African springhare ( Pedetes capensis ) , or springhaas as it is called in Afrikaans , is not actually a hare , but a Rodent .
Thelypteris ( maiden ferns ) is a genus of ferns in the family Thelypteridaceae , order Polypodiales .
Aphanes ( parsley - piert ) is a genus of around 20 species in the rose family ( Rosaceae ) , native to Europe , Asia and Australia .
Mustelinae is a paraphyletic subfamily of family Mustelidae , which includes wolverines , weasels , ferrets , martens , and minks , to the exclusion of the otters ( Lutrinae ) .
Celtis bungeana , commonly known as Bunge 's hackberry is a deciduous tree in the Celtis genus that can grow 15 meters in height .
Paroreodon is an extinct genus of oreodont of the family Merycoidodontidae , subfamily Merycoidodontinae , endemic to North America during the Oligocene - Miocene subepochs ( 30.8 - -20.6 mya ) , existing for approximately 10.2 million years .
Cinctipora is a bryozoan genus in the family Cinctiporidae also known in fossil records .
Chaunax is a genus of bony fish in the sea toad family Chaunacidae .
Halone is a genus of moth in the family Arctiidae from southern Asia and Australia .
Named in 2003 , Susisuchus is the sole member of the family Susisuchidae , and is closely related to the clade Eusuchia , which includes living crocodilians .
Trophis is a genus in the plant family Moraceae which includes about nine species , six of which are Neotropical and three which are Palaeotropical .
Hirtodrosophila is a genus of fruit fly from the family Drosophilidae .
Corynexochina is a poorly understood subdivision of the trilobite order Corynexochida .
Myelochroa is a genus of lichenized fungi within the family Parmeliaceae .
Ant nest beetles ( subfamily Paussinae ) or paussines , some members of which are known also as flanged bombardier beetles , are a large subfamily within the ground beetles ( Carabidae ) .
Thaumatogryllus is a genus of crickets in the family Gryllidae .
Moreiradromia is a genus of sponge crabs in the family Dromiidae .
The Makumuno Assumbo caecilian , Idiocranium russeli , is a species of African caecilian in the family Indotyphlidae .
Xenopsylla is a flea genus in the family Pulicidae .
The Natal Midlands dwarf chameleon ( Bradypodion thamnobates ) , also known under the longer common name of KwaZulu - Natal Midlands dwarf chameleon , is a chameleon native to woodland habitat in the Midlands area of the South African province of KwaZulu - Natal .
The Australian sharpnose shark ( Rhizoprionodon taylori ) is a requiem shark , belonging to the family Carcharhinidae .
Paramyxoviridae ( from Greek para- , beyond , -myxo- , mucus or slime , plus virus , from Latin poison , slime , thus meaning `` slime beyond slime '' ; often abbreviated PMV ) is a family of viruses in the order Mononegavirales .
Cipura is a genus of perennial , herbaceous and bulbous plants in the Iris family ( Iridaceae ) , related to the genus Cypella .
Delany 's mouse or Delany 's swamp mouse ( Delanymys brooksi ) is a species of rodent in the family Nesomyidae .
Lufengpithecus is a genus of extinct ape generally placed in the Ponginae subfamily .
The Gadidae are a family of marine fish , included in the order Gadiformes , known as the cods , codfishes or true cods .
Syrdenoidius spinipes is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Syrdenoidius .
Oosterellidae is an extinct ammonoid cephalopod family belonging to the superfamily Perisphinctoidea .
Vateriopsis seychellarum is a species of plant in the family Dipterocarpaceae .
Doratulina is a genus of leafhoppers belonging to the family Cicadellidae , subfamily Deltocephalinae , tribe Stenometopiini .
The Gulf Coast pygmy sunfish , Elassoma gilberti , is a species of pygmy sunfish endemic to Florida , USA .
The Père David 's rock squirrel ( Sciurotamias davidianus ) , also known as the Chinese rock squirrel , is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Secatophus australis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Secatophus .
The Finsch 's francolin ( Scleroptila finschi ) is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Axelia is a prehistoric genus of lobe - finned fish which belonged to the family of Coelacanthidae .
The Mali cobra ( Naja katiensis ) , also called the Katian spitting cobra , is a species of spitting cobra found in West Africa .
The South - west European nase ( Parachondrostoma toxostoma ) is a species of cyprinid fish that is found in France and Spain .
Anodonta is a genus of freshwater mussels in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Hadrokirus martini is an extinct species of true seal ( Phocidae ) that lived on the coast of Peru about 6 million years ago .
Turbinoidea was a superfamily of small to large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Octomylodon is an extinct genus of ground sloth of the family Mylodontidae , living during the Miocene - Pleistocene .
Carinostoma is an harvestmen genus in the family Nemastomatidae .
Notopteroidei is a suborder of the order Osteoglossiformes that contains the Gymnarchidae ( aba ) , Notopteridae ( feather backs and knifefish ) , mormyrids ( the elephantfishes ) , as well as extinct families .
Gratiola is a genus of plants in the Plantaginaceae family .
Peachella is an average sized biceratopsid trilobite , that exhibits the strongly effaced cephalic features that are typical for a clade wikthin the Biceratopsinae subfamily .
The Cresthead flounder , Pseudopleuronectes schrenki , is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
The Armenian gull ( Larus armenicus ) is a large gull found in the Caucasus and Middle East .
Clover yellow mosaic virus ( ClYMV ) is a plant pathogenic virus in the genus Potexvirus and the virus family Alphaflexiviridae .
Lepidonectes corallicola , known commonly as the Galapagos triplefin blenny , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Lepidonectes .
Pedicularis is a genus of perennial green root parasite plants currently placed in the broomrape family Orobanchaceae ( the genus previously having been placed in Scrophulariaceae sensu lato ) .
The Grand Comoro drongo ( Dicrurus fuscipennis ) is a species of bird in the Dicruridae family .
Xyletinus is a genus of beetles in the family Anobiidae and subfamily Xyletininae .
Dichorisandra is a genus of perennial monocotyledonous flowering plants in the dayflower family ( Commelinaceae ) .
Piranhea is a plant genus under the family Picrodendraceae described as a genus in 1866 .
Australocamelus is an extinct genus of terrestrial herbivore the family Camelidae , endemic to North America during the Miocene 16.3 - -13.6 mya existing for approximately 2.7 million years .
Omalogyroidea is a superfamily of minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the informal group Lower Heterobranchia .
Kupeus arcuatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Kupeus .
The Chaetothyriaceae are a family of ascomycetous fungi within the order Chaetothyriales and within the class Eurotiomycetes .
Beddomeia is a genus of very small freshwater snails that have a gill and an operculum , aquatic operculate gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
The Australasian gannet ( Morus serrator or Sula bassana ) , also known as Australian gannet and Tākapu , is a large seabird of the gannet family Sulidae .
The Tanimbar flycatcher ( Ficedula riedeli ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Dinomischus is a rare fossil animal from the Cambrian period .
The Rudd 's apalis ( Apalis ruddi ) is a species of bird in the Cisticolidae family .
Placenticeratidae is an extinct family of mostly Late Cretaceous ammonites ( cephalopod order Ammonitida ) included in the superfamily Hoplitaceae , derived from the Engonoceratidae by an increase in suture complexity .
Sinohippus is an extinct equid genus belonging to the subfamily Anchitheriinae .
Blacktip cardinalfish ( Apogon atradorsatus ) are reef fish in the South Pacific .
Myiopagis is a genus of bird in the Tyrannidae family , the tyrant flycatchers .
Retrophyllum is a genus of coniferous gymnosperms in the family Podocarpaceae .
Macmillan 's thicket rat ( Grammomys macmillani ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Under the Cronquist classification system , Polygalaceae were treated in a separate order of their own , Polygalales .
The Euphrates softshell turtle ( Rafetus euphraticus ) is a species of softshell turtle in the Trionychidae family .
Trymalium is a genus of shrubs or trees in the family Rhamnaceae .
The Panama slender opossum ( Marmosops invictus ) , also known as the slaty slender mouse opossum , is a species of opossum in the family Didelphidae .
Eulaceura is a genus of butterflies in the family Nymphalidae subfamily Apaturinae .
The Montseny brook newt ( Catalan : tritó del Montseny ) , Calotriton arnoldi , is a species of salamander in the family Salamandridae .
Reticulitermes is a termite genus in the family Rhinotermitidae .
Mimachlamys is a genus of scallops , marine bivalve molluscs in the taxonomic family Pectinidae .
Oarisma is a genus of butterflies in the skipper family , Hesperiidae .
The Maud Island frog , Leiopelma pakeka , is a primitive frog native to New Zealand , one of only four extant species belonging to the taxonomic family Leiopelmatidae .
The Sangihe tarsier ( Tarsius sangirensis ) , also known as Sangihe Island tarsier , is a small primate found on Sangir Island , which is located about 200 kilometers north - east of the island of Sulawesi in Indonesia .
The Forrest 's rock squirrel ( Sciurotamias forresti ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology , Part H Brachiopida ( revised ) now places the Order Pentamerida in the Class Rhynchonellata and divides it into the suborders Syntrophiidina and Pentameridina .
Parandrinae is a subfamily of the longhorn beetle family ( Cerambycidae ) .
Pholcidae , commonly known as cellar spiders , are a spider family in the suborder Araneomorphae .
Maihuenia is a genus of cactus ( family Cactaceae ) and the sole genus of the subfamily Maihuenioideae , which is the smallest subfamily of the Cactaceae .
The Nayarit mouse or Sinaloan deer mouse ( Peromyscus simulus ) is a species of cricetid rodent endemic to Mexico .
The Lord Howe woodhen ( Gallirallus sylvestris ) also known as the Lord Howe Island woodhen or Lord Howe ( Island ) rail , is a flightless bird of the rail family , ( Rallidae ) .
The Chinese francolin ( Francolinus pintadeanus ) or Burmeese francolin is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
The Mossambique forest tree frog , Leptopelis mossambicus , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in Malawi , Mozambique , South Africa , Swaziland , Zimbabwe , and possibly Botswana .
Micronelima brevipes is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
The Paghman stream salamander or the Afghani brook salamander ( Paradactylodon mustersi ) is a salamander endemic to Afghanistan .
Oxera is a genus of flowering plants in the family Labiatae / Lamiaceae native to Vanuatu and New Caledonia in the western Pacific .
Odopoia is a genus of wasps in the family Torymidae , containing the following species :
Sierraia is a genus of freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic prosobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Bithyniidae .
The Bering cisco or Lauretta whitefish ( Coregonus laurettae ) is a freshwater whitefish found in Alaska and part of Russia .
Hohenbergiopsis is a genus in the botanical family Bromeliaceae , subfamily Bromelioideae .
The Gueldenstaedt 's shrew ( Crocidura gueldenstaedtii ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Contemporary taxonomic treatments include Rhynchospora and the related genus Pleurostachys in the tribe Rhynchosporae , a well - supported clade within Cyperaceae .
Olegius turkmenicus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Olegius .
The Busuanga squirrel ( Sundasciurus hoogstraali ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The Aspidoceratidae comprise a family of middle and upper Jurassic ammonites that make up part of the superfamily Perisphinctoidea , characterized by evolute shells , commonly stocky , that tend to develop tubercles .
The Tanzanian masked weaver or Tanganyika masked weaver ( Ploceus reichardi ) is a species of bird in the weaver family , Ploceidae .
The Rhizocarpaceae are a family of fungi in the Ascomycota , class Lecanoromycetes .
Anemone hortensis , commonly called broad - leaved anemone , is a perennial herbaceous plant with an underground rhizome , belonging to the genus Anemone of the Ranunculaceae family .
The New Zealand pigeon or kererū ( Hemiphaga novaeseelandiae ) is a bird endemic to New Zealand .
Italaphaenops dimaioi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Italaphaenops .
Corythucha is a large genus of lace bug Tingidae that is primarily distributed in the New World , especially North America .
The Apsidoceratidae is a family of Middle and Upper Ordovician Barrandeocerina , ( a suborder of tarphycerids ) , characterized by curved or coiled , smooth , transversely marked , or laterally costate shells , with a conspicuous hyponomic sinus .
The Cuban fig - eating bat , or white - shouldered bat , ( Phyllops falcatus ) is a species of bat in the family Phyllostomidae , found only in the Caribbean .
The Malayan flat - shelled turtle ( Notochelys platynota ) is a species of turtle found in Southeast Asia .
Papagomys is a genus of very large rats in the tribe Rattini of the subfamily Murinae .
The Rodrigues giant day gecko ( Phelsuma gigas ) is an extinct species of day gecko .
Mekosuchus is a genus of extinct Australasian crocodiles within the subfamily Mekosuchinae .
Dracophyllum is a genus of plants belonging to the family Ericaceae , formerly Epacridaceae .
Fusinus is a genus of small to large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Fasciolariidae , the spindle snails and tulip snaills .
Lydomorphus is a genus of beetle in family Meloidae , containing the following selected species :
Duddingtonia is a genus of fungi in the family Orbiliaceae comprising only the species Duddingtonia flagrans .
Agathiphaga is a genus of moths in the family Agathiphagidae , known as kauri moths .
Leptosiphon androsaceus ( syn . Linanthus androsaceus ) is a species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name false babystars .
The Venezuelan bristle tyrant ( Phylloscartes venezuelanus ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .

Entemnotrochus is a genus of large to very large deepwater sea snails with gills and an operculum , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Pleurotomariidae , the slit snails .
Nesophanes fulgidum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Nesophanes .
The Emydinae are a subfamily of the turtles in the family Emydidae .
Esox is a genus of freshwater fish , the only living genus in the family Esocidae -- the esocids which were endemic to North America and Eurasia during the Paleogene through present .
The Nile lechwe or Mrs Gray 's lechwe ( Kobus megaceros ) is a species of antelope .
Primnoisis is a genus of deep - sea bamboo coral of the Isididae family .
The Spencer 's river tree frog , or Spencer 's tree frog or spotted tree frog ( Litoria spenceri ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
The Saint Vincent blacksnake ( Chironius vincenti ) is a species of colubrid snake .

The Temminck 's mouse ( Mus musculoides ) is a species of the genus Mus and of the subgenus Nannomys .
The Serra do Mar tyrannulet ( Phylloscartes difficilis ) is a small species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
The Tamá harlequin frog or Venezuela stubfoot toad ( Atelopus tamaense ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
The Algerian wall gecko ( Tarentola neglecta ) is a species of lizard in the family Gekkonidae .
Cryptocotyle is a genus of trematodes from the family Heterophyidae .
Nasiternella is a genus of hairy - eyed craneflies ( family Pediciidae ) with a Holarctic distribution .
Mainwaringia is a genus of sea snails or freshwater snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
The Lesser Sundas goshawk ( Accipiter sylvestris ) is a bird of prey native to Indonesia .
Zosterornis is a genus of passerine bird in the Old World babbler family Zosteropidae ( Moyle et al . , 2009 ) , although some taxonomists continue to place the genus in the Old World babbler family Timaliidae .
The Columbia pebblesnail , scientific name Fluminicola columbiana , is a species of very small freshwater snail that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Lithoglyphidae .
Talisia is a genus of 52 species of flowering plants in the soapberry family , Sapindaceae , native to tropical regions of the Americas .
Gazella psolea is an unusual prehistoric species of gazelle that lived in Africa and Arabia ; it is only known from fossils .
Physaloptera is a genus of parasitic nematodes in the family Physalopteridae .
The Chignahuapan splayfoot salamander or Cope 's flat - footed salamander ( Chiropterotriton orculus ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Yaldwyn 's triplefin , Notoclinops yaldwyni , is a fish of the genus Notoclinops , found around the North Island of New Zealand from low water to depths of about 5 metres , most common in reef areas of broken rock , but nowhere common .
Globularia is a genus of about 22 species of flowering plants in the family Plantaginaceae , native to central and southern Europe , Macaronesia , northwest Africa and southwest Asia .
The Formosan subterranean termite ( Coptotermes formosanus ) is an invasive species of termite .
Goniothalamus is one of the largest palaeotropical genera of plant in family Annonaceae .
Aerides , known commonly as cat's - tail orchids and fox brush orchids , is a genus belonging to the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) ( subfamily Epidendroideae , tribe Vandeae , subtribe Aeridinae ) .
Tordylium is a genus of flowering plants in the carrot family ( Apiaceae ) .
Trionyx is a genus of softshell turtles belonging to the family Trionychidae .
The Malaysian partridge , or Campbell 's partridge , ( Arborophila campbelli ) is a species of bird in the Phasianidae family .
Leurolepas roseola is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets and slit limpets .
The Enggano thrush ( Geokichla leucolaema ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
The Sunda warbler ( Seicercus grammiceps ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Phylloscopidae ( or Sylviidae ) family .
Banksia is a genus of around 170 species in the plant family Proteaceae .
Puyseguria is a genus of marine bivalve molluscs of the family Neoleptonidae .
Catharesthes elegans is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Catharesthes .
Anchotrechus punctipennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Anchotrechus .
The typical spinetails , Cranioleuca , are a genus of birds in the Furnariidae family .
Actaeon beetle ( Megasoma actaeon ) is a rhinoceros beetle belonging to the Scarabaeidae family .
Named by Hyatt , 1900 , Anahamulina is included in the family Ptychoceratidae , which is part of the Turrilitaceae .
Hamaticherus bellator is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Hamaticherus .
Kossmaticeratidae is an extinct ammonoid family belonging to the order Ammonitida .

Achoerodus gouldii , the western blue groper , is a species of wrasse native to coastal waters of southern Australia from the Houtman Abrolhos in Western Australia to west of Melbourne .
The Chinese brill , Tephrinectes sinensis , is a species of flatfish in the large - tooth flounder family , Paralichthyidae .
Haddadus is a genus of frogs in the Craugastoridae family .
Babakina is in the subfamily Babakininae within the family Flabellinidae in the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , ( 2005 ) .
Cephaloplon pedunculatum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Cephaloplon .
Bollons ' rattail , Coelorinchus bollonsi , is a species of rattail found along the east coast of New Zealand at depths of between 300 and 800 m. Its length is between 10 to 25 cm .
Shuaphaenops parvicollis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Shuaphaenops .
Atractosteus spatula Lacépède , 1803 ( Alligator gar ) Atractosteus tristoechus Bloch & J. G. Schneider , 1801 ( Cuban gar ) Atractosteus tropicus T. N. Gill , 1863 ( Tropical gar )
Antigrella orissana is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Sternotomis is a genus of beetle belonging to the family Cerambycidae .
The Nassau grouper ( Epinephelus striatus ) is one of the large number of perciform fishes in the family Serranidae commonly referred to as groupers .
Detarium is a plant genus of the family Fabaceae ( legume family ) .
The Thread eel ( Serrivomer bertini , also known as the Thread sawtooth eel ) is an eel in the family Nemichthyidae ( snipe eels ) .
Xerolirion is a monotypic genus of perennial herbs in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Lomandroideae .
The Puerto Rican flycatcher ( Myiarchus antillarum ) is a tyrant flycatcher endemic to the archipelago of Puerto Rico and one of the 22 species belonging to the Myiarchus genus of the Tyrannidae family .
The New Zealand scaup ( Aythya novaeseelandiae ) commonly known as a black teal , is a diving duck species of the genus Aythya .
Differences between Hymenocaris and Canadaspis have been used to justify erecting a separate family , Hymenocarididae and order , Hymenostraca for Hymenocaris , although it is also sometimes placed in the family Canadaspididae and the order Canadaspidida .
The Bornean banded pitta ( Hydrornis schwaneri ) is a species of bird in the Pittidae family .
The Phylloxeroidea is a small superfamily of the Hemiptera closely related to the aphids , and often traditionally included in the Aphidoidea , which is the sister taxon .
Now recognised as a member of the family Spinosauridae , Baryonyx 's affinities were obscure when it was discovered .
Sporisorium is a fungus genus in the Ustilaginaceae family .
The Recife broad - nosed bat , Platyrrhinus recifinus , is a species of bat from South America .
Eucladoceros ( Greek for `` well - branched antler '' ) or bush - antlered deer is an extinct genus of deer whose fossils have been discovered in Europe , the Middle East and Central Asia .
Discoclymeniinae is one of two subfamilies of the Posttornoceratidae family , a member of the Goniatitida order .
The Sumatran cochoa ( Cochoa beccarii ) is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
The Oaxacan pocket gopher ( Orthogeomys cuniculus ) is a species of rodent in the family Geomyidae .
Amblypomacentrus is a small genus of fish in the family Pomacentridae .
Crane fly is a common name referring to any member of the insect family Tipulidae , of the order Diptera , true flies in the superfamily Tipuloidea .
Gyrocarpus is a small genus of flowering plants in the Hernandiaceae family with a wide pantropical distribution .
The Manipur bush quail ( Perdicula manipurensis ) is a species of quail found in India , inhabiting damp grassland , particularly stands of tall grass , in West Bengal , Assam , Nagaland , Manipur , and Meghalaya .
In taxonomy , the Rhodobacteraceae are a family of the Rhodobacterales .
Aacanthocnema is a genus of lice from the jumping plant lice family ( Triozidae ) .
Hyphomycetes are a form classification of Fungi , part of what has often been referred to as Fungi imperfecti , Deuteromycota , or anamorphic fungi .
Nyctereutes is an Old World genus of the family Canidae , consisting of just one living species , the raccoon dog of East Asia .
The Striped weever , Trachinus lineolatus , is a fish of the Trachinidae family .
The Makira flycatcher ( Myiagra cervinicauda ) , also known as the ochre - tailed flycatcher , is a species of bird in the Monarchidae family .
Tridentarius is a monospecific genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
The Cape gray mongoose ( Galerella pulverulenta ) , also called the small gray mongoose , is a mongoose endemic to southern Africa .
Typhlonesiotes swaluwenbergi is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Typhlonesiotes .
Reston virus ( RESTV ) is one of five known viruses within the genus Ebolavirus .
Lampyris is a genus of beetle in the firefly family ( Lampyridae ) .
Barbour 's map turtle ( Graptemys barbouri ) is a species of turtle in the family Emydidae .
Australorhipis aphanochila is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Australorhipis .
Rhyncogonus is a genus of beetle in family Curculionidae .
The Kibonde or salmontail catfish , Chrysichthys brachynema , is a Lake Tanganyikan catfish of the family Claroteidae , occasionally kept in aquariums .
Hardwicke 's woolly bat ( Kerivoula hardwickii ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Pyrgophorus is a genus of very small freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod molluscs in the family Hydrobiidae .
Coilopoceras is a compressed , involute , lenticular ammonitid from the Upper Cretaceous with a narrow venter and raggedy ammonitic suture ; type of the Coilopoceratidae , a family in the Acanthoceratoidea of the suborder Ammonitina .
Erythrosquilla is a genus of mantis shrimp , placed in its own family ( Erythrosquillidae ) and superfamily ( Erythrosquilloidea ) comprising two species :
The Zeravshan dace ( Leuciscus lehmanni ) is a species cyprinid fish found mainly in Afghanistan and Uzbekistan .
The Madagascan lark ( Mirafra hova ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family endemic to Madagascar .
Potiapua antonia is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Potiapua .
The Paniai gudgeon ( Oxyeleotris wisselensis ) is a species of sleeper goby endemic to the Paniai Lakes ( absent from Lake Paniai itself , but present in both Lake Tigi and Tage ) and their tributaries in West Papua , Indonesia .
The Ross 's gull ( Rhodostethia rosea ) is a small gull , the only species in its genus , although it has been suggested it should be moved to the genus Hydrocoloeus , which otherwise only includes the little gull .
The Grey - cheeked nunlet ( Nonnula frontalis ) is a species of puffbird in the Bucconidae family .
Crocus tommasinianus , the woodland crocus , early crocus , or Tommasini 's crocus , often referred to as ' tommies ' , were named after the botanist Muzio G. Spirito de Tommasini ( 1794 - 1879 ) , who was Mayor of the city of Trieste .
Acanthurinae is a subfamily of fish belonging to the family Acanthuridae , including 55 species in four genera .
Sclater 's mouse shrew ( Myosorex sclateri ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae endemic to South Africa .
Palmer 's tree frog , Hyloscirtus palmeri , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family found in Colombia , Costa Rica , Ecuador , and Panama .
Encelia is a genus of the plant family Asteraceae .
Hahncappsia is a genus of moths of the Crambidae family , and the order Lepidoptera .
Rytidosperma pallidum ( syn . Joycea pallida ) , commonly known as red - anther wallaby grass , is an Australian species of tussock grass found in Victoria , New South Wales and the Australian Capital Territory .
The Barahona rock frog or Hispaniola dwarf robber frog ( Eleutherodactylus alcoae ) is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family that is endemic to southern Hispaniola .
Thunia is a genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) and the only genus of the subtribe Thuniinae .
Phillyrea is a genus of two species of flowering plants in the family Oleaceae , native to the Mediterranean region , and naturalized in the Canary Islands and Madeira .
Peters ' dwarf epauletted fruit bat ( Micropteropus pusillus ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Adrianitidae is a family in the Adrianitaceae , a superfamily of ammonites in the cephalopod order , Goniatitida , known from the Middle Pennsylvanian to the Middle Permian .
Plasmodium pteropti is a currently ( 2007 ) considered to be a species of the genus Hepatocystis rather than Plasmodium .
Curry 's bat ( Glauconycteris curryae ) is a species of vesper bat in the family Vespertilionidae .
Cycnogeton is a genus of plants in the family Juncaginaceae described as a genus in 1838 .
The Cunene labeo or Kunene labeo ( Labeo ansorgii ) is a species of fish in the family Cyprinidae , the carps and minnows .
Metaverpulus is a genus of harvestmen in the family Sclerosomatidae .
The Manyas shemaya ( Alburnus carinatus ) is a species of cyprinid fish in the genus Alburnus .
Whitfieldia is a genus of plant in family Acanthaceae with about 10 species in tropical Africa .
Gleviceras was described by Buckman in 1918 and is included in the Family Oxynoticeratidae and superfamily Psilocerataceae .
Lophoceras is a Nautilid genus belonging to the tainoceratacean family , Koninckioceratidae , found in Lower Carboniferous sediments in Europe , and named by Hyatt , 1893 .
Chirixalus is a now - synonymized genus in the moss frog family ( Rhacophoridae ) .
Drymatus tesselatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Drymatus .
Myomyrus is a genus of elephantfish in the family Mormyridae .
The Mauritius cuckooshrike ( Coracina typica ) is a species of bird in the Campephagidae family .
The West Coast lady ( Vanessa annabella ) is one of three North American species of brush - footed butterflies known colloquially as the `` painted ladies '' .
The Tricholomataceae are a large family of mushrooms within the Agaricales .
The Caspian kutum ( Rutilus kutum ) or Caspian White Fish is a member of the family Cyprinidae from brackish water habitats of the Caspian Sea and from its freshwater tributaries .
Eucyclidae is an extinct family of fossil gastropods in the superfamily Seguenzioidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Odocoileus lucasi , historically incorrectly confused with Navahoceros fricki , and known as the American mountain deer , is an extinct species of North American deer .
The Galapagos land iguana ( Conolophus subcristatus ) is a species of lizard in the family Iguanidae .
Exosphaeroma is a genus of marine isopod of the family Sphaeromatidae .
Dussartius baeticus is a species of crustacean in the family Diaptomidae .
The Fuegian snipe ( Gallinago stricklandii ) also known as the cordilleran snipe , is a small stocky wader .
Rimellopsis is a genus of large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Rostellariidae within the Stromboidea , the true conchs and their allies .
The Geelvink pygmy tree frog ( Litoria pygmaea ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Palaeostoidae is an extinct family of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Clausilioidea ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Charadrophila is a genus of flowering plants in the family Stilbaceae described as a genus in 1899.Tropicos , Charadrophila Marloth There is only one known species , Charadrophila capensis , native to the Cape Province region of South Africa .
The Quitabaquito tryonia , scientific name Tryonia quitobaquitae , is a species of small freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Bytharia is a genus of moth in the family Geometridae with the species which are relatively large for the Sterrhinae subfamily and characterized by pale yellow wings with uniform gray margins and , on the forewing , gray along the costa .
The Graciloceratidae is a family of nautiloid cephalopods from the Middle and Upper Ordovician belonging to the Oncocerida , characterized by exogastric cyrtocones that expand slightly or moderately and have thin walled , orthochoantic marginal or subventral , tubular siphuncles ( Sweet 1964 ) .
Leith 's softshell turtle ( Nilssonia leithii ) is a species of turtle found in peninsular Indian rivers including the Bhavani , Godavari , and Moyar Rivers .
Lambis is a genus of large sea snails sometimes known as spider conchs , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Strombidae , the true conch family .
The New Mexico spadefoot toad ( Spea multiplicata ) is a species of American spadefoot toad found in the southwestern United States and Mexico .
The Hewitson 's small tree - nymph ( Ideopsis hewitsonii ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
Ricinula is a genus of predatory sea snails , marinegastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Platycephalus is a genus of mostly marine , bottom - dwelling fish in the family Platycephalidae .
The Bahamas sawshark , Pristiophorus schroederi , is a sawshark of the family Pristiophoridae , found in the western Central Atlantic Ocean from the Bahamas and Cuba at depths of between 400 and 1,000 m. These sharks are at least 80 cm long .
Helcogrammoides cunninghami , known commonly as the Cunningham 's triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Helcogrammoides .
The Bering flounder , Hippoglossoides robustus , is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
The Bini free - tailed bat ( Myopterus whitleyi ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
Rhaebo is a genus of true toads , family Bufonidae , from Central and South America .
Adnatoceras is a mid Devonian to Pennsylvanian orthoconic nautiloid cephalopod included in the pseudorthocerid family Spyroceratidae , characterized by tubular , straight - sided , siphuncle segments that expand abruptly at the septal foremena .
Hapunalikevirus ( synonym : Hap1likevirus ) is a genus of viruses in the family Myoviridae , not assigned to a subfamily .
Hoffmannseggia is a genus of flowering plants in the pea family , Fabaceae , known generally as rushpeas .
Aclerdidae are a family of Coccoidea , the scale insects .
Trissopelopia is a genus of non - biting midges in the subfamily Tanypodinae of the bloodworm family Chironomidae .
Haemamoeba is a subgenus of the genus Plasmodium -- all of which are parasitic protozoa .
Underwood 's bonneted bat ( Eumops underwoodi ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae found in Belize , Costa Rica , El Salvador , Guatemala , Honduras , Mexico , Nicaragua and the southwestern United States .
APG III ( 2009 ) places Vitaceae in its own order , Vitales .
The Martinique giant ameiva ( Ameiva major ) was a species of lizard in the Teiidae family .
Pingalla midgleyi is a species of fish in the family Terapontidae known by the common names black - blotch grunter and Midgley 's grunter .
The Carolinian reed warbler or Caroline Islands reed warbler ( Acrocephalus syrinx ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Acrocephalidae family .
The Palawan flying squirrel or bising ( Hylopetes nigripes ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Volvox is a polyphyletic genus of chlorophyte green algae in the family Volvocaceae .
Yates ( 2005 ) assigned Dracovenator to the clade Neotheropoda .
The Central Asian salamander ( Ranodon sibiricus ) is a species of salamander in the monotypic genus Ranodon of the Hynobiidae family .
Thaumastochilus is a spider genus of the Zodariidae family .
Picobirnavirus is a genus of dsRNA viruses , the only genus in the family Picobirnaviridae .
Larches are conifers in the genus Larix , in the family Pinaceae .
Tetrophthalmi is an extinct suborder of Opiliones ( commonly known as harvestmen or daddy longlegs ) that had four eyes .
Anderson 's gerbil , Gerbillus andersoni is a species of gerbils distributed from Tunisia to Israel .
Panthera onca onca ( Linnaeus , 1758 ) was proposed as a subspecies of jaguar , before later research failed to find evidence for it .
The Mindanao squirrel ( Sundasciurus mindanensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
Hoplophoneus is an extinct genus of the family Nimravidae , subfamily Nimravinae , endemic to North America during the Late Eocene to Early Oligocene epochs ( 38 - -33.3 mya ) , existing for approximately 3.9 million years .
Rhizocybe is a mushroom genus in the family Tricholomataceae in the broad sense .
The Delhi Sands flower - loving fly ( Rhaphiomidas terminatus abdominalis ) is a mydid fly in the genus Rhaphiomidas , and the only fly presently on the Endangered Species List .
Hintzeia is a trilobite in the order Phacopida ( family Pliomeridae ) , that existed during the lower Ordovician in what is now the United States .
Northern puffer , Sphoeroides maculatus , is a species in the family ( ( ) ) , or pufferfishes .
Aethalops is a genus of megabats in the family Pteropodidae .
Dryophthorus Germar , 1824 is a genus of beetle in family Dryophthoridae .
Capelio is a genus of flowering plant in the Asteraceae first described as a genus in 1836 with the name Alciope .
Zhuchengceratops shares may features with Leptoceratopsidae as well as other ceratopsian groups such as Ceratopsidae .
Tephrocyon is an extinct genus of the Borophaginae and a small to medium - sized terrestrial canine ( bear - dog ) which inhabited most of North America during the Barstovian stage of the Middle Miocene 16.3 - -13.6 Ma , existing for approximately 2.7 million years .
The Haitian edible rat ( Brotomys contractus ) is an extinct species of rodent in the family Echimyidae .
Brueelia ( formerly spelled Brüelia ) is a genus of lice in the family Philopteridae , containing the following species :
Domatoceras is a nautiloid genus and member of the Grypoceratidae from the Pennsylvanian and Permian with a wide spread distribution .
Nyctaegeria is a genus of moths in the Sesiidae family containing only one species , Nyctaegeria nobilis , which is known from Angola and Tanzania .
The Australian crake , also known as Australian spotted crake , ( Porzana fluminea ) is a species of bird in the family Rallidae .
Flustrina is a suborder under the order Cheilostomata of gymnolaematan Bryozoa ( sea mats ) .
Tacheocampylaea is a genus of air - breathing , land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Helicidae , the typical snails .
The Lombok flying fox ( Pteropus lombocensis ) is a species of megabat in the Pteropus genus .
Stipa coronata , formerly classified as Achnatherum coronatum , is a greenish species of grass known by the common name crested needlegrass , giant ricegrass , and giant stipa .
† Gyrotoma is a genus of extinct freshwater snails with an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Pleuroceridae .
Portulacaria is a genus of succulent plant in the family Didiereaceae , that is indigenous to southern Africa .
The Indo - Pacific shorttail conger ( Coloconger scholesi ) , also known as the short - tail conger , is an eel in the family Colocongridae ( worm eels / short - tail eels ) .
Mesodma is an extinct genus of mammal , a member of the extinct order Multituberculata within the suborder Cimolodonta , family Neoplagiaulacidae .
Pusillimonas is a genus of Gram - negative oxidase - positive bacteria of the family Alcaligenaceae .
Caesulia is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Caesulia axillaris .
The Cuban solitaire ( Myadestes elisabeth ) , also known as the Cuban nightingale , is a species of bird in the family Turdidae .
The Murray River turtle ( Emydura macquarii ) is a wide - ranging species that occurs throughout many of the rivers of the eastern half of Australia .
Ctenorhachis ( Greek for `` comb spine '' ) is an extinct genus of the family Sphenacodontidae .
Forficulinae is a subfamily of earwigs in the family Forficulidae .
Erycitidae is a family of Lower and Middle Jurassic ammonites included in the Hammatoceratoidea .
Empoasca is a genus of leafhoppers belonging to the family Cicadellidae subfamily Typhlocybinae .
Compsodrillia is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Turridae , the turrids .
The Ohio lamprey ( Ichthyomyzon bdellium ) is a lamprey found in the Ohio River drainage basin in the United States and is a parasitic species of lampreys .
Microthyris is a genus of pyraloid moths , belonging to the subfamily Spilomelinae of the grass moth family ( Crambidae ) .
The Ricinidae are a family of a larger group Amblycera of the chewing lice .
Baliospermum is a genus of plants under the family Euphorbiaceae first described as a genus in 1825 .
Grapevine virus E ( GVE ) is a plant virus species in the genus Vitivirus .
Cubaecola hoploderoides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Cubaecola .
Palaeophis ( ' ancient snake ' ) is an extinct genus of marine snake belonging to the family Palaeophiidae .
Paralichthodinae is a subfamily of flatfish in the Pleuronectidae family .
The Siamese algae eater ( Crossocheilus oblongus ) is a species of freshwater fish in the carp family , Cyprinidae .
Christinus is a genus of Gekkonidae geckos found in southern regions of Australia .
Bajacalia is a genus of three flowering plants in the sunflower family , Asteraceae .
The Eoderoceratidae is the ancestral and most primitive family of the Eoderocerataceae ; lower Jurassic ammonite cephalopods , characterized by evolute , commonly serpenticonic , shells that had long body chambers and would have had no stable floating position ; and thus resemble contemporary Psilocerataceae .
Austroglanis is the only genus in the catfish family Austroglanididae .
Antrodiella is a genus of fungi traditionally classified in the family Phanerochaetaceae of the Polyporales , although molecular studies suggest that the Steccherinaceae is a better familial placement .
Bocaparvovirus is a genus of viruses , in the family Parvoviridae , in the subfamily Parvovirinae .
Anachloris is a genus of moth in the family Geometridae , with 3 species , found in Australia , New Zealand and Papua New Guinea .
The Genus Hemichoanella is a small , extinct , orthoconic nautiloid cephalopod from the Lower Ordovician of Western Australia assigned to the orthoceratoid family , Baltoceratidae .
The Tagula honeyeater ( Meliphaga vicina ) is a species of bird in the family Meliphagidae .
Cicuta , commonly known as water hemlock , is a small genus of four species of highly poisonous plants in the family Apiaceae .
Werner 's catfish ( Clarias werneri ) is a species of airbreathing catfish .
The Seychelles skink ( Trachylepis seychellensis ) is a species of skink in the Scincidae family .
The Southern spearnose poacher ( Agonopsis sterletus ) is a fish in the family Agonidae ( poachers ) .
Parophidion is a genus of cusk - eels found in the Atlantic Ocean .
Barbaceniopsis is a plant genus in the family Velloziaceae , described as a genus in 1962 .
The nearest relatives of Mesolenellus are the species of the genus Mesonacis , with which it constitutes the subfamily Mesonacinae .
Plumbago is a genus of 10 - 20 species of flowering plants in the family Plumbaginaceae , native to warm temperate to tropical regions of the world .
Tirsa is a genus of moths of the Crambidae family , containing only one species Tirsa fiona .
Chaetanthus is a group of plants in the Restionaceae described as a genus in 1810 .
The Malaysian honeyguide ( Indicator archipelagicus ) is a medium - sized , up to 18 cm long , olive - brown honeyguide with greenish streaks , reddish iris , thick grey bill and greyish white below .
The Mindanao bleeding - heart ( Gallicolumba crinigera ) , also known as Bartlett 's bleeding heart dove , Barlett 's bleeding heart pigeon and the hair - breasted bleeding heart , is a species of bird in the pigeon family .
Acraspis is a genus of gall wasps in the family Cynipidae , comprising the following species :
Codia is a genus of trees and shrubs in the family Cunoniaceae .
The Indian blackbird ( Turdus simillimus ) is a member of the thrush family Turdidae .
The Jaliscan cotton rat ( Sigmodon mascotensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Older works have usually placed Astianthus in the tribe Tecomeae , but the circumscription of that tribe was greatly revised in 2009 .
Megatylopus ( also known as the North American camel ) is an extinct and large genus of terrestrial herbivore the family Camelidae , endemic to North America from the Miocene through Late Pliocene--
The African spotted creeper ( Salpornis salvadori ) is a small passerine bird , which is a member of the subfamily Salpornithinae of the treecreeper family Certhiidae .
Traditionally , Endlicheria was placed near Aniba and the other Lauraceae with two locellate anthers .
Hyalorbilia is a genus comprising 10 species of fungi in the family Orbiliaceae .
The Tanzanian shrew ( Crocidura tansaniana ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
The Korean salamander ( Hynobius leechii ) is the most common species of salamander on the Korean peninsula , and is also found in nearby provinces of China ( Liaoning , Jilin and Heilongjiang ) and on Jeju Island .
Paraxiphodon is an extinct genus of Artiodactyl ( family Xiphodontidae ) from the Eocene - Lower Oligocene of Europe .
The Canopy chameleon ( Furcifer willsii ) , also known as Will 's chameleon , is a species of chameleon that is endemic to Madagascar .
The Zhenhai brown frog ( Rana zhenhaiensis ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family found in China and possibly Hong Kong and Macau .
Denhamia is a genus of plants within the family Celastraceae , with all species endemic to eastern and northern Australia .
The South Georgia diving petrel or Georgian diving - petrel ( Pelecanoides georgicus ) is a diving petrel , one of four very similar auk - like small petrels of the southern oceans .
The Visayan hornbill ( Penelopides panini ) is a hornbill found in rainforests on the islands of Panay , Negros , Masbate , and Guimaras , and formerly Ticao , in the Philippines .
Cephalouterina is a trematode genus within the family Lecithodendriidae under the order Plagiorchiida .
Ashmunella is a genus of small , air - breathing , land snails in the family Polygyridae .
The Yaqui chub ( Gila purpurea ) is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family .
The Supatá golden frog ( Ranitomeya sp . nov . `` Supatáe '' ) is a species of poison dart frog endemic to Colombia .
Kerguelenella is a genus of air - breathing sea snails , marine pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Siphonariidae , the false limpets .
Together with other species from scattered localities in the United States , Japan , and Europe , Apeomyoides is classified in the subfamily Apeomyinae of the extinct rodent family Eomyidae .
Pyrgodesmidae is a family of flat - backed millipedes in the order Polydesmida .
The Chlamisini form a tribe within the leaf beetle subfamily Cryptocephalinae , though historically they were often treated as a distinct subfamily , Chlamisinae .
Heterojinus semilaetanus is a species of beetle in the family Laemophloeidae , the only species in the genus Heterojinus .
Mormolycina obertheuri is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Mormolycina .
Froggatt 's catfish or the Smallmouthed salmon catfish ( Cinetodus froggatti ) is a species of sea catfish found in West Papua in Indonesia and Papua New Guinea where it is found in the Purari , Fly , Strickland and Digul River systems as well as in the Roper River system of Northwest Territories , Australia .
Ashtonia is a genus of flowering plant belonging to the family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1968 .
Allantinae is a subfamily of sawflies in the family Tenthredinidae .
The Western Spanish ibex or Gredos ibex ( Capra pyrenaica victoriae ) is a vulnerable goat endemic to Spain and Portugal .
Halesia , also known as silverbell or snowdrop tree , is a small genus of four or five species of deciduous large shrubs or small trees in the family Styracaceae .
Hartlaub 's babbler or Angola babbler ( Turdoides hartlaubii ) is a species of bird in the Leiothrichidae family .
The Newfoundland wolf ( Canis lupus beothucus ) was a possible subspecies of gray wolf native to Newfoundland .
The Tetragonoceratidae is a small family of nautilitids constituting a part of the superfamily Tainocerataceae in which shells are coiled with a generally quadrate whorl section .
Pseudoomphalina is a genus of fungi in the placed in the family Tricholomataceae for convenience .
The Himalayan bulbul ( Pycnonotus leucogenys ) or White - cheeked Bulbul is a species of songbird in the Pycnonotidae family .
Eupterodactyloidea ( meaning `` true Pterodactyloidea '' ) is an extinct clade of pterodactyloid pterosaurs from the earliest Early Cretaceous to the latest Late Cretaceous ( Berriasian to Maastrichtian stages ) of all continents except Antarctica .
Pupoidopsis is a genus of very small or minute air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Pupillidae .
Eotrechodes larisae is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Eotrechodes .
Tsuga ( /ˈsuːɡə/ , from Japanese : 栂 ( ツガ ) , the name of Tsuga sieboldii ) is a genus of conifers in the pine family Pinaceae .
In taxonomy , the Chlamydomonadaceae are a family of algae within the order Volvocales .
The Cervinae or the Old World deer ( denoting their place of origin , not their current distribution ) , are a subfamily of deer .
Percilia is a genus of perch - like fish in the Percichthyidae family .
Moelleriopsis is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks unassigned in the superfamily Seguenzioidea .
Geosaurus is an extinct genus of marine crocodyliform within the family Metriorhynchidae , that lived during the Late Jurassic and the Early Cretaceous .
Angarioidea is a superfamily of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Vetigastropoda .
The Malagasy lapwing ( Vanellus madagascariensis ) is an extinct wader in the lapwing family .
The Yungas manakin ( Chiroxiphia boliviana ) is a species of bird in the Pipridae family .
Nissolia , the yellowhoods , is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Polia 's shrew ( Crocidura polia ) is a species of mammal in the family Soricidae .
Swans are grouped with the closely related geese in the subfamily Anserinae where they form the tribe Cygnini .
Atractonotus mulsanti is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Atractonotus .
The Argentine swamp rat ( Scapteromys aquaticus ) is a semiaquatic rodent species from South America .
The Marlborough green gecko , also known as the Manuka Gecko , Naultinus manukanus , is a small species of gecko endemic to New Zealand .
The Cuban gnatcatcher ( Polioptila lembeyei ) is a species of bird in the Polioptilidae family , the gnatcatchers .
Exoglossum is a genus of mound - building freshwater fish of the minnow family ( Cyprinidae ) containing two species , commonly known as cutlip minnows , although the individual species , particularly Exoglossum maxillingua , are also locally known by that name .
Myoxocephalus is a genus of fish in the sculpin family Cottidae .
Aderus is a genus of leaf beetles of the family Aderidae that resemble ants .
The Goliath heron ( Ardea goliath ) , also known as the giant heron , is a very large wading bird of the heron family , Ardeidae .
The Japanese roughshark ( Oxynotus japonicus ) is a rare species of shark in the family Oxynotidae , known only from a handful of specimens recovered from Suruga Bay and the Enshunada Sea off Japan .
Dinocardium is a genus of large saltwater clams or cockles , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Cardiidae , the cockles .
Actinodium is a genus of the botanical family Myrtaceae , described as a genus in 1836 .
Lampropeltis getula floridana or the Florida kingsnake is a snake species native to southern Florida .
The Yangtze giant softshell turtle ( Rafetus swinhoei ) is an extremely rare species of softshell turtle found in China .
The Piedmont ringlet ( Erebia meolans ) is a member of the Nymphalidae family .
Soletellina is a genus of bivalve molluscs in the family Psammobiidae , known as sunset shells .
The Bahia tyrannulet ( Phylloscartes beckeri ) is a species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
The Oriental dwarf kingfisher ( Ceyx erithaca ) , also known as the black - backed kingfisher or three - toed kingfisher , is a species of bird in the family Alcedinidae .
The Lake Chala tilapia ( Oreochromis hunteri ) is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Chala a crater lake on the border of Kenya and Tanzania .
Latrodectus is a genus of spider in the big spider family Theridiidae , most of which are commonly known as widow spiders .
Spinosaurus gives its name to the Spinosauridae family of dinosaurs , which includes two subfamilies :
Myrmephytum is a genus of myrmecophytic flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family .
Heleia is a genus of bird in the white - eye family Zosteropidae .
Cheatum 's snail also known as the Phantom tryonia , scientific name Tryonia cheatumi , is a species of small freshwater snails with a gill and an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Hydrobiidae .
Eumictoxenus is a genus of Tephritid or fruit flies in the family Tephritidae .
The Moluccan cuckooshrike ( Coracina atriceps ) is a species of bird in the Campephagidae family .
Celianella is a genus of flowering plant belonging to the family Phyllanthaceae first described as a genus in 1965 .
Haidomyrmex is an extinct genus of ants in the formicid subfamily Sphecomyrminae , and is one of only three genera placed in the tribe Haidomyrmecini .
Bocage 's African fat mouse ( Steatomys bocagei ) is an extant species of rodent indigenous to Angola , the Republic of the Congo , and the Democratic Republic of the Congo ( DRC ) .
Southern puffer , Sphoeroides nephelus , is a species in the family Tetraodontidae , or pufferfishes .
Amylostereum is the single genus in the fungal family Amylostereaceae .
Metroxylon is a genus of monoecious flowering plants in the Arecaceae ( palm ) family , consisting of seven species .
Cirrhinus is a genus of fish in the family Cyprinidae , the carps and minnows .
The Guatemala stream frog , Ptychohyla panchoi , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Guatemala .
Dall 's porpoise ( Phocoenoides dalli ) is a species of porpoise found only in the North Pacific .
The Sri Lankan elephant ( Elephas maximus maximus ) is one of three recognized subspecies of the Asian elephant , and native to Sri Lanka .
Scagea is a genus of plants under the family Picrodendraceae described as a genus in 1986 .
The Eomoropidae is most likely a paraphyletic group within Chalicotherioidea .
Beloceras is a genus of ammonites included in the family Beloceratidae .
Peanut , also known as groundnut ( Arachis hypogaea ) , is a crop of global importance .
Gulickia is a genus of gastropod in the Achatinellidae family .
Later research showed however that Paraprefica had characteristics found only in the family Nyctibiidae , order Caprimulgiformes ( the nightjars ) .
Mungos is a genus in the mongoose family ( Herpestidae ) .
The New Zealand pea crab , Pinnotheres novaezelandiae , is a small , parasitic crab that lives most commonly inside New Zealand green - lipped mussels .
Eristalis is a large genus of hoverflies , family Syrphidae , in the order Diptera .
Antilophia is a genus of South American bird in the Pipridae family .
Pachystoma is a genus of orchids ( family Orchidaceae ) .
Bitis gabonica , most commonly known as the Gaboon viper , is a venomous viper species found in the rainforests and savannas of sub - Saharan Africa .
The Sharpe 's longclaw ( Hemimacronyx sharpei ) is a passerine bird in the longclaw family Motacillidae , which also includes the pipits and wagtails .
Brachaluteres is a genus of filefish of the family Monacanthidae .
The Alai mole vole ( Ellobius alaicus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Notarchus is a genus of sea slugs or sea hares , marine opisthobranch gastropod mollusks in the family Aplysiidae , the sea hares .
Coots are small water birds that are members of the Rallidae ( rail ) family .
The Myanmar arowana , Scleropages inscriptus , is a large , bony - tongued fish native to Myanmar .
The describers placed Bolong in Hadrosauroidea .
Psellocoptus is a genus of running spiders ( family Corinnidae , formerly Clubionidae ) that is endemic to Venezuela .
Sprivivirus is a genus of viruses in the order Mononegavirales , in the family Rhabdoviridae .
The Medeolariales are an order of the class Leotiomycetes within the phylum Ascomycota .
The Crowley 's tiger ( Parantica crowleyi ) is a species of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
David 's fulvetta ( Alcippe davidi ) is a species of bird in the Pellorneidae family .
The Puvel 's illadopsis ( Illadopsis puveli ) is a species of bird in the Pellorneidae family .
The Victorville shoulderband ( Helminthoglypta mohaveana ) is a species of land snail in the family Helminthoglyptidae .
The describers assigned Arthurdactylus to the Ornithocheiridae .
Solemyidae is a family of saltwater clams , marine protobranch bivalve mollusks in the order Solemyoida .
The Puerto Rican bullfinch ( Loxigilla portoricensis ) or comeñame in Spanish , is a small bullfinch tanager endemic to the archipelago of Puerto Rico and one of three species belonging to the genus Loxigilla .
The antpipits , Corythopis , are a genus of birds in the Tyrannidae family .
Melanthieae is a tribe of flowering plants within the family Melanthiaceae .
The Little Swan Island hutia ( Geocapromys thoracatus ) is an extinct species of rodent that lived on the Swan Islands , off north - eastern Honduras in the Caribbean .
The Oriental hobby ( Falco severus ) is a species of falcon typically 27 - -30 cm long .
The Trauna River tree frog ( Litoria oenicolen ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family , endemic to Papua New Guinea .
