The Meghalaya danio ( Danio meghalayensis ) is a recently discovered species of fish from the Meghalaya state , India .
The Sudell 's frog or painted burrowing frog ( Neobatrachus sudelli ) is a species of burrowing frog common to a large part of southeastern Australia .
The Malayan banded pitta ( Hydrornis irena ) is a species of bird in the Pittidae family .
The Okavango dwarf gecko or Chobe dwarf gecko ( Lygodactylus chobiensis ) is a species of gecko found along the Chobe and Zambesi Rivers and into the Okavango Delta , and into Mozambique , Zimbabwe and Zambia .
Beau 's wrasse , Cirrhilabrus beauperryi , is a species of wrasse native to the western Pacific Ocean .
Isotrilophus erraticus is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Isotrilophus .
The Yellow - spotted snake eel ( Callechelys lutea , also known as the Freckled snake eel ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
The Boyer 's cuckooshrike ( Coracina boyeri ) is a species of bird in the Campephagidae family .
The Ibiza rail ( Rallus eivissensis ) is a recently discovered fossil species of rail , described from a late Pleistocene to Holocene cave deposit at Es Pouàs , on the island of Ibiza .
The Semper 's warbler ( Leucopeza semperi ) is an extremely rare or possibly extinct New World warbler which is endemic to Saint Lucia , part of the Lesser Antilles .
Enneapterygius unimaculatus , known commonly as the Onespot triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
The Lulworth skipper ( Thymelicus acteon ) is a butterfly of the Hesperiidae family .
Acetabularia is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Polyphysaceae family , Typically found in subtropical waters , Acetabularia is a single - celled organism , but gigantic in size and complex in form , making it an excellent model organism for studying cell biology .
Pezizomycotina contains the filamentous ascomycetes and is a subphylum of the Ascomycota ( fungi which form their spores in a sac - like ascus ) .
The Garman New Guinea tree frog ( Litoria jeudii ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
The Bethylidae are a family of aculeate wasps in the superfamily Chrysidoidea .
Acangassuini is a beetle tribe in the Cerambycinae subfamily , containing the single genus Acangassu and the single species Acangassu diminuta .
The Australian snubfin dolphin ( Orcaella heinsohnri ) is a dolphin found off the northern coasts of Australia .
Gonatus is a genus of squid in the family Gonatidae , comprising twelve species , and therefore containing the most species in the family .
Marathonitidae is the only family in the Marathonitaceae superfamilies .
The Peters 's epauletted fruit bat ( Epomophorus crypturus ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae .
Fülleborn 's boubou ( Laniarius fuelleborni ) is a species of bird in the Malaconotidae family .
The Titicaca orestias ( Orestias cuvieri ) , also known by its native name amanto , is a likely extinct freshwater killifish from Lake Titicaca in South America .
Euroleon is an antlion genus in the family Myrmeleontidae .
Parapachycerina is a genus of small African flies of the family Lauxaniidae .
Geomela is a genus containing several small dark beetles in the family Chrysomelidae .
Trigenicus is a small extinct genus of Artiodactyla , of the family Protoceratidae , endemic to North America from the Late Eocene epoch ( Chadronian stage ) 37.2 - -33.9 Ma , existing for approximately 3.3 million years .
The Cunene horse mackerel ( Trachurus trecae ) is a species named after mackerel in the family Carangidae .
The Straneck 's tyrannulet ( Serpophaga griseicapilla ) , also known as the monte tyrannulet and grey - crowned tyrannulet , is a small species of bird in the Tyrannidae family .
Nauta salamander or Nauta mushroomtongue salamander ( Bolitoglossa altamazonica ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
Thermanaeromonas is a genus of bacteria within the family Thermoanaerobacteraceae .
Coosa shiner ( Notropis xaenocephalus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Notropis .
Scutellastra is a genus of sea snails with gills , typical true limpets , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Patellidae , the true limpets .
Beelzebub 's tube - nosed bat ( Murina beelzebub ) , also Beelzebub bat or demon bat , is a species in the vesper bat family Vespertilionidae , found in the Greater Mekong region of Southeast Asia , specifically the Quảng Trị and Gia Lai provinces of Vietnam .
Schidlovsky 's vole ( Microtus schidlovskii ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Burmese yuhina ( Yuhina humilis ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Gehyra is a genus of geckos known commonly as web - toed geckos or dtellas .
The Sardinian warbler ( Sylvia melanocephala ) is a common and widespread typical warbler from the Mediterranean region .
Together with Eucommia ulmoides the Garryaceae are currently placed by the Angiosperm Phylogeny Group in an own order , the Garryales .
The Maltese palpigrade ( Eukoenenia christiani , known as Il - Palpigrad ta ' Malta in Maltese ) , endemic to the Maltese Islands , comes from the order Palpigradi , a rather primitive order of arachnids .
The Anderson 's shrew ( Suncus stoliczkanus ) is a medium - sized species of shrew .
Pyropterus is a genus of net - winged beetles belonging to the family Lycidae .
Liopleurodon belongs to the family Pliosauridae , a clade within Plesiosauria , known from the Jurassic ( maybe also from the Cretaceous ) of Europe and North America .
Lobotos is a genus of bird in the cuckooshrike family Campephagidae .
The Malagasy slit - faced bat , ( Nycteris madagascariensis ) is a species of slit - faced bat in Madagascar .
Diplommatinidae is a family of small land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Cyclophoroidea .
Thomas 's mosaic - tailed rat ( Paramelomys mollis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
The San Esteban Island mouse ( Peromyscus stephani ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Myrceugenia is a genus of evergreen woody flowering trees and shrubs belonging to the myrtle family , Myrtaceae , first described as a genus in 1855 .
Theocolax is a parasitic wasps genus in the family Pteromalidae .
Uronautes is a dubious genus of extinct plesiosaur from the family Rhomaleosauridae .
Scaphytopiini is a tribe of leafhoppers in the subfamily Deltocephalinae .
The Aristideae is the sole tribe of grasses in the monotypic subfamily Aristidoideae of the true grass family Poaceae .
The Arfak Mountains frog ( Hylarana arfaki ) is a species of true frog in the genus Hylarana .
Cypseloides is a genus of swift in the Apodidae family .
Pleuronectinae is a subfamily of fish in the Pleuronectidae family , comprising 27 genera and 62 extant species ( there are also fossil species , including two Clidoderma ) .
The Yapacana antbird ( Myrmeciza disjuncta ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
The Saint Lucia lancehead or Saint Lucia pit viper ( Bothrops caribbaeus ) is a species of venomous snake which is endemic to the West Indies .

The FIE Fencing World Cup is an international fencing competition held by the Fédération Internationale d'Escrime .
The Hank Aaron Award is given annually to the Major League Baseball ( MLB ) players selected as the top hitter in each league , as voted on by baseball fans and members of the media .
Gert Ligterink ( born 17 November 1949 in Oldekerk ) is a Dutch chess player .
The Larkana Bulls is a limited overs cricket team based in Larkana , Sindh , Pakistan .
Romain Taofifénua ( born 14 September 1990 in Mont - de - Marsan ) is a French rugby union player , playing as Lock for Toulon in the Top 14 .
Parallel bars is an apparatus used by gymnasts in artistic gymnastics .
Lowell Hamilton ( born May 3 , 1966 ) was a former high school and college basketball player during the 1980s .
Dwayne Anderson , II ( born June 22 , 1986 ) is an American basketball coach .
Vladimir Krstić ( born July 27 , 1972 in Osijek , SR Croatia , SFR Yugoslavia ) is a Croatian professional basketball coach and former professional player .
Ties Kruize ( born 17 November 1952 ) is a former field hockey player from the Netherlands .
Bradley Ronald Johnstone ( born 30 July 1950 ) , known as Brad Johnstone , is a former New Zealand rugby union footballer and a current coach .
FK Šaca is a Slovak association football club located in Šaca which is a borough of Košice .
The South London Pirates , known until 2012 as the Croydon Pirates , is a British baseball club based in South London .
Trine Haltvik ( born March 23 , 1965 in Trondheim ) is a Norwegian handball coach and former player .
Callaway Golf Company is an American global sporting goods company that designs , manufactures , markets and sells golf equipment , golf accessories and golf lifestyle - related products in more than 70 countries worldwide .
Viljar Veski ( born April 29 , 1986 ) is an Estonian basketball player , who currently plays in the Spanish third division for Palma Air Europa .
Marco Salvatore ( born February 20 , 1986 ) is an Austrian professional association football player currently playing for SV Horn in the Austrian Football First League .
Juvenia Stadium ( Polish : Stadion Juvenii Kraków ) is a rugby union stadium in Kraków , Poland .
The Greatest Baseball Game Never Played was a 1982 simulated broadcast of a hypothetical baseball game between all - time Major League Baseball greats .
Stanley Havili ( born November 14 , 1987 ) is an American football fullback who is on the Seattle Seahawks practice squad .
Mélodie Daoust ( born January 7 , 1992 ) is a women 's ice hockey player from Canada .
Paola Croce ( born March 6 , 1978 in Rome ) is an Italian volleyball player , who plays as a libero .
The Naismith College Player of the Year is an annual basketball award given by the Atlanta Tipoff Club to the top men 's and women 's collegiate basketball players .
Kimmie Meissner began figure skating at age six after watching her older brothers playing ice hockey .
The 1959 Scottish Cup Final was an association football match between St Mirren F.C. and Aberdeen F.C. on 25 April 1959 at Hampden Park in Glasgow , Scotland .
The Chess Monthly was a short - lived monthly chess magazine produced from January 1857 and May 1861 in the United States .
The Toledo Goaldiggers were a minor professional ice hockey club based in Toledo , OH from 1974 - 1986 .
The Melbourne Ice are a semi - professional ice hockey team in the Australian Ice Hockey League .
Mason Cole ( born March 28 , 1996 ) is an American football player .
Andrew Jarrett ( born 9 January 1958 in Belper , Derbyshire , England ) , is a former professional tennis player from the United Kingdom .
Rotherham Giants is a rugby league team based in Rotherham , South Yorkshire , playing in the Yorkshire Premier of the Rugby League Conference .
Hélio Rubens Garcia ( born Franca , Brazil , September 2 , 1940 ) , known as Hélio Rubens , is a former Brazilian basketball player and coach .
The Nelson Mandela Challenge Plate is a rugby union trophy contested between Australia and South Africa .
The Rugby Nordic Cup is the biggest club rugby union tournament in Scandinavia , annually pitching the champions of each Nordic county against each other to find out who is the best .
Paul Maurice ( born January 30 , 1967 ) is a Canadian former ice hockey player and current head coach of the Winnipeg Jets of the National Hockey League ( NHL ) .
The Southampton Trailblazers were a basketball club based in Southampton , England , which competed in the English Basketball League Division 3 ( South ) at the time of the club 's demise .
Kyle Connor ( born December 9 , 1996 ) is an American ice hockey player , who currently plays college ice hockey for the Michigan Wolverines of the Big Ten Conference .
Greg Pankewicz ( born October 6 , 1970 ) is a Canadian ice hockey coach and former professional ice hockey player .
The Japan national under-17 football team is a national association football youth team of Japan and is controlled by the Japan Football Association .
The Czech Women 's Handball First Division is the premier category of the Czech Republic 's women 's handball national league .
Terry Simpson ( born August 30 , 1943 in Brantford , Ontario ) is a retired Canadian professional ice hockey player and a former NHL head coach .
The Hokkaido Marathon held in Sapporo , Hokkaidō , Japan , is one of the prominent marathon races of the year .
Neerim - Neerim South Football Club , nicknamed The Cats , is an Australian rules football club in the Ellinbank & District Football League .
The UEFA Women 's Euro 2013 Final was an association football match on 28 July 2013 at the Friends Arena in Solna , Sweden , to determine the winner of UEFA Women 's Euro 2013 .
Kristina Elez ( born 22 May 1987 as Kristina Franić ) is a Croatian handball player and a member of the Croatian national team .
Max Harmonist ( Berlin , 10 February 1864 - -16 October 1907 ) was a leading German chess master .
Hedera canariensis is a species of Ivy ( genus Hedera ) which is native to the Atlantic coast in Canary islands and northern Africa .
Olga Sober ( Šober ) ( born in Sarajevo ) is an opera singer and leading soprano in the Croatian National Theatre in Rijeka .
Giuseppina Ronzi de Begnis ( born Giuseppina Ronzi ; Milan 11 January 1800 - died , Florence , 7 June 1853 ) was an Italian soprano opera singer famous for the roles written for her by the prominent composers of the 1820s and 1830s .
Pauline Wales ( born 1938 ) is an English singer and actress best known for her performances in the mezzo - soprano roles of the Gilbert and Sullivan operas with the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company .
Teresa Stolz ( born 2 June 1834 , Elbekosteletz ( Czech : Kostelec nad Labem ) , Bohemia -- died 23 August 1902 , Milan ) was a Bohemian soprano , long resident in Italy , who was associated with significant premieres of the works of Giuseppe Verdi , and may have been his mistress .
Joan Pons Álvarez ( Ciutadella , Spain , 8 August 1946 ) , is a Spanish operatic baritone , known internationally as Juan Pons .
Therese Malten was the stage name of Therese Müller ( 21 June 1855 -- 2 January 1930 ) , a well - known German dramatic soprano .
Jessica Rivera ( born 1974 ) is an American soprano of Peruvian - American ancestry .
Beverly Bower ( September 30 , 1925 -- March 24 , 2002 ) was an American operatic soprano who had an active international opera career from the mid-1950s through the early 1970s .
Aprile Millo ( born April 14 , 1958 ) is an American operatic soprano of Italian and Irish ancestry who is particularly admired for her interpretations of the works of Giuseppe Verdi .
Stoyanka Savova Nikolova , best known by her stage name Elena Nicolai ( 24 January 1905 -- 23 October 1993 ) , was a Bulgarian mezzo - soprano and opera singer .
Pavel Koshetz ( Russian : Павел Алексеевич Кошиц ; real last name is Poray - Koshetz ( ru:Порай-Кошиц ) ; December 14 , 1863 in Kiev Oblast , Russian Empire -- March 2 , 1904 in Moscow ) was a Russian opera singer ( tenor ) .
Joanne Lunn is an English classical soprano in opera and concert .
Claramae Turner ( née Haas , October 28 , 1920 - May 18 , 2013 ) was an American operatic contralto , perhaps best known for her appearance in the film Carousel ( 1956 ) , adapted from the Rodgers and Hammerstein stage musical of the same name .
James Billings ( born 1932 , Springfield , Missouri ) is an American operatic baritone , librettist , and opera director .
Eva Mylott ( 1875 - 20 March 1920 ) was an Australian contralto opera singer .
Giuditta Grisi ( 28 July 1805 -- 1 May 1840 ) was an Italian operatic mezzo - soprano , sister of soprano Giulia Grisi and cousin of ballerina Carlotta Grisi .
Karan Armstrong ( born December 14 , 1941 , Havre , Montana ) is an American operatic soprano , who is celebrated as a singing - actress .
Giacomo Lauri - Volpi ( December 11 , 1892 -- March 17 , 1979 ) was an Italian tenor with a lyric - dramatic voice of exceptional range and technical facility .
Zhang Liping ( simplified Chinese : 张立萍 ; traditional Chinese : 張立萍 ; born 1965 ) is a Chinese - Canadian soprano , who has sung leading roles in the opera houses of both Europe and North America .
Hélène Bouvier ( June 20 , 1905 , Paris -- March 11 , 1978 , Paris ) was a French operatic mezzo - soprano , particularly associated with the French repertoire .
Anton Schott ( born Schloss Staufeneck , Bavaria , June 24 , 1846 - died Stuttgart , January 6 , 1913 ) was a German dramatic tenor .

Kari Rueslåtten ( Trondheim , October 3 , 1973 ) is a Norwegian soprano singer , songwriter and keyboardist , who was well known for being the former lead singer and songwriter for the now disbanded Norwegian doom metal / experimental band , The 3rd and the Mortal from 1992 to 1994 .
Colette Alliot - Lugaz ( born 20 July 1947 ) is a French soprano , particularly associated with Mozart .
Elvira Casazza ( 15 November 1887 -- 24 January 1965 ) was an Italian mezzo - soprano opera singer ( also known as Elvira Mari - Casazza ) .
Ana María Martínez ( born 1971 ) is a Puerto Rican - American soprano .
Gustáv Papp ( 28 September 1919 -- 7 October 1997 ) was a Slovak operatic tenor who had an active international career during the 1940s through the 1980s .
Romilda Pantaleoni ( 1847 -- 20 May 1917 ) was an Italian soprano who had a prolific opera career in Italy during the 1870s and 1880s .
Marie Te Hapuku ( formerly Marie - Adele McArthur ) is an operatic soprano from Gisborne , New Zealand and is a direct descendant of the Māori chief , Te Hapuku .
Jörg Dürmüller ( born 28 August 1959 in Bern ) is a Swiss classical tenor in concert and opera .
Marie Selika Williams ( c. 1849 - -1937 ) was an American coloratura soprano .
Gitta Alpár ( née Regina Klopfer ; 5 February 1903 -- 17 February 1991 ) , was a Hungarian - born opera and operetta soprano .
Jon Garrison ( né Jon Long ; born December 11 , 1944 in Higginsville , Missouri ) is a successful American operatic tenor who has been performing in locations around the world since 1965 .
Richard Mayr ( 18 November 1877 , in Henndorf -- 1 December 1935 , in Vienna ) was an Austrian operatic bass - baritone who was particularly admired for his performances in works by Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart , Richard Wagner and Richard Strauss .
Anthony Stuart Lloyd ( born 1967 , Cardiff ) is a Welsh baritone opera singer from Wales .
Giuseppe Giacomini ( * September 7 , 1940 ; Veggiano near Padua , Italy ) is an Italian dramatic tenor .
Hermann Prey ( 11 July 1929 -- 22 July 1998 ) was a German lyric baritone , best known for his lieder renditions and for light comic roles in opera .
Pierre Gaveaux ( 9 October 1761 -- 5 February 1825 ) was a French operatic tenor and composer , notable for creating the role of Jason in Cherubini 's Médée and for composing Leonore ou l'amour conjugal , the first operatic version of the story that later found fame as Fidelio .
Stuart Howe ( July 19 , 1967 ) is an operatic tenor who has become particularly noted for his interpretation of the heroic roles of Rossini and Donizetti .
Anna Kasyan ( Armenian : Աննա Կասյան ) is a Georgian - born Armenian opera singer ( soprano ) living in France .
Marietta Marcolini ( born c. 1780 -- date of death unknown ) was an Italian operatic contralto .
Nikos Gounaris ( Greek : Νίκος Γούναρης ; 1915 -- 5 May 1965 in Athens ) was a Greek tenor who was enormously popular as a `` pop '' singer in the 1950s .
Georgine von Milinkovič ( July 7 , 1913 , Prague - February 26 , 1986 , Munich ) was a Croatian operatic mezzo - soprano of Czech birth , particularly associated with Wagner and Strauss roles .
A singer ( mezzo - soprano ) and composer herself , Elsa Respighi created ballets out of Respighi 's Ancient Airs and Dances suites and completed his final opera Lucrezia in 1937 .
Petre Munteanu ( 26 November 1916 - 18 July 1988 ) was a Romanian operatic tenor particularly associated with Mozart and lighter Italian roles .
Clémentine Delauney ( born 11 February 1987 ) is a French soprano singer from Lyon .
Andreas Dippel ( 30 November 1866 -- 12 May 1932 ) was a German - born operatic tenor and impresario who from 1908 to 1910 was the joint manager ( with Giulio Gatti - Casazza ) of the New York Metropolitan Opera .
Delores Ziegler ( born 4 September 1951 ) is an American mezzo - soprano who has had an active international performance career since the late 1970s .
Giovanni Paroli ( 1856 , Brescia - 1920 , Brescia ) was an Italian operatic tenor who had an active international performance career for four decades .
James Oldfield ( born in October 1981 in Ipswich , UK ) is an English bass - baritone .
Margarete Teschemacher ( 3 March 1903 -- 19 May 1959 ) was a German operatic soprano , particularly associated with the German repertory , although she sang a wide range of roles .
Radmila Bakočević ( Serbian Cyrillic : Радмила Бакочевић , pronounced ( rǎdmila bakɔ̌ːtʃɛʋitɕ ) ; born January 5 , 1933 ) , is a Serbian operatic soprano who had a major international opera career that began in 1955 and ended upon her retirement from the stage in 1982 .
Niels Jacob Hansen ( 1880 - -1969 ) was a Danish tenor , mostly famous for his roles in opera .
Arthur Fear ( 1902 - -1984 ) was a Welsh bass and baritone opera singer .
Gary Lehman is an American operatic tenor , specialising in the Heldentenor repertoire .
Laura Macrì ( born 29 June 1990 in Caltanissetta , Sicily , Italy ) is a Sicilian - Italian soprano singer .
Lubomír Havlák ( 27 December 1921 -- 28 September 2014 ) was a Czech dramatic tenor born at Fryčovice near Ostrava ( former Czechoslovakia ) .
Christian du Plessis ( born 2 July 1944 ) is a South African baritone , largely based in England , and particularly associated with the bel canto repertory .
Roberta Alexander ( born 3 March 1949 , in Lynchburg , Virginia ) is an American operatic soprano .
Giuseppe Filianoti ( born 11 January 1974 ) is an Italian lyric tenor from Reggio Calabria .
John Ken Nuzzo ( ジョン・健・ヌッツォ , born 5 May 1966 in Tokyo ) is a Japanese - Italian tenor .
Naděžda Kniplová ( née Pokorná ) ( born 18 April 1932 ) is a Czech operatic soprano who had an active international career from the 1950s through the 1980s .
Roberta Peters ( born May 4 , 1930 ) is an American coloratura soprano .
Aino Ackté ( originally Achte ; 23 April 1876 -- 8 August 1944 ) was a Finnish soprano .
Korliss Uecker is an American vocalist ( soprano ) from Hettinger , North Dakota .
Gerd Türk is a German classical tenor .
Anna de Belocca ( née de Bellokh ) ( 4 January 1854 -- unknown ) , was a Russian - born operatic contralto .
Ján Koehler ( died 28 June 1895 ) was a Polish operatic baritone .
Hilary Summers is a Welsh dramatic contralto .
Jennifer Vyvyan ( 13 March 1925 -- 5 April 1974 ) was a British classical soprano who had an active international career in operas , concerts , and recitals from 1948 up until her death in 1974 .
Elisabetta Manfredini - Guarmani ( 2 June 1780 -- after 1828 ) was an Italian opera singer best known for having created the leading soprano roles in four of Rossini 's operas , roles which he wrote specifically for her voice .
Maria Reining ( August 7 , 1903 in Vienna -- March 11 , 1991 in Deggendorf ) was an Austrian soprano and Kammersänger .
Heinrich Sontheim ( 1820 - -1912 ) , also known as Honas Bär Sontheimer , was a prominent late-19th - Century tenor and kammersänger ( chamber singer ) based in Stuttgart , Germany .
Pierre Jélyotte ( 13 April 1713 -- 11 September 1797 ) was a French operatic tenor , particularly associated with works by Rameau , Lully , Campra , Mondonville and Destouches .
Vyacheslav Polozov ( born January 1 , 1950 ) is an operatic spinto tenor from the former Ukrainian SSR .
Anne Sofie von Otter ( born 9 May 1955 ) is a Swedish mezzo - soprano whose repertoire encompasses lieder , operas , oratorios and also rock and pop songs .
Vincent Niclo ( born in Paris on 6 January 1975 ) is a French light pop tenor singer .
Dino Borgioli ( February 15 , 1891 -- September 12 , 1960 ) was an Italian lyric tenor .
Salvador Novoa ( born in Mexico City , Mexico , on October 30 , 1937 ) is a Mexican dramatic tenor .
Aloys Pennarini , also spelled Alois Pennarini , ( born Aloys Federler ; June 21 , 1870 in Vienna , Austria - Hungary -- June 23 , 1927 in Liberec , Czechoslovakia ) , was an opera singer ( tenor ) , opera director and film actor .
John Gostling ( 1644 - -1733 ) was a 17th - century Church of England clergyman and bass singer famed for his range and power .
